{"title_page": "Vidya Balan", "text_new": "{{short description|Indian film actress}}\n{{pp-blp|expiry=indef|small=yes}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2019}}\n{{featured article}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=May 2013}}\n{{Indian name|Vidya|Balan}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Vidya Balan\n| image              = Vidya Balan promoting Mission Mangal.jpg\n| alt                = Vidya Balan poses for the camera\n| caption            = Vidya promoting Mission Mangal in 2019\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1979|1|1|df=y}}\n| birth_place        = [[Bombay]], Maharashtra, India\n| alma_mater         = [[University of Mumbai]]\n| occupation         = Actress\n| yearsactive        = 1995, 2003\u2013present\n| spouse             = {{married|[[Siddharth Roy Kapur]]|2012}}\n| works              = [[Vidya Balan filmography|Full list]]\n| awards             = [[List of awards and nominations received by Vidya Balan|Full list]]\n| honours            = [[Padma Shri]] (2014)\n}}\n\n'''Vidya Balan''' (pronounced {{IPA-hns|\u028b\u026ad\u032aja\u02d0 ba\u02d0l\u0259n|}}; born 1 January 1979) is an Indian actress. Known for pioneering a change in the portrayal of women in [[Bollywood|Hindi cinema]] with her roles in female-led films, she is the recipient of [[List of awards and nominations received by Vidya Balan|several awards]], including a [[National Film Awards|National Film Award]] and six [[Filmfare Awards]]. She was awarded the [[Padma Shri]] by the [[Government of India]] in 2014.\n\nVidya aspired to a career in film from a young age and had her first acting role in the 1995 sitcom ''[[Hum Paanch (TV series)|Hum Paanch]]''. She pursued a master's degree in sociology from the [[University of Mumbai]] and simultaneously made several unsuccessful attempts to start a career in film. She subsequently featured in television commercials and music videos. In 2003 she made her feature film debut by starring in the independent [[Cinema of West Bengal|Bengal]]i drama ''[[Bhalo Theko]]''. Vidya subsequently received praise for her first Hindi film, the drama ''[[Parineeta (2005 film)|Parineeta]]'', and followed it with a leading role in the top-grossing comedy film ''[[Lage Raho Munna Bhai]]'' (2006).\n\nThis breakthrough was followed by roles in the romantic comedies ''[[Heyy Babyy]]'' (2007) and ''[[Kismat Konnection]]'' (2008) which had negative reviews. Vidya went on to establish herself by playing five consecutive roles to critical acclaim in the 2009 drama ''[[Paa (film)|Paa]]'', the 2010 black comedy ''[[Ishqiya]]'', the 2011 semi-biographical thriller ''[[No One Killed Jessica]]'', the 2011 biopic ''[[The Dirty Picture]]'', and the 2012 thriller ''[[Kahaani]]'', winning several awards for each of them. She followed this with a series of films that performed poorly at the box office, although her performance in ''[[Kahaani 2: Durga Rani Singh]]'' (2016) was praised. This changed when she starred as a radio jockey in ''[[Tumhari Sulu]]'' (2017) and a scientist in ''[[Mission Mangal]]'' (2019). The latter ranks as her highest-grossing release.\n\nVidya also promotes humanitarian causes and supports the empowerment of women. She is a member of the Indian [[Central Board of Film Certification]] and hosts a radio show. She initially drew criticism for her fluctuating weight and dress sense, but was later credited in the media for her unconventionality. Vidya is married to the film producer [[Siddharth Roy Kapur]].\n\n==Early life and initial career struggles==\nVidya was born on 1 January 1979 in [[Mumbai|Bombay]] (present-day Mumbai),<ref>{{cite web |url=https://in.style.yahoo.com/real-age-vidya-balan-not-wikipedia-saying-100458995.html |title=This Is Real Age Of Vidya Balan And Not What Wikipedia Is Saying |publisher=Yahoo Lifestyle |accessdate=6 December 2016 |date=6 December 2016 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161206114826/https://in.style.yahoo.com/real-age-vidya-balan-not-wikipedia-saying-100458995.html |archivedate=6 December 2016 |df= }}</ref> to parents of [[Tamil people|Tamilian]] descent.<ref>{{cite web|title=Temple wedding for Vidya Balan and Siddharth Roy Kapur |url=http://movies.ndtv.com/bollywood/temple-wedding-for-vidya-balan-and-siddharth-roy-kapur-630333 |date=11 December 2012 |accessdate=24 May 2015 |publisher=NDTV |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150524154305/http://movies.ndtv.com/bollywood/temple-wedding-for-vidya-balan-and-siddharth-roy-kapur-630333 |archivedate=24 May 2015 |df= }}</ref> Her father, P. R. Balan, is the executive vice-president of Digicable and her mother, Saraswathy Balan, is a homemaker.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.digicable.in/index.php/about-us/management-team |title=Management team, Digicable |publisher=Digicable |accessdate=20 February 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130531084316/http://digicable.in/index.php/about-us/management-team |archivedate=31 May 2013 |df= }}</ref><ref name=\"something\"/><ref>\n{{cite news|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/over-the-years-vidya-balan-goes-from-geek-to-haute/story-CY7LmU3wv2Crat773i7dyL.html|title=Over the years: Vidya Balan from geek to haute!|author=Bansal, Robin|date=22 September 2012|work=Hindustan Times|accessdate=24 September 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171009195047/http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/over-the-years-vidya-balan-goes-from-geek-to-haute/story-CY7LmU3wv2Crat773i7dyL.html|archive-date=9 October 2017|url-status=live}}\n</ref> According to Vidya, they speak a mix of [[Tamil language|Tamil]] and [[Malayalam]] at home.<ref>{{cite news|work=The Hindu |url=http://www.hindu.com/fr/2007/02/16/stories/2007021600410100.htm |date=16 February 2007 |accessdate=9 August 2011 |author=Siddiqui, Rana |title=`It's a dream come true' |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120114155348/http://www.hindu.com/fr/2007/02/16/stories/2007021600410100.htm |archivedate=14 January 2012 |df= }}</ref> Her elder sister, Priya Balan, works in advertising.<ref name=\"something\">\n{{cite news |title=There's something about Vidya |url=http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P3-1168964461.html |work=Hindustan Times {{Subscription required|via=[[HighBeam Research]]}} |accessdate=23 September 2012 |date=25 November 2006 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131011162727/http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P3-1168964461.html |archivedate=11 October 2013  }}\n</ref> The actress [[Priyamani]] is her second cousin.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-filmi-family-tree-know-priyamanis-famous-relative/20131008.htm#1 |title=Filmi Family Tree: Know Priyamani's famous relative? |publisher=Rediff.com |date=8 October 2013 |accessdate=16 April 2014 |pages=2 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140203040650/http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-filmi-family-tree-know-priyamanis-famous-relative/20131008.htm |archivedate= 3 February 2014 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/tabloid/hyderabad/not-going-ask-vidya-balan-advice-priyamani-672 | title=Not going to ask Vidya Balan for advice: Priyamani | work=Deccan Chronicle | date=11 May 2012 | accessdate=16 April 2014 | author=Prakash, B. V. S. | archiveurl=https://wayback.archive-it.org/all/20120512011620/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/tabloid/hyderabad/not-going-ask-vidya-balan-advice-priyamani-672 | archivedate=12 May 2012}}</ref>\n\nVidya grew up in the suburban neighbourhood of [[Chembur]], Mumbai and attended St. Anthony Girls' High School.<ref>{{cite news|title=Celeb diary: Vidya Balan |url=http://www.mid-day.com/entertainment/2010/feb/040210-Celeb-Dairy-Vidya-Balan.htm |accessdate=24 May 2012 |work=Mid Day |date=4 February 2010 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130103041053/http://www.mid-day.com/entertainment/2010/feb/040210-Celeb-Dairy-Vidya-Balan.htm |archivedate= 3 January 2013 |df= }}</ref><ref>\n{{cite news|last=Gupta|first=Priya|title=I have never done a barter with God: Vidya Balan|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-09-17/news-interviews/42114811_1_ganpati-vidya-balan-aarti|accessdate=26 January 2014|work=The Times of India|date=17 September 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140202185556/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-09-17/news-interviews/42114811_1_ganpati-vidya-balan-aarti|archive-date=2 February 2014|url-status=live}}\n</ref> From a young age, she aspired to a career in film and was inspired by the work of actors [[Shabana Azmi]] and [[Madhuri Dixit]].<ref name=\"rules\"/><ref>{{cite web|publisher=CNN-IBN |url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/madhuri-was-my-inspiration-in-life-vidya-balan/218414-8-66.html |date=6 January 2012 |accessdate=13 October 2012 |title=Madhuri is my inspiration in life: Vidya Balan |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120420044855/http://ibnlive.in.com/news/madhuri-was-my-inspiration-in-life-vidya-balan/218414-8-66.html |archivedate=20 April 2012 |df= }}</ref> At the age of 16, she starred in the first season of [[Ekta Kapoor]]'s sitcom ''[[Hum Paanch (TV series)|Hum Paanch]]'' as Radhika, a bespectacled teenager.<ref>{{cite news |last=Ganguly |first=Pritwish |title=I said no to Ekta: Vidya Balan |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2010-10-22/news-interviews/28271540_1_tv-debut-vidya-balan-s-homepage-audition |accessdate=23 September 2012 |work=The Times of India |date=22 October 2010 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131023060327/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2010-10-22/news-interviews/28271540_1_tv-debut-vidya-balan-s-homepage-audition |archivedate=23 October 2013 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref><ref name=\"tree\">{{cite news|url=http://www.telegraphindia.com/1100725/jsp/7days/story_12723277.jsp |title=It could have been George Clooney or a tree. I would have made love to the tree if I had to |first=Draupadi |last=Rohera |work=The Telegraph |accessdate=19 November 2012 |date=25 June 2010 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130313102649/http://www.telegraphindia.com/1100725/jsp/7days/story_12723277.jsp |archivedate=13 March 2013 |df= }}</ref> After the series ended, Vidya refused director [[Anurag Basu]]'s offer to star in a television soap opera, as she wanted to concentrate on a film career.<ref name=\"native\">{{cite news |last=Bamzai |first=Kaveree |title=Return of the native |url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/Return+of+the+native/1/82489.html |accessdate=23 September 2012 |work=India Today |date=4 February 2010 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121023235254/http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/Return+of+the+native/1/82489.html |archivedate=23 October 2012 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref> Her parents were supportive of the decision but encouraged her to complete her education first.<ref name=\"rules\">\n{{cite news|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/why-vidya-balan-rules/story-kBrnl5alAyNYS51Hzl2JNL.html|title=Why Vidya Balan rules|author=Sanghvi, Vir|date=17 December 2011|work=Hindustan Times|accessdate=11 January 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180708081025/https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/why-vidya-balan-rules/story-kBrnl5alAyNYS51Hzl2JNL.html|archive-date=8 July 2018|url-status=live}}\n</ref> She attended [[St. Xavier's College, Mumbai|St. Xavier's College]] to pursue a bachelor's degree in [[sociology]] and later earned a master's degree from the [[University of Mumbai]].<ref>{{cite news |work=The Times of India |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-01-09/news-interviews/28367559_1_sociology-films-khar |date=9 January 2011 |accessdate=23 August 2012 |title=Sociology was my major subject: Vidya |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131023055734/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-01-09/news-interviews/28367559_1_sociology-films-khar |archivedate=23 October 2013 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Just how educated are our Bollywood heroines? |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-just-how-educated-are-bollywood-heroines/20120118.htm |publisher=Rediff |accessdate=20 November 2012 |date=18 January 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20130201061849/http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-just-how-educated-are-bollywood-heroines/20120118.htm |archivedate= 1 February 2013 |df= }}</ref>\n\nWhile pursuing her master's degree, Vidya was cast as the female lead in the [[Malayalam cinema|Malayalam film]] ''Chakram'', opposite [[Mohanlal]] and was subsequently signed on for 12 other Malayalam language films.<ref name=\"rules\"/> However, due to production difficulties, ''Chakram'' was shelved.<ref name=\"beginning\"/> The postponement of a film starring Mohanlal was an unheard occurrence in Malayalam cinema and producers blamed Vidya for bringing \"bad luck\" to the project; labelled her as a \"jinx\"; and replaced her in the films that she had been contracted for.<ref name=\"rules\"/> She shifted focus to [[Tamil cinema]]. In 2001, she was cast as the female lead in [[N. Linguswamy]]'s ''[[Run (2002 film)|Run]]'' (2002). However, after completing the first [[shooting schedule]], she was unceremoniously dropped and replaced by [[Meera Jasmine]].<ref>{{cite web|title=The Vidya magic! |publisher=Sify |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/the-vidya-magic-news-tamil-kkfv22bcabh.html |accessdate=23 November 2006 |date=7 July 2005 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131222210357/http://www.sify.com/movies/the-vidya-magic-news-tamil-kkfv22bcabh.html |archivedate=22 December 2013 |df= }}</ref> She was signed up under false pretences for a [[sex comedy]], a genre she was uncomfortable with, and decided to leave the project.<ref name=\"rules\"/> Thereafter, she signed on for a third Tamil film, ''[[Manasellam]]'' (2003), but was replaced by [[Trisha (actress)|Trisha]] as the director was dissatisfied with her work.<ref>{{cite news |title=When Vidya Balan was kicked out |work=The Times of India |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-03-13/did-you-know-/31160200_1_vidya-balan-hindi-films-south-filmmakers |accessdate=23 March 2012 |date=7 July 2005 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131023114243/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-07-13/did-you-know-/31160200_1_vidya-balan-hindi-films-south-filmmakers |archivedate=23 October 2013 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref> ''[[Kalari Vikraman]]'', another Malayalam film that she completed work for in 2003, failed to get a theatrical release.<ref>{{cite journal|title=Kalari Vikraman from Jail|journal=[[Vellinakshatram (magazine)|Vellinakshatram]]|date=5 January 2003}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=\u0d38\u0d3e\u0d15\u0d4d\u0d37\u0d30\u0d24\u0d2f\u0d41\u0d33\u0d4d\u0d33 \u0d15\u0d47\u0d30\u0d33\u0d24\u0d4d\u0d24\u0d3f\u0d7d \u0d05\u0d28\u0d4d\u0d27\u0d35\u0d3f\u0d36\u0d4d\u0d35\u0d3e\u0d38\u0d3f\u0d15\u0d7e \u0d15\u0d42\u0d1f\u0d41\u0d24\u0d32\u0d46\u0d28\u0d4d\u0d28\u0d4d\u200c \u0d35\u0d3f\u0d26\u0d4d\u0d2f\u0d3e\u0d2c\u0d3e\u0d32\u0d7b |url=http://www.malayalivartha.com/cinema/star-trek/35679 |publisher=[[Mangalam]] |accessdate=30 January 2017 |date=27 April 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170202041234/http://www.malayalivartha.com/cinema/star-trek/35679 |archivedate= 2 February 2017 |df= }}</ref> After failing to start a film career, Vidya appeared in approximately 60 television commercials and in music videos for [[Euphoria (Indian band)|Euphoria]] and [[Shubha Mudgal]]; a majority of these were directed by [[Pradeep Sarkar]].<ref name=\"native\"/><ref>\n{{cite news |title=Stand-out act four not-so-new newcomers have found critical acclaim in breakthrough roles this year. Now all they need is stardom |url=http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P2-10956992.html |work=India Today {{Subscription required|via=[[HighBeam Research]]}} |accessdate=23 September 2012 |date=18 July 2005 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131105232954/http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P2-10956992.html |archivedate=5 November 2013  }}\n</ref>\n\n==Career==\n{{see also|Vidya Balan filmography}}\n\n===Film debut and breakthrough (2003\u20132008)===\n[[File:Vidyabalan.jpg|left|upright=1.0|thumb|alt=Vidya Balan is looking directly at the camera.|Vidya at the launch of a book based on her film ''[[Lage Raho Munna Bhai]]'' (2006). The film ranks among her highest-grossing releases.<ref name=\"all-time\"/>]]\nIn 2003, Vidya was signed on by [[Goutam Halder]] for his independent [[Cinema of West Bengal|Bengali]] drama ''[[Bhalo Theko]]'': her first film release.<ref>{{cite news|title=Love for Bengal: A mystery in Vidya Balan's life|url= http://www.indianexpress.com/news/love-for-bengal-a-mystery-in-vidya-balans-life/819021/|work=The Indian Express|accessdate=24 October 2013|date=18 July 2011}}</ref> Her portrayal of Anandi, a young woman reminiscing about her past, won her an [[Anandalok Awards|Anandalok Purashkar]] for Best Actress.<ref>\n{{cite news|title=I feel I was Bengali in my last life: Vidya Balan|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/i-feel-i-was-bengali-in-my-last-life-vidya-balan/story-usw68eTdzeG4nxfJ6QAdkM.html|work=Hindustan Times|accessdate=23 March 2012|date=1 February 2008|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171203153803/http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/i-feel-i-was-bengali-in-my-last-life-vidya-balan/story-usw68eTdzeG4nxfJ6QAdkM.html|archive-date=3 December 2017|url-status=live}}\n</ref> Vidya made her Hindi film debut in 2005 with Pradeep Sarkar's musical drama ''[[Parineeta (2005 film)|Parineeta]]''. Before being cast, she had to undergo extensive auditions for six months.<ref name=\"beginning\">{{cite web|accessdate=23 October 2007 |first=Ronjita |last=Kulkarni |url=http://specials.rediff.com/movies/2005/jun/08vidya2.htm |title=Meet the new girl in Saif's life |publisher=Rediff |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071109164805/http://specials.rediff.com/movies/2005/jun/08vidya2.htm |archivedate= 9 November 2007 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|accessdate=20 November 2012 |date=1 January 2009 |url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/1158478/Small-people-with-big-egosnot-for-me-Vidhu-Vinod-Chopra |title=Small people with big egos, not for me! |publisher=Bollywood Hungama |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131023060206/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/1158478/Small-people-with-big-egosnot-for-me-Vidhu-Vinod-Chopra |archivedate=23 October 2013 |df= }}</ref> The film, an adaptation of [[Sarat Chandra Chattopadhyay]]'s [[Parineeta (novel)|novel of the same name]], narrated the love story of an idealist Lalita (Vidya) and a musician Shekhar ([[Saif Ali Khan]]), the son of a capitalist businessman.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.telegraphindia.com/1050611/asp/nation/story_4854277.asp |title=Parineeta breathes Bengal among the tulips |first=Pratim D. |last=Gupta |date=10 June 2005 |accessdate=9 August 2011 |work=The Telegraph |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110629155510/http://www.telegraphindia.com/1050611/asp/nation/story_4854277.asp |archivedate=29 June 2011 |df= }}</ref> Her performance in the film was praised by critics;<ref name=\"tree\"/> Derek Elley from ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'' wrote, \"An acting revelation is Tamil newcomer [Vidya] Balan, whose devoted but dignified Lalita is the picture's heart and soul.\"<ref>{{cite news|accessdate=27 October 2007|url=http://www.variety.com/review/VE1117929519.html?categoryId=31&cs=1 |title=Parineeta: Film review |first=Derek |last=Elley |work=Variety |date=7 February 2006}}</ref> ''Parineeta'' fetched her a [[Filmfare Best Female Debut Award|Best Female Debut]] award and a nomination for [[Filmfare Best Actress Award|Best Actress]] at the annual [[Filmfare Awards]] ceremony.<ref name=\"oldawards\">{{cite web|url=http://oldbh.bollywoodhungama.com/celebrities/awards/13469/index.html|title=Vidya Balan: Awards & nominations|accessdate=23 July 2010|publisher=Bollywood Hungama|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100409130237/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/celebrities/awards/13469/index.html|archivedate=9 April 2010 }}</ref> The following year, Vidya appeared opposite [[Sanjay Dutt]] in [[Rajkumar Hirani]]'s comedy film ''[[Lage Raho Munna Bhai]]''. She portrayed the role of Jhanvi, a [[Radio personality|radio jockey]] and the love interest of the protagonist [[Munna Bhai]]. To prepare for her role, she met with a couple of radio jockeys and watched them at work.<ref name=hindusiddiqui>{{Cite news |first=Rana |last=Siddiqui |title=The grace of Munnabhai |url=http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/fr/2006/09/01/stories/2006090102090100.htm |work=The Hindu |date=1 September 2006 |accessdate=20 April 2007 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071001001546/http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/fr/2006/09/01/stories/2006090102090100.htm |archivedate=1 October 2007 |df= }}</ref> Her performance was critically well received,<ref>{{cite web|last=Masand |first=Rajeev |url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/masands-verdict-lage-raho-munnabhai/20366-8.html |title=Masand's verdict: Lage Raho Munnabhai |publisher=CNN-IBN |accessdate=7 July 2011 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120331030411/http://ibnlive.in.com/news/masands-verdict-lage-raho-munnabhai/20366-8.html |archivedate=31 March 2012 |df= }}</ref> and the film emerged as a major financial success with earnings of {{INRConvert|1.19|b}}.<ref name=\"all-time\">{{cite web|url=http://boxofficeindia.com/arounddetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=3997&nCat=|title=Top All Time Worldwide Grossers Updated|publisher=BoxOfficeIndia|accessdate=13 October 2013|date=11 May 2012|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131105215110/http://www.boxofficeindia.com/arounddetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=4409&nCat=|archivedate=5 November 2013 }}</ref>\n\nIn 2007 Vidya featured in a supporting role in [[Mani Ratnam]]'s semi-biographical drama ''[[Guru (2007 film)|Guru]]'' as a woman suffering from [[multiple sclerosis]]. The film, which starred [[Mithun Chakraborty]], [[Abhishek Bachchan]], [[Aishwarya Rai Bachchan]], and [[R. Madhavan]] in leading roles, performed well at the box office.<ref name=\"lifetime\">{{cite web|title=Top Lifetime Grossers Worldwide |url=http://boxofficeindia.com/showProd.php?itemCat=312&catName=TGlmZXRpbWU= |publisher=BoxOfficeIndia |accessdate=9 January 2008 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131015223626/http://boxofficeindia.com/showProd.php?itemCat=312&catName=TGlmZXRpbWU%3D |archivedate=15 October 2013 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref> However, film critics [[Khalid Mohamed]] and [[Raja Sen]] noted that her \"talent was wasted\" in a \"minuscule role\".<ref>\n{{cite news|last=Mohamed|first=Khalid|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/india/review-guru-good-value-for-mani/story-Ud7i9oRKpeSnjsqEDkeVOI.html|title=Guru: Good value for Mani|work=Hindustan Times|date=12 January 2007|accessdate=6 July 2011|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171203172546/http://www.hindustantimes.com/india/review-guru-good-value-for-mani/story-Ud7i9oRKpeSnjsqEDkeVOI.html|archive-date=3 December 2017|url-status=live}}\n</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Sen |first=Raja |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/2007/jan/12guru.htm |title=Watch Guru for the actors |publisher=Rediff |date=12 January 2007 |accessdate=6 July 2011 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110123022904/http://www.rediff.com/movies/2007/jan/12guru.htm |archivedate=23 January 2011 |df= }}</ref> Her next release was [[Nikhil Advani]]'s ''[[Salaam-e-Ishq: A Tribute To Love]]'', a romantic comedy featuring an [[ensemble cast]], in which she was paired opposite [[John Abraham (actor)|John Abraham]]. The film, which narrated six love stories, saw Vidya play the role of a television reporter, Tehzeeb Hussain, suffering from a [[Amnesia|memory loss condition]]. The film, which was a critical and commercial failure,<ref name=\"lifetime\"/> generated positive reviews for Vidya. Sukanya Verma of [[Rediff.com]] wrote, \"Vidya's transformation from a self-assured working woman to a helpless, vulnerable person is superb.\"<ref>{{cite web|last=Verma |first=Sukanya |publisher=Rediff |title=Salaam-e-Ishq: Stars shine in mediocre film |url=http://in.rediff.com/movies/2007/jan/26salaam.htm |date=26 January 2007 |accessdate=2 May 2007 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070501151402/http://in.rediff.com/movies/2007/jan/26salaam.htm |archivedate= 1 May 2007 |df= }}</ref>\n\n[[File:Vidya Balan Bhool Bhulaiyaa.jpg|right|upright=1.0|thumb|alt=Vidya Balan is looking directly at the camera.|Vidya at a promotional event for ''[[Bhool Bhulaiyaa]]'' in 2007]]\n\nVidya then took a supporting role in [[Vidhu Vinod Chopra]]'s drama ''[[Eklavya: The Royal Guard]]'', alongside [[Amitabh Bachchan]], [[Boman Irani]], [[Sharmila Tagore]], Saif Ali Khan, and Sanjay Dutt. The film, which failed commercially, met with positive critical reviews and was selected as [[List of Indian submissions for the Academy Award for Best Foreign Language Film|India's official entry to the Oscars]] for the [[80th Academy Awards]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Eklavya sent to Oscars |last=Dasgupta |first=Priyanka |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2007-09-26/news-interviews/27996379_1_eklavya-official-entry-oscar-entry |accessdate=13 October 2012 |date=26 September 2007 |work=The Times of India |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130930075552/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2007-09-26/news-interviews/27996379_1_eklavya-official-entry-oscar-entry |archivedate=30 September 2013 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref> She was later cast as Isha Sahni, a single mother, in [[Sajid Khan (director)|Sajid Khan]]'s ''[[Heyy Babyy]]'', alongside co-stars [[Akshay Kumar]], [[Ritesh Deshmukh]], and [[Fardeen Khan]]. The comedy was a box-office success<ref name=\"lifetime\"/> but garnered negative reviews from critics, as did Vidya's performance; [[CNN-IBN]]'s [[Rajeev Masand]] criticised her wardrobe and make-up, and considered her the \"sore thumb\" of the film.<ref>{{cite web|last=Masand |first=Rajeev |url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/review-heyy-babyy--is-gross-comedy-overthetop-drama/47410-8.html |title=Masand's verdict: Heyy Babyy |publisher=CNN-IBN |accessdate=9 January 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120409052934/http://ibnlive.in.com/news/review-heyy-babyy--is-gross-comedy-overthetop-drama/47410-8.html |archivedate= 9 April 2012 |df= }}</ref><ref name=\"Publishing2008\">{{cite book|author=Outlook Publishing |title=Outlook |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=PjEEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA69 |accessdate=10 June 2012 |date=3 March 2008 |publisher=Outlook Publishing |page=68 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140107140526/http://books.google.com/books?id=PjEEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA69 |archivedate= 7 January 2014 |df= }}</ref>\n\nVidya's fifth and final film of 2007 was [[Priyadarshan]]'s ''[[Bhool Bhulaiyaa]]'', a remake of the Malayalam film ''[[Manichitrathazhu]]'' (1993). Vidya featured as Avani Chaturvedi (a character played by [[Shobana]] in the Malayalam original), a woman suffering from [[dissociative identity disorder]].<ref>{{cite web|accessdate=15 October 2012 |date=11 October 2007 |url=http://specials.rediff.com/movies/2007/oct/11sl3.htm |title=Who's who in Bhool Bhulaiyaa |publisher=Rediff |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131023055250/http://specials.rediff.com/movies/2007/oct/11sl3.htm |archivedate=23 October 2013 |df= }}</ref> Co-starring [[Shiney Ahuja]], Akshay Kumar, and [[Ameesha Patel]], ''Bhool Bhulaiyaa'' was a commercial success with a worldwide revenue of over {{INRConvert|830|m}}.<ref name=\"lifetime\"/> Reviewers, while being generally negative of the film, were appreciative of Vidya's performance. Writing for ''[[Hindustan Times]]'', Khalid Mohamed described her as \"bankably likeable\" and [[Bollywood Hungama]]'s [[Taran Adarsh]] labelled her as \"splendid\".<ref>\n{{cite news|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/movie-reviews/review-bhool-bhulaiya/story-265AQRIkqzKc6H9Fqc0baN.html|title=Review: Bhool Bhulaiya|first=Khalid|last=Mohamed|date=12 October 2007|accessdate=15 October 2012|work=Hindustan Times|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171203172546/http://www.hindustantimes.com/movie-reviews/review-bhool-bhulaiya/story-265AQRIkqzKc6H9Fqc0baN.html|archive-date=3 December 2017|url-status=live}}\n</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/moviemicro/criticreview/id/54360 |title=Bhool Bhulaiyaa review |publisher=Bollywood Hungama |author=Adarsh, Taran |accessdate=9 January 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121125060922/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/moviemicro/criticreview/id/54360 |archivedate=25 November 2012 |df= }}</ref> The role earned Vidya a second Filmfare nomination in the Best Actress category.<ref name=\"oldawards\"/>\n\nIn 2008's ''[[Halla Bol]]'', Vidya played a supporting role alongside [[Ajay Devgn]] and [[Pankaj Kapur]]. The story was based on the life of activist [[Safdar Hashmi]], who was killed by political rivals while performing in a street play (''Halla Bol'') in 1989.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/halla-bol-based-on-safdar-hashmi-rajkumar-santoshi/story-ER1YDLo2kud4osws2bH95L.html |title=Halla Bol based on Safdar Hashmi: Rajkumar Santoshi |work=Hindustan Times |date=12 July 2007 |accessdate=20 November 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160127022913/http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/halla-bol-based-on-safdar-hashmi-rajkumar-santoshi/story-ER1YDLo2kud4osws2bH95L.html |archivedate=27 January 2016 |df= }}</ref> The film was a critical failure.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/movie-reviews/review-halla-bol/story-CK0FF3CqKkN56HGVuYY6JP.html |title=Review: Halla Bol |work=Hindustan Times |author=Mohamed, Khalid |date=11 January 2008 |accessdate=9 January 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160127030751/http://www.hindustantimes.com/movie-reviews/review-halla-bol/story-CK0FF3CqKkN56HGVuYY6JP.html |archivedate=27 January 2016 |df= }}</ref> Later that year, she co-starred with [[Shahid Kapoor]] in [[Aziz Mirza]]'s romantic comedy ''[[Kismat Konnection]]''. Faring poorly at the box office,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.boxofficeindia.com/showProd.php?itemCat=215&catName=MjAwOA== |title=Box office 2008 |publisher=BoxOfficeIndia |accessdate=9 January 2012 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131014132123/http://boxofficeindia.com/showProd.php?itemCat=215&catName=MjAwOA%3D%3D |archivedate=14 October 2013 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref> the film and her performance generated a negative response; critic Sonia Chopra commented, \"[Balan] is made to look downright drab. The haircut is unflattering, the make-up too plain, the clothes usually in off-white or brown. Plus the character is repetitive and reminds us of the one she played in ''Lage Raho Munna Bhai''.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/review-2-kismat-konnection-review-bollywood-14719095.html |title=Review 2: Kismat Konnection |last=Chopra |first=Sonia |publisher=Sify |accessdate=9 January 2012 |date=18 July 2008 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131222174813/http://www.sify.com/movies/review-2-kismat-konnection-review-bollywood-14719095.html |archivedate=22 December 2013 |df= }}</ref>\n\n===Success (2009\u20132012)===\n[[File:VidyaBalan05.jpg|thumb|upright|left|Vidya at a promotional event for ''[[Paa (film)|Paa]]'' in 2009. She won her first [[Filmfare Award for Best Actress]] for the film.]]\nIn 2009 Vidya played the role of an unwed [[gynaecologist]] struggling with her 12-year-old son's [[progeria syndrome]], in the [[R. Balki]]-directed [[dramedy]] ''[[Paa (film)|Paa]]''. Amitabh Bachchan played the role of Vidya's son and Abhishek Bachchan played the title character. A critical and commercial success, the film has been described as a major turning point in her career.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://boxofficeindia.com/showProd.php?itemCat=288&catName=MjAwOQ== |title=Box office 2009 |publisher=BoxOfficeIndia |accessdate=9 January 2012 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131014131907/http://boxofficeindia.com/showProd.php?itemCat=288&catName=MjAwOQ%3D%3D |archivedate=14 October 2013 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Vidya Balan: Raring to go! |work=The Times of India |author=Kazmi, Nikhat |date=3 December 2009 |accessdate=25 August 2010 |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2010-01-01/news-interviews/28146207_1_vidya-balan-paa-happy-new-year |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130908172803/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2010-01-01/news-interviews/28146207_1_vidya-balan-paa-happy-new-year |archivedate=8 September 2013 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref> Sukanya Verma compared her acting style to that of [[Dimple Kapadia]] and noted, \"Balan is poignant yet restrained and projects an impressive figure of grace and integrity\";<ref>{{cite web|title=Watch Paa for Auro |publisher=Rediff |author=Verma, Sukanya |date=4 December 2009 |accessdate=25 August 2010 |url=http://movies.rediff.com/report/2009/dec/04/review-watch-paa-for-auro.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100410161623/http://movies.rediff.com/report/2009/dec/04/review-watch-paa-for-auro.htm |archivedate=10 April 2010 |df= }}</ref> [[Nikhat Kazmi]] from ''[[The Times of India]]'' further argued that Vidya was successful in lending a \"rare dignity to the image of the Bollywood mom.\"<ref>{{cite news |title=Review: Paa |author=Kazmi, Nikhat |date=3 December 2009 |accessdate=25 August 2010 |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/movie-reviews/hindi/Paa/movie-review/5297226.cms |work=The Times of India |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131221134747/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/movie-reviews/hindi/Paa/movie-review/5297226.cms |archivedate=21 December 2013 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref> Her portrayal garnered her several awards, including a Filmfare Award for Best Actress and a [[Screen Award for Best Actress]].<ref name=\"oldawards\"/>\n\nVidya followed the success of ''Paa'' with the [[Vishal Bhardwaj]]-produced ''[[Ishqiya]]'' (2010), a [[black comedy]] directed by debutant [[Abhishek Chaubey]]; co-starring [[Naseeruddin Shah]], [[Arshad Warsi]], and [[Salman Shahid]]. Vidya's role was that of the sexually manipulative Krishna Verma. Vidya described her character as \"an epitome of grey\" and a departure from the conventional portrayal of women in cinema.<ref>{{cite news|title=Vidya Balan in never seen before role in 'Ishqiya' |date=26 January 2010 |accessdate=16 October 2012 |url=http://www.thehindu.com/arts/movies/article94956.ece |work=The Hindu |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131214155906/http://www.thehindu.com/arts/movies/article94956.ece |archivedate=14 December 2013 |df= }}</ref> In preparation for her part, she undertook professional training to speak in the local [[Uttar Pradesh]]-dialect.<ref>{{cite news|title=Vidya Balan takes acting lessons from Naseer|date=29 September 2008|accessdate=16 October 2012|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report_vidya-balan-takes-acting-lessons-from-naseer_1194161|work=Daily News and Analysis}}</ref> The feature as well as her performance received critical acclaim. [[Anupama Chopra]] of [[NDTV]] stated, \"Vidya Balan's smoldering looks scorch the screen even as her eyes hint at tragedy. She proves that she is miles ahead of the cookie cutter Barbie dolls that clutter Bollywood and that sensuality has very little to do with showing skin.\"<ref>{{cite web|title=Review : Ishqiya |url=http://movies.ndtv.com/movie-reviews/ishqiya-473 |author=Chopra, Anupama |date=29 January 2010 |publisher=NDTV |accessdate=9 January 2011 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140110090129/http://movies.ndtv.com/movie-reviews/ishqiya-473 |archivedate=10 January 2014 |df= }}</ref> Her work in the film earned Vidya a [[Filmfare Critics Award for Best Actress]], a second consecutive Best Actress award at Screen and a nomination for Best Actress at Filmfare.<ref name=\"awards\"/>\n\n[[Raj Kumar Gupta]]'s semi-biographical thriller ''[[No One Killed Jessica]]'' with [[Rani Mukerji]] was Vidya's first release of 2011. The film, based on the [[Jessica Lal]] murder case, saw her portray the real-life character of Sabrina Lal, Jessica's reticent sister. While preparing for the role, Vidya did not meet Lal on the insistence of Gupta as \"the Sabrina [...] today is different from the Sabrina a decade ago, [when] the story begins\".<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/arts/cinema/article960860.ece |title=Take Two |last=Devi Dundoo |first=Sangeetha |date=25 December 2010 |accessdate=11 January 2012 |work=The Hindu |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20120914062120/http://www.thehindu.com/arts/cinema/article960860.ece |archivedate=14 September 2012  }}</ref> ''No One Killed Jessica'' met with contrasting reviews from critics, but Vidya's performance was particularly praised. ''[[The Hindu]]'' remarked on Vidya's ability to be \"in sublime control over her emotions\"<ref>{{cite news |title=The sledgehammer wants to be subtle |url=http://www.thehindu.com/arts/cinema/article1073041.ece |last=Kamath |first=Sudhish |date=29 January 2012 |work=The Hindu |accessdate=8 January 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110111045134/http://www.thehindu.com/arts/cinema/article1073041.ece |archivedate=11 January 2011  }}</ref> and Savera Someshwar of Rediff.com added that \"her hesitant body language, her faith, her helplessness, her rage, her sorrow and her gratitude all come across beautifully\".<ref>{{cite web|title=Review: No One Killed Jessica could have been better |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/no-one-killed-jessica-review/20110106.htm |last=Someshwar |first=Savera |date=6 January 2012 |publisher=Rediff |accessdate=8 October 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121104044329/http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/no-one-killed-jessica-review/20110106.htm |archivedate= 4 November 2012 |df= }}</ref> The film had earnings of {{INRConvert|490|m}} and was noted for being a commercial success despite the absence of a male lead.<ref name=\"boxoffice2011\">{{cite web|url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/bollywood-rediscovered-mega-hits-in-2011/212464-8-66.html |title=Bollywood rediscovered mega hits in 2011 |publisher=CNN-IBN |accessdate=17 December 2011 |date=16 December 2011 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130726093958/http://ibnlive.in.com/news/bollywood-rediscovered-mega-hits-in-2011/212464-8-66.html |archivedate=26 July 2013 |df= }}</ref> Vidya earned another Filmfare nomination in the Best Actress category for the film.<ref>{{cite web|title=Nominations for 57th Idea Filmfare Awards 2011 |url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/celebrities/features/type/view/id/2974/2974 |publisher=Bollywood Hungama |accessdate=11 January 2011 |date=11 January 2011 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20120720224321/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/celebrities/features/type/view/id/2974/2974 |archivedate=20 July 2012 |df= }}</ref> In March 2011, a retrospective of Vidya's films was held in Australia, as part of the [[Bollywood and Beyond]] festival.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Bollywood Hungama |title=Indian film festival in Australia to screen retrospective of Vidya Balan's films |url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/1295329/Indian-Film-Festival-in-Australia-to-screen-retrospective-of-Vidya-Balans-films |date=15 March 2011 |accessdate=13 March 2011 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131023060505/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/1295329/Indian-Film-Festival-in-Australia-to-screen-retrospective-of-Vidya-Balans-films |archivedate=23 October 2013 |df= }}</ref> That same year, Vidya featured in a [[guest appearance]] in [[Santosh Sivan]]'s Malayalam language [[fantasy film]] ''[[Urumi (film)|Urumi]]''.<ref>{{cite news |title=Vidya to dub in Malayalam for Urumi |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-02-27/news-interviews/28637924_1_malayalam-film-vidya-balan-urumi |date=27 February 2012 |work=The Times of India |accessdate=20 November 2012 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131023060529/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-02-27/news-interviews/28637924_1_malayalam-film-vidya-balan-urumi |archivedate=23 October 2013 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref>\n\n[[File:Tusshar Kapoor, Vidya Balan, Emraan Hashmi at The Dirty Picture audio release (10).jpg|thumb|upright=1.0|alt=Tusshar Kapoor, Vidya Balan and Emraan Hashmi pose for the camera together.|Vidya with co-stars [[Tusshar Kapoor]] (left) and [[Emraan Hashmi]] at the audio release of ''[[The Dirty Picture (2011 film)|The Dirty Picture]]'' in 2011. Her performance earned her a [[National Film Award for Best Actress]].]]\n\nVidya's next appearance was in Ekta Kapoor's production ''[[The Dirty Picture (2011 film)|The Dirty Picture]]'', a biopic based on the life and death of the controversial Indian actress [[Silk Smitha]].<ref>{{cite news |work=The Hindu |author=Kumar, Anuj |title=What an odd one! |url=http://www.thehindu.com/arts/cinema/article1075100.ece |date=9 January 2011 |accessdate=9 January 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110112071923/http://www.thehindu.com/arts/cinema/article1075100.ece |archivedate=12 January 2011  }}</ref> Vidya was cast as Silk, who was\u2014in Vidya's words\u2014\"known for her brazenness and in-your-face sexuality.\"<ref>{{cite web|publisher=CNN-IBN |title=Silk is sexy, desirable, but not sleazy: Vidya |url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/silk-is-sexy-desirable-but-not-sleazy-vidya/206962-8-66.html |date=29 November 2011 |accessdate=3 December 2011 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111201213043/http://ibnlive.in.com/news/silk-is-sexy-desirable-but-not-sleazy-vidya/206962-8-66.html |archivedate= 1 December 2011 |df= }}</ref> She described the role as the \"boldest\" she had ever played, one that \"required a lot of mental preparation.\" To look the part, she gained {{convert|12|kg|lb|0}}.<ref>\n{{cite news|work=Hindustan Times|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/i-gained-12-kilograms-for-the-dirty-picture-vidya-balan/story-WivVWCiYJZMY7MN0RZcYDI.html|agency=ANI|date=30 November 2011|accessdate=2 December 2011|title=I gained 12 kilograms for The Dirty Picture: Vidya Balan|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170324212117/http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/i-gained-12-kilograms-for-the-dirty-picture-vidya-balan/story-WivVWCiYJZMY7MN0RZcYDI.html|archive-date=24 March 2017|url-status=live}}\n</ref> The film opened to major critical acclaim, and Vidya received unanimous praise for her portrayal which several reviewers regarded as her best performance to date.<ref name=\"Hero\"/><ref>{{cite news |work=The Times of India |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-01-03/news-interviews/30581535_1_vidya-balan-silk-smitha-sabrina-lal |date=5 January 2012 |accessdate=7 January 2012 |author=Iyer, Meena |title=What's left for Vidya Balan to do in 2012 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130908174032/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-01-03/news-interviews/30581535_1_vidya-balan-silk-smitha-sabrina-lal |archivedate=8 September 2013 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref><ref>\n{{cite news|last=Bhattacharya|first=Roshmila|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/vidya-balan-rules-bo-with-biggest-grossing-woman-centric-films/story-YztihFamFXeM6q5h8MzXKO.html|title=Vidya Balan rules BO with biggest grossing woman-centric films|work=Hindustan Times|accessdate=23 September 2012|date=12 April 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171203172546/http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/vidya-balan-rules-bo-with-biggest-grossing-woman-centric-films/story-YztihFamFXeM6q5h8MzXKO.html|archive-date=3 December 2017|url-status=live}}\n</ref> Khalid Mohamed observed, \"She's extraordinary: gutsy, consistently in character and unafraid of exposing her darker side. Here's the kind of complex performance which you haven't evidenced in years and years.\"<ref>\n{{cite news|work=Hindustan Times|title=Critics go gaga over The Dirty Picture|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/critics-go-gaga-over-the-dirty-picture/story-YblUtdRKbDsZMKc4r3iOPI.html|date=2 December 2011|accessdate=2 December 2011|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170319041916/http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/critics-go-gaga-over-the-dirty-picture/story-YblUtdRKbDsZMKc4r3iOPI.html|archive-date=19 March 2017|url-status=live}}\n</ref> Her director [[Milan Luthria]] described her as the contemporary claimant of the \"sex-symbol\" title and compared her \"voluptuousness\" to the likes of yesteryear actresses [[Sridevi]] and [[Vyjayanthimala]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-12-01/news-interviews/30459254_1_vidya-balan-naseeruddin-shah-milan-luthria |title=Vidya Balan has a unique sex-appeal: Milan Luthria |work=The Times of India |date=1 December 2011 |accessdate=1 December 2011 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130908175135/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-12-01/news-interviews/30459254_1_vidya-balan-naseeruddin-shah-milan-luthria |archivedate=8 September 2013 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref> With earnings of {{INRConvert|1.14|b}} worldwide, ''The Dirty Picture'' ranks among her most successful releases.<ref name=\"all-time\"/> Vidya won a second Filmfare Award, a third consecutive Screen Award, and a [[National Film Award for Best Actress]].<ref name=\"awards\">{{cite web|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/celebritymicro/awards/id/8098 |title=Vidya Balan&nbsp;\u2014 Awards |accessdate=25 August 2010 |publisher=Bollywood Hungama |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120129143424/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/celebritymicro/awards/id/8098 |archivedate=29 January 2012 |df= }}</ref><ref name=\"national\">{{cite web|title=National Awards: Vidya Balan gets best actress for 'The Dirty Picture' |url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/national-awards-vidya-balan-gets-best-actress/236998-8-66.html |publisher=CNN-IBN |accessdate=30 September 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120703041747/http://ibnlive.in.com/news/national-awards-vidya-balan-gets-best-actress/236998-8-66.html |archivedate= 3 July 2012 |df= }}</ref>\n\nFor her next feature film, Vidya starred as Vidya Bagchi, a pregnant woman in search of her missing husband in [[Sujoy Ghosh]]'s ''[[Kahaani]]'' (2012). The thriller, set in the city of [[Kolkata]] during the [[Durga Puja]] festivities, met with wide critical acclaim. To lend authenticity to her part, Vidya met several pregnant women and learnt about their lifestyle.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.indianexpress.com/news/vidya-balan-gets-into-character-of-pregnant-woman-for--kahaani-/905582|title=Vidya Balan gets into character of pregnant woman for 'Kahaani'|work=The Indian Express|accessdate=15 October 2012|date=30 January 2012}}</ref> She generated public and media attention by wearing a fake baby bump during the film's promotional activities.<ref>{{cite news |last=Kelkar Dabholkar |first=Reshma |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-02-21/news-interviews/31078998_1_kahaani-vidya-balan-sujoy-ghosh |title=Vidya Balan's baby bump? |work=The Times of India |accessdate=21 February 2012 |date=18 October 2012 |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20130103130955/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-02-21/news-interviews/31078998_1_kahaani-vidya-balan-sujoy-ghosh |archivedate=3 January 2013 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Vidya Balan rides BEST bus to promote her Kahaani |url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/vidya-balan-rides-best-bus-to-promote-her-kahaani/1/175688.html |date=28 February 2012 |work=India Today |accessdate=18 October 2012 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121030060134/http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/vidya-balan-rides-best-bus-to-promote-her-kahaani/1/175688.html |archivedate=30 October 2012 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref> Vidya received further appreciation for her performance in ''Kahaani''. Subhash K. Jha praised Vidya's portrayal of \"grace under pressure\" as \"measured and skilled\"; Pratim D. Gupta of ''[[The Telegraph (Calcutta)|The Telegraph]]'' added that she \"gets into the physicality of a pregnant woman with unfailing mastery\".<ref>{{cite web|title=Review: Kahaani |url=http://movies.ndtv.com/movie-reviews/review-kahaani-689 |author=Jha, Subhash K. |date=9 March 2012 |publisher=NDTV |accessdate=15 October 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150103061147/http://movies.ndtv.com/movie-reviews/review-kahaani-689 |archivedate= 3 January 2015 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.telegraphindia.com/1120310/jsp/entertainment/story_15231247.jsp#.T3F0dEoQgrU |title=What a ''Kahaani'' |first=Pratim D. |last=Gupta |work=The Telegraph |accessdate=27 March 2012 |date=10 March 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120313013944/http://www.telegraphindia.com/1120310/jsp/entertainment/story_15231247.jsp |archivedate=13 March 2012 |df= }}</ref> Once again, the film proved to be a success, grossing over {{INRConvert|1.04|b}} worldwide.<ref>\n{{cite news|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/vidya-balan-s-kahaani-completes-50-days-grosses-rs-104-cr-worldwide/story-8bAabZus5GJWR8fLwIoXQN.html|title=Vidya Balan's Kahaani completes 50 days, grosses Rs. 104 cr worldwide|work=Hindustan Times|accessdate=27 April 2012|date=27 April 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171112021436/http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/vidya-balan-s-kahaani-completes-50-days-grosses-rs-104-cr-worldwide/story-8bAabZus5GJWR8fLwIoXQN.html|archive-date=12 November 2017|url-status=live}}\n</ref> Vidya won a fourth consecutive Best Actress Award at Screen and a third Best Actress Award at Filmfare.<ref>{{cite news|last=Gupta |first=Shubhra |title=Night belongs to Paan Singh Tomar, Barfi!, Kahaani |url=http://www.indianexpress.com/news/night-belongs-to-paan-singh-tomar-barfi--kahaani/1058501/0 |date=13 January 2013 |work=The Indian Express |accessdate=13 January 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130116205054/http://www.indianexpress.com/news/night-belongs-to-paan-singh-tomar-barfi--kahaani/1058501/0 |archivedate=16 January 2013 |df= }}</ref><ref name=\"ff12\">{{cite web|title=Filmfare Awards: All the action from the awards night |url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/filmfare-awards-live-all-the-action-from-the-awards-night/316815-8-66.html |date=21 January 2013 |publisher=CNN-IBN |accessdate=21 January 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130121023308/http://ibnlive.in.com/news/filmfare-awards-live-all-the-action-from-the-awards-night/316815-8-66.html |archivedate=21 January 2013 |df= }}</ref>\n\n===Commercial struggles and resurgence (2013\u20132017)===\n\n[[File:Vidya Balan in 2013.jpg|thumb|upright|alt=Vidya Balan is smiling away from the camera|Vidya at a promotional event for ''[[Shaadi Ke Side Effects]]'' in 2014]]\n\nAfter completing the duties of a jury member at the [[2013 Cannes Film Festival]], Vidya starred opposite [[Emraan Hashmi]] as a boisterous [[Punjabi people|Punjabi woman]] in ''[[Ghanchakkar (film)|Ghanchakkar]]'', a comic-thriller from director Raj Kumar Gupta.<ref name=\"cannes\">{{cite news|last=Kulkarni |first=Onkar |title=Vidya Balan on ''Ghanchakkar'' and her first Cannes outing |url=http://www.indianexpress.com/news/vidya-balan-on-ghanchakkar-and-her-first-cannes-outing/1134594/0 |date=29 June 2013 |work=The Indian Express |accessdate=1 July 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130704030052/http://www.indianexpress.com/news/vidya-balan-on-ghanchakkar-and-her-first-cannes-outing/1134594/0 |archivedate= 4 July 2013 |df= }}</ref><ref>\n{{cite news|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-01-23/news-interviews/36485185_1_vidya-balan-siddharth-roy-kapur-rajkumar-gupta|title=Marriage won't affect my work: Vidya Balan|date=23 January 2013|work=The Times of India|accessdate=23 January 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131127162002/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-01-23/news-interviews/36485185_1_vidya-balan-siddharth-roy-kapur-rajkumar-gupta|archive-date=27 November 2013|url-status=live}}\n</ref> Critics were unenthusiastic about the film and it earned little at the box office.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.indianexpress.com/news/ghanchakkar-flops-emraan-hashmi-will-be-the-most-affected/1137791/ |title=Ghanchakkar flops, Emraan Hashmi will be the most affected |work=The Indian Express |author=Singh, Harneet |date=5 July 2013 |accessdate=5 July 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130708090603/http://www.indianexpress.com/news/ghanchakkar-flops-emraan-hashmi-will-be-the-most-affected/1137791 |archivedate= 8 July 2013 |df= }}</ref> Vidya then provided the voice of [[Draupadi]] for ''[[Mahabharat (2013 film)|Mahabharat]]'', a [[computer animation|3D animation film]] based on the Indian epic [[Mahabharata|of the same name]].<ref>\n{{cite news|title=Plan your weekend: movies releasing this Friday|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/plan-your-weekend-movies-releasing-this-friday/story-6iSDch5Lh32iSgAJSf8MOO.html|date=26 December 2013|work=Hindustan Times|accessdate=28 December 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171117174702/http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/plan-your-weekend-movies-releasing-this-friday/story-6iSDch5Lh32iSgAJSf8MOO.html|archive-date=17 November 2017|url-status=live}}\n</ref>\n\nThe romantic comedy ''[[Shaadi Ke Side Effects]]'' was Vidya's first film release of 2014. Directed by [[Saket Chaudhary]] and co-starring [[Farhan Akhtar]], the film is about a married couple who face a series of comic events after the birth of their child. Critics found the film to be a \"bit overstretched\", but praised both Akhtar and Vidya's performances.<ref>{{cite news|title=Movie review: Shaadi Ke Side Effects is a bit overstretched |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/reviews/movie-review-vidya-farhan-s-performances-enrich-shaadi-ke-side-effects/article1-1189011.aspx |date=27 February 2014 |work=Hindustan Times |accessdate=1 March 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140228201227/http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/reviews/movie-review-vidya-farhan-s-performances-enrich-shaadi-ke-side-effects/article1-1189011.aspx |archivedate=28 February 2014 |df= }}</ref> Also that year, Vidya featured as the host of ''No More Kamzor'', a television special on women empowerment.<ref>{{cite news|title=Vidya Balan hosts women's day special 'No More Kamzor' |url=http://www.deccanherald.com/content/389708/vidya-balan-hosts-women039s-day.html |date=4 March 2014 |work=Deccan Herald |accessdate=6 March 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140306130936/http://www.deccanherald.com/content/389708/vidya-balan-hosts-women039s-day.html |archivedate= 6 March 2014 |df= }}</ref> She then starred in the comedy-drama ''[[Bobby Jasoos]]'', in which she played the eponymous role of a [[Hyderabadi]] woman aspiring to be a detective. Vidya was drawn to the idea of playing a detective and identified with the character's struggle to prove herself.<ref>{{cite news|title=My character in 'Bobby Jasoos' does not know everything: Vidya Balan |url=http://www.financialexpress.com/news/my-character-in-bobby-jasoos-does-not-know-everything-vidya-balan/1264998 |date=28 June 2014 |work=The Financial Express |accessdate=4 July 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140701010745/http://www.financialexpress.com/news/my-character-in-bobby-jasoos-does-not-know-everything-vidya-balan/1264998 |archivedate= 1 July 2014 |df= }}</ref> It required her to sport twelve elaborate disguises, and she trained with a language coach to adopt a Hyderabadi accent.<ref>{{cite news|last=KBR |first=Upala |title=I really wanted to do a film with a Khan but I can't do it now: Vidya Balan |url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/interview-i-really-wanted-to-do-a-film-with-a-khan-but-i-can-t-do-it-now-vidya-balan-1996203 |date=18 June 2014 |work=Daily News and Analysis |accessdate=4 July 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714222805/http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/interview-i-really-wanted-to-do-a-film-with-a-khan-but-i-can-t-do-it-now-vidya-balan-1996203 |archivedate=14 July 2014 |df= }}</ref> Saumil Gandhi of ''[[Mumbai Mirror]]'' wrote that Vidya's \"effervescence rubs off on the proceedings and gives it an energy that drives the film\".<ref>{{cite news|last=Shetty-Saha |first=Shubha |title=Movie Review: 'Bobby Jasoos' |url=http://www.mid-day.com/articles/movie-review-bobby-jasoos/15424162 |date=4 July 2014 |work=Mid Day |accessdate=7 April 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150414011404/http://www.mid-day.com/articles/movie-review-bobby-jasoos/15424162 |archivedate=14 April 2015 |df= }}</ref> However, both ''Shaadi Ke Side Effects'' and ''Bobby Jasoos'' failed to find a wide audience.<ref>{{cite news |last=Pradhan |first=Bharathi S. |title=Three flops, and a kiss |url=http://www.telegraphindia.com/1140713/jsp/7days/18609788.jsp |date=13 July 2014 |work=The Telegraph |accessdate=12 June 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150614043516/http://www.telegraphindia.com/1140713/jsp/7days/18609788.jsp |archivedate=14 June 2015  }}</ref>\n\nIn 2015, Vidya reteamed with Hashmi in the [[Mohit Suri]]-directed romantic drama ''[[Hamari Adhuri Kahani]]''. Penned by [[Mahesh Bhatt]], the film tells the story of Vasudha, a single mother trapped in an abusive marriage, who has an extra-marital affair.<ref>{{cite web|last=Tuteja |first=Joginder |title=Book review - Mahesh Bhatt's All That Could Have Been (soon to be made as Hamaari Adhuri Kahaani) |url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/features/type/view/id/7953 |date=23 February 2015 |publisher=Bollywood Hungama |accessdate=19 March 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150331053301/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/features/type/view/id/7953 |archivedate=31 March 2015 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Das |first=Anirban |title=Vidya Balan to play Suchitra Sen |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/vidya-balan-to-play-suchitra-sen/article1-1326495.aspx |date=15 March 2015 |work=Hindustan Times |accessdate=19 March 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150317173610/http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/vidya-balan-to-play-suchitra-sen/article1-1326495.aspx |archivedate=17 March 2015 |df= }}</ref> Shubha Shetty-Saha of ''[[Mid Day]]'' commented that Vidya \"has shown us what she's capable of in her earlier movies. But here, saddled with a boring, outdated, weepy character, there was nothing much even she could do\".<ref>{{cite news|last=Shetty-Saha |first=Shubha |title='Hamari Adhuri Kahani' {{ndash}} Movie Review |url=http://www.mid-day.com/articles/hamari-adhuri-kahani---movie-review/16286150 |date=12 June 2015 |work=Mid Day |accessdate=12 June 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150613234058/http://www.mid-day.com/articles/hamari-adhuri-kahani---movie-review/16286150 |archivedate=13 June 2015 |df= }}</ref> Vidya next took on the part of a police officer in ''[[Te3n]]'' (2016), a thriller inspired by the 2013 South Korean film ''[[Montage (2013 film)|Montage]]'', co-starring Amitabh Bachchan and [[Nawazuddin Siddiqui]]. She identified with her character's \"silent aggression\" and drawn to the idea of playing a character who commands respect.<ref name=\"move\">{{cite news|last=Chatterjee|first=Alakananda|title=Constantly on the move|url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/mumbai/entertainment/constantly-on-the-move/article8699167.ece|date=7 June 2016|work=The Hindu|accessdate=9 June 2016}}</ref> NDTV's Saibal Chatterjee criticised the decision to bill Vidya's pivotal role as a special appearance and noted how much her presence benefited the film.<ref>{{cite web|last=Chatterjee|first=Saibal|title=Te3n Movie Review|url=http://movies.ndtv.com/movie-reviews/te3n-movie-review-1273|date=9 June 2016|publisher=NDTV|accessdate=3 December 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171204171118/http://movies.ndtv.com/movie-reviews/te3n-movie-review-1273|archivedate=4 December 2017}}</ref> Rajeev Masand was critical of the film's predictable denouement, but wrote that Vidya \"is reliably solid each time she's on screen, raising her brow, curling her lip to effectively communicate more than words can\".<ref>{{cite web|last=Masand |first=Rajeev |title='Te3n' Review: Compelling Thriller, Slowly Draws You Into Suspense |url=http://www.news18.com/news/movies/te3n-review-compelling-thriller-slowly-draws-you-into-suspense-1254559.html |date=10 June 2016 |publisher=CNN-IBN |accessdate=12 June 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160611132152/http://www.news18.com/news/movies/te3n-review-compelling-thriller-slowly-draws-you-into-suspense-1254559.html |archivedate=11 June 2016 |df= }}</ref> She then portrayed the actress [[Geeta Bali]] in multiple songs for ''[[Ekk Albela]]'', a [[Marathi cinema|Marathi]] language biopic of [[Bhagwan Dada]].<ref name=\"move\"/>\n\n[[File:Vidya Balan at the 63rd Filmfare Awards.jpg|thumb|upright=0.8|left|Vidya at the [[63rd Filmfare Awards]], where she won her fourth Best Actress award for ''[[Tumhari Sulu]]'' (2017)]]\n\nVidya's final release of 2016 was Sujoy Ghosh's ''[[Kahaani 2: Durga Rani Singh]]'', a sequel to ''Kahaani'', although it narrated a different story. The film was highly anticipated, and critics believed that Vidya's recent spate of poorly received films would come to an end.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/kahaani-2-vidya-balan-arjun-rampal-sujoy-ghosh-durga-rani-singh/1/823386.html |title=Between Kahaani and Kahaani 2, what accounts for Vidya Balan's lack of success? |last=Ghosh |first=Devarshi |work=India Today |date=30 November 2016 |accessdate=10 December 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161218064837/http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/kahaani-2-vidya-balan-arjun-rampal-sujoy-ghosh-durga-rani-singh/1/823386.html |archivedate=18 December 2016 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/kahaani-2-will-vidya-balan-recreate-the-kahaani-magic/story-gSPfkvNput5xoQOQdyrDvI.html |title=Kahaani 2: Will Vidya Balan recreate the Kahaani magic? |work=Hindustan Times |date=10 December 2016 |accessdate=10 December 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161209233820/http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/kahaani-2-will-vidya-balan-recreate-the-kahaani-magic/story-gSPfkvNput5xoQOQdyrDvI.html |archivedate= 9 December 2016 |df= }}</ref> ''Kahaani 2'', however, was not as well-received as the first film, although Vidya received a Best Actress nomination at Filmfare for her portrayal of a [[child sexual abuse]] survivor in the film.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/kahaani-2-review-roundup-heres-what-critics-have-say-about-vidya-balan-starrer-706509 |title=Kahaani 2 review roundup: Here's what critics have to say about the Vidya Balan-starrer |last=Goswami |first=Parismita |work=[[International Business Times]] |date=2 December 2016 |accessdate=10 December 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161202114311/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/kahaani-2-review-roundup-heres-what-critics-have-say-about-vidya-balan-starrer-706509 |archivedate= 2 December 2016 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=62nd Jio Filmfare Awards 2017 Nominations |url=http://www.filmfare.com/news/nominations-for-the-62nd-jio-filmfare-awards-17987.html |work=Filmfare |date=9 January 2017 |accessdate=13 January 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170113122217/http://www.filmfare.com/news/nominations-for-the-62nd-jio-filmfare-awards-17987.html |archivedate=13 January 2017 |df= }}</ref> Raja Sen thought that despite being an engaging thriller the film's denouement was predictable, but added that \"with tremendous commitment to the part, [Vidya] gives us a stirring performance free of vanity or obviousness\" and praised her \"knack for winning the audience over; when she gasps, we gasp\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/review-kahaani-2-is-let-down-by-predictability/20161202.htm |title=Review: Kahaani 2 is let down by predictability |last=Sen |first=Raja |publisher=Rediff.com |date=2 December 2016 |accessdate=13 January 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170113172230/http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/review-kahaani-2-is-let-down-by-predictability/20161202.htm |archivedate=13 January 2017 |df= }}</ref>\n\n[[Srijit Mukherji]]'s period drama ''[[Begum Jaan]]'' (2017) saw Vidya play the role of the titular [[procuring (prostitution)|procurer]]. A Hindi language remake of the Bengali film ''[[Rajkahini]]'' (2015), ''Begum Jaan'' tells the story of prostitutes who are affected by the [[partition of India]] in 1947.<ref>{{cite news|last=Ray |first=Dhritiman |title=Mahesh Bhatt\u2019s Rajkahini remake being shot in Jharkhand |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/Mahesh-Bhatts-Rajkahini-remake-being-shot-in-Jharkhand/articleshow/52890427.cms |date=23 June 2016 |work=The Times of India |accessdate=27 June 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160628031709/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/Mahesh-Bhatts-Rajkahini-remake-being-shot-in-Jharkhand/articleshow/52890427.cms |archivedate=28 June 2016 |df= }}</ref> In preparation, Vidya worked with Mukherji to provide a backstory to her character, and she researched the era by reading [[Urvashi Butalia]]\u2019s novel ''[[Urvashi Butalia#The Other Side of Silence|The Other Side of Silence]]''.<ref name=\"begum\">{{cite news|last=Jhunjhunwala |first=Udita |title=Vidya Balan on Begum Jaan: \u2018She\u2019s almost like Gabbar, she fears no one\u2019 |url=http://www.livemint.com/Leisure/Zr7riZyQ7UNmqwq93zf7cM/Vidya-Balan-I-have-not-played-a-character-who-is-so-inyou.html |date=13 April 2017 |work=[[Mint (newspaper)|Mint]] |accessdate=15 April 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170415154349/http://www.livemint.com/Leisure/Zr7riZyQ7UNmqwq93zf7cM/Vidya-Balan-I-have-not-played-a-character-who-is-so-inyou.html |archivedate=15 April 2017 |df= }}</ref> Filming in the barren landscape of rural [[Jharkhand]] proved to be a challenge for Vidya, and she said that the experience taught her that \"if push comes to shove, I can brave scorpions, snakes and whatever else\".<ref name=\"begum\"/> [[Anna M. M. Vetticad]] of ''[[Firstpost]]'' disliked the film and blamed the writing for Vidya's inability to \"dig deep and summon up a relatable human being\".<ref>{{cite web|last=Vetticad |first=Anna MM |title=Begum Jaan movie review: Vidya Balan and feminism deserve better than this soulless film |url=http://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/begum-jaan-movie-review-vidya-balan-and-feminism-deserve-better-than-this-soulless-film-3383716.html |date=14 April 2017 |website=[[Firstpost]] |accessdate=15 April 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170414232602/http://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/begum-jaan-movie-review-vidya-balan-and-feminism-deserve-better-than-this-soulless-film-3383716.html |archivedate=14 April 2017 |df= }}</ref>\n\nLater in 2017, Vidya played Sulu, a spirited housewife who moonlights as a relationship advice talk show host, in the comedy-drama ''[[Tumhari Sulu]]''. She identified with her character's enthusiastic personality and was challenged by the opportunity to play a rare comic part.<ref name=\"sulu\">{{cite web|last=Parikh|first=Urvi|url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/you-want-it-to-sound-sexy-na-vidya-balan-tumhari-sulu/20171106.htm|title='You want it to sound sexy, na?'|publisher=Rediff.com|date=6 November 2017|accessdate=25 January 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180126012536/http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/you-want-it-to-sound-sexy-na-vidya-balan-tumhari-sulu/20171106.htm|archivedate=26 January 2018}}</ref> She drew on her experience of playing a radio jockey in ''Lage Raho Munna Bhai'' and listened to late-night talk shows.<ref name=\"sulu\"/> Writing for ''The Times of India'', Neil Soans commended Vidya for \"infusing Sulu with an abundance of infectious optimism without being aggravating\", and Shubhra Gupta of ''[[The Indian Express]]'' took note of how well she channeled \"her distinctive voice and full-bellied laughter to invest Sulu with real warmth\".<ref>{{cite news |last=Soans |first=Neil |title=Tumhari Sulu Movie Review |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/movie-reviews/tumhari-sulu/movie-review/61668494.cms |date=16 November 2017 |work=The Times of India |accessdate=17 November 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171117093917/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/movie-reviews/tumhari-sulu/movie-review/61668494.cms |archivedate=17 November 2017  }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Gupta |first=Shubhra |title=Tumhari Sulu Movie Review |url=http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/movie-review/tumhari-sulu-movie-review-vidya-balan-manav-kaul-film-4940289/ |date=17 November 2017 |work=The Indian Express |accessdate=17 November 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171117174759/http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/movie-review/tumhari-sulu-movie-review-vidya-balan-manav-kaul-film-4940289/ |archivedate=17 November 2017  }}</ref> With earnings of over {{INRConvert|500|m}} on a {{INRConvert|200|m}} budget, ''Tumhari Sulu'' proved to be Vidya's first commercial success since ''Kahaani''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ndtv.com/entertainment/tumhari-sulu-box-office-collection-day-3-vidya-balans-film-had-a-super-strong-weekend-1777717|title=Tumhari Sulu Box Office Collection Day 3: Vidya Balan's film had a \"super-strong weekend\"|publisher=NDTV|date=20 November 2017|accessdate=20 November 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171121034525/https://www.ndtv.com/entertainment/tumhari-sulu-box-office-collection-day-3-vidya-balans-film-had-a-super-strong-weekend-1777717|archivedate=21 November 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/box-office-special-features/box-office-worldwide-collections-day-wise-break-tumhari-sulu/|title=Box Office: Worldwide collections and day wise break up of Tumhari Sulu|publisher=Bollywood Hungama|accessdate=18 December 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171201043132/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/box-office-special-features/box-office-worldwide-collections-day-wise-break-tumhari-sulu/|archivedate=1 December 2017}}</ref> NDTV listed her performance as the best by a Hindi film actress that year, and she won her fifth Screen Award and fourth Filmfare Award for Best Actress.<ref>{{cite web|last=Sen|first=Raja|url=https://www.ndtv.com/entertainment/zaira-wasim-to-vidya-balan-a-list-of-2017s-best-actresses-1795708|title=Zaira Wasim To Vidya Balan: A List Of 2017's Best Actresses|publisher=NDTV|date=4 January 2018|accessdate=25 January 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180126012450/https://www.ndtv.com/entertainment/zaira-wasim-to-vidya-balan-a-list-of-2017s-best-actresses-1795708|archivedate=26 January 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Star Screen Awards 2017 full Winners List: Irrfan Khan, Rajkummar Rao, Vidya Balan, Neha Dhupia & Dangal win big!|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/star-screen-awards-2017-full-winners-list-irrfan-khan-rajkummar-rao-vidya-balan-neha-dhupia-751790|work=International Business Times|accessdate=3 December 2017|date=3 December 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171205042010/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/star-screen-awards-2017-full-winners-list-irrfan-khan-rajkummar-rao-vidya-balan-neha-dhupia-751790|archivedate=5 December 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"ff18\">{{cite news|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/63rd-jio-filmfare-awards-2018-vidya-balan-wins-the-best-actor-in-a-leading-role-female-award/articleshow/62586291.cms|title=63rd Jio Filmfare Awards 2018: Vidya Balan wins the Best Actor In A Leading Role (Female) award|work=The Times of India|access-date=21 January 2018|date=21 January 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180121061556/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/63rd-jio-filmfare-awards-2018-vidya-balan-wins-the-best-actor-in-a-leading-role-female-award/articleshow/62586291.cms|archivedate=21 January 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Professional expansion (2019\u2013present)===\n[[File:Vidya Balan on the sets of UTV Bindass.jpg|alt=|thumb|Vidya on the sets of UTV Bindass]]\nFollowing a year-long absence, Vidya returned to the screen in 2019 to play Basavatarakam, the first wife of actor, filmmaker and politician [[N. T. Rama Rao]] (played by [[Nandamuri Balakrishna]]) in a two-part Telugu-language biopic directed by [[Krish (director)|Krish]], titled ''[[N.T.R: Kathanayakudu]]'' and ''[[N.T.R: Mahanayakudu]]''.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/release-date-of-ntr-mahanayakudu-confirmed/articleshow/67160842.cms|title=Release date of NTR Mahanayakudu confirmed|date=19 December 2018|work=The Times of India|access-date=4 January 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190109010520/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/release-date-of-ntr-mahanayakudu-confirmed/articleshow/67160842.cms|archive-date=9 January 2019|url-status=live}}\n</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/ntr-biopic-starring-nandamuri-balakrishna-vidya-balan-rana-daggubati-to-release-on-9-january-2019-5316621.html|title=NTR biopic, starring Nandamuri Balakrishna, Vidya Balan, Rana Daggubati, to release on 9 January, 2019|date=4 October 2018|work=Firstpost|access-date=11 October 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181011174427/https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/ntr-biopic-starring-nandamuri-balakrishna-vidya-balan-rana-daggubati-to-release-on-9-january-2019-5316621.html|archive-date=11 October 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> Sangeetha Devi Dundoo of ''The Hindu'' found Vidya to be a \"treat to watch\", adding that \"her quietude and eyes [...] speak a thousand words contrasting NTR\u2019s histrionics\".<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/ntr-kathanayakudu-on-a-reverential-tone/article25949259.ece|title='NTR Kathanayakudu' review: On a reverential tone|date=9 January 2019|work=The Hindu|access-date=20 January 2019}}</ref> Writing for ''Firstpost'', Hemanth Kumar opined that \"there's something soothing about her mere presence that makes you want to respect her instantly\".<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/ntr-kathanayakudu-movie-review-balakrishnas-performance-stands-out-in-this-tribute-to-an-icon-5863661.html|title=NTR Kathanayakudu movie review: Balakrishna\u2019s performance stands out in this tribute to an icon|first=Hemanth|last=Kumar|work=Firstpost|date=9 January 2019|accessdate=19 January 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190120044625/https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/ntr-kathanayakudu-movie-review-balakrishnas-performance-stands-out-in-this-tribute-to-an-icon-5863661.html|archive-date=20 January 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Both films failed to perform well commercially.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ibtimes.co.in/ntr-kathanayakudu-box-office-collection-day-9-biopic-turns-first-big-disaster-2019-790314|title=NTR: Kathanayakudu box office collection day 9 - Biopic turns first big disaster of 2019|work=International Business Times|first=Shekhar|last=H Hooli|accessdate=19 January 2019|date=19 January 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190120043052/https://www.ibtimes.co.in/ntr-kathanayakudu-box-office-collection-day-9-biopic-turns-first-big-disaster-2019-790314|archive-date=20 January 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ibtimes.co.in/ntr-mahanayakudu-box-office-collection-it-biggest-failure-nandamuri-balakrishnas-career-792733|title=NTR: Mahanayakudu box office collection: It is the biggest failure of Nandamuri Balakrishna's career|first=Shekhar H.|last=Hooli|date=27 February 2019|work=International Business Times|accessdate=5 March 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190227123847/https://www.ibtimes.co.in/ntr-mahanayakudu-box-office-collection-it-biggest-failure-nandamuri-balakrishnas-career-792733|archive-date=27 February 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> In the same year, Vidya had her first Tamil film release in ''[[Nerkonda Paarvai]]'', a remake of the courtroom drama ''[[Pink (2016 film)|Pink]]'' (2016), in which she briefly played the wife of [[Ajith Kumar]]'s character.<ref>{{cite news|last=KBR|first=Upala|url=https://www.mid-day.com/articles/boney-kapoor-vidyas-role-is-a-powerful-one-in-pink-remake/403841|title=Boney Kapoor: Vidya's Role Is A Powerful One In Pink Remake|date=4 January 2019|work=Mid Day|access-date=4 January 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190104161213/https://www.mid-day.com/articles/boney-kapoor-vidyas-role-is-a-powerful-one-in-pink-remake/403841|archive-date=4 January 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Although not keen on remakes, she agreed to the project to bring attention to [[sexual consent]] to a different audience.<ref>{{cite news|last=S|first=Srivatsan|url=https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/vidya-balan-on-working-with-thala-ajith-in-nerkonda-paarvai/article28684451.ece|title=I was floored by Ajith\u2019s personality, says Vidya Balan on working in 'Nerkonda Paarvai'|date=23 July 2019|work=The Hindu|access-date=6 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190724113611/https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/vidya-balan-on-working-with-thala-ajith-in-nerkonda-paarvai/article28684451.ece|archive-date=24 July 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Srinivasa Ramanujam of ''The Hindu'' liked the film but thought that the portions involving Vidya \"doesn\u2019t quite sit with the narrative\".<ref>{{cite news|last=Ramanujam|first=Srinivasa|url=https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/reviews/nerkonda-paarvai-review-ajith-aces-this-courtroom-drama-which-reiterates-the-meaning-of-consent/article28833914.ece|title='Nerkonda Paarvai' movie review: Ajith aces this courtroom drama which reiterates the meaning of consent|date=6 August 2019|work=The Hindu|access-date=6 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190807132940/https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/reviews/nerkonda-paarvai-review-ajith-aces-this-courtroom-drama-which-reiterates-the-meaning-of-consent/article28833914.ece|archive-date=7 August 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> It emerged as one of the highest-grossing Tamil films of the year.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/bigil-petta-viswasam-kanchana-3-nerkonda-paarvai-kaithi-power-kollywoods-theatrical-takings-in-2019-to-rs-1000-cr-7736851.html|title=Bigil, Petta, Viswasam, Kanchana 3, Nerkonda Paarvai, Kaithi power Kollywood's theatrical takings in 2019 to Rs 1000 cr|work=Firstpost|date=4 December 2019 |accessdate=27 December 2019}}</ref>\n\nLater in 2019, Vidya starred alongside an ensemble cast, including Akshay Kumar and [[Taapsee Pannu]], in ''[[Mission Mangal]]'', a retelling of the [[Mars Orbiter Mission]] (which marked India's first interplanetary expedition).<ref>{{cite news|title=Akshay Kumar\u2019s Mission Mangal will star Vidya Balan, Taapsee Pannu, Nithya Menen, Sonakshi Sinha|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/akshay-kumar-signs-three-new-projects-to-start-shooting-for-mission-mangal-this-month/story-SJRWDHneqcNvDEBRBgHXMO.html|work=Hindustan Times|accessdate=5 November 2018|date=5 November 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181105061942/https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/akshay-kumar-signs-three-new-projects-to-start-shooting-for-mission-mangal-this-month/story-SJRWDHneqcNvDEBRBgHXMO.html|archive-date=5 November 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> She liked the idea of playing Tara Shinde, a seemingly ordinary homemaker who balances her family life with her work as a scientist.<ref>{{cite news|title=Mission Mangal actor Vidya Balan: Tara Shinde is not a superwoman|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/vidya-balan-mission-mangal-playing-tara-shinde-mars-orbiter-akshay-kumar-5905272/|work=The Indian Express|accessdate=15 August 2019|date=15 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190815060049/https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/vidya-balan-mission-mangal-playing-tara-shinde-mars-orbiter-akshay-kumar-5905272/|archive-date=15 August 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> She was also pleased to work with four other leading ladies, which she believed was rare in Hindi films.<ref>{{cite news|title=Vidya Balan gears up for Mission Mangal|url=https://www.telegraphindia.com/entertainment/vidya-balan-gears-up-for-mission-mangal/cid/1697859|work=The Telegraph|accessdate=15 August 2019|date=14 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190814195653/https://www.telegraphindia.com/entertainment/vidya-balan-gears-up-for-mission-mangal/cid/1697859|archive-date=14 August 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Joe Leydon]] of ''Variety'' found Vidya to be \"drop-dead perfect from wire to wire\" and Nandini Ramnath of [[Scroll.in]] wrote that she \"perfectly conveys Tara\u2019s optimism and dedication, and hers is the only female character who has agency in this space agency saga\".<ref>{{cite news|title=Film Review: \u2018Mission Mangal\u2019|url=https://variety.com/2019/film/reviews/mission-mangal-review-1203304480/|work=Variety|accessdate=16 August 2019|date=15 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190816082957/https://variety.com/2019/film/reviews/mission-mangal-review-1203304480/|archive-date=16 August 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=\u2018Mission Mangal\u2019 movie review: A space opera with a little bit of science|url=https://scroll.in/reel/933953/mission-mangal-movie-review-a-space-opera-with-a-little-bit-of-science|website=[[Scroll.in]]|accessdate=15 August 2019|date=15 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190815043836/https://scroll.in/reel/933953/mission-mangal-movie-review-a-space-opera-with-a-little-bit-of-science|archive-date=15 August 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> She received another Best Actress nomination at Filmfare.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.filmfare.com/awards/filmfare-awards-2020/nominations|title=Nominations for Filmfare Awards 2020|work=Filmfare|accessdate=3 February 2020}}</ref> With global earnings of {{INRConvert|2.9|b}}, ''Mission Mangal'' emerged as her highest-grossing release.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bollywoodhungama.com/box-office-collections/worldwide/all-time/page/2/|title=Bollywood Top Grossers Worldwide|website=Bollywood Hungama|access-date=10 September 2019}}</ref>\n\nVidya will next star in a short film about gender equality, entitled ''Natkhat'', which will also mark her first production venture.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/mail-today/story/reaching-for-the-sky-and-beyond-1581371-2019-08-16|title=Reaching for the sky and beyond|date=16 August 2019|work=India Today|access-date=16 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190816095936/https://www.indiatoday.in/mail-today/story/reaching-for-the-sky-and-beyond-1581371-2019-08-16|archive-date=16 August 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> She will then portray the [[mental calculator]] [[Shakuntala Devi]] in an [[Shakuntala Devi (film)|eponymous biopic]] and star in [[Amit V. Masurkar]]'s ''Sherni''.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/vidya-balan-to-play-math-genius-shakuntala-devi-says-i-am-extremely-excited-to-play-the-human-computer/story-13uBrYF18ONi5bbEjnwv4L.html|title=Vidya Balan is all set to play Shakuntala Devi on-screen|date=8 May 2019|work=Hindustan Times|access-date=8 May 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190508084631/https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/vidya-balan-to-play-math-genius-shakuntala-devi-says-i-am-extremely-excited-to-play-the-human-computer/story-13uBrYF18ONi5bbEjnwv4L.html|archive-date=8 May 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.mid-day.com/articles/after-shakuntala-devi-vidya-balan-is-all-set-to-turn-into-a-sherni/22600186|title=After Shakuntala Devi, Vidya Balan Is All Set To Turn Into A Sherni!|date=13 February 2020|work=Mid Day|access-date=13 February 2020}}</ref> Vidya has also committed to produce and star as [[Indira Gandhi]] in a yet-untitled web series based on [[Sagarika Ghose]]'s biography ''Indira \u2013 India's Most Powerful Prime Minister''.<ref>{{cite news|last=Iyer|first=Sanyukta|title=Vidya Balan: I always wanted to play Indira Gandhi|url=https://mumbaimirror.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/vidya-balan-i-always-wanted-to-play-indira-gandhi/articleshow/62449906.cms|work=Mumbai Mirror|accessdate=11 January 2018|date=11 January 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180111003923/https://mumbaimirror.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/vidya-balan-i-always-wanted-to-play-indira-gandhi/articleshow/62449906.cms|archivedate=11 January 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Revealed: Vidya Balan starrer Indira Gandhi biopic to now be a web-series|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/bollywood/revealed-vidya-balan-starrer-indira-gandhi-biopic-now-web-series/|publisher=Bollywood Hungama|accessdate=13 August 2018|date=11 August 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180813111137/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/bollywood/revealed-vidya-balan-starrer-indira-gandhi-biopic-now-web-series/|archive-date=13 August 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life and off-screen work==\n[[File:Vidya Siddharth cropped.jpg|thumb|left|upright=1.2|alt=Vidya Balan and Siddharth Roy Kapur are smiling at the camera.|Vidya and [[Siddharth Roy Kapur]] at their wedding ceremony in December 2012]]\nThe mass media has often speculated about a romantic relationship between Vidya and her co-actors, but she has strongly denied these reports.<ref>{{cite news |work=India Today |url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/Poor+Vidya+pays+price+of+link-ups+with+stars/1/98590.html |date=24 May 2010 |accessdate=7 October 2012 |title=Poor Vidya pays price of link-ups with stars |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141210095710/http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/Poor+Vidya+pays+price+of+link-ups+with+stars/1/98590.html |archivedate=10 December 2014 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Vidya happy she's not linked to Arshad|url=https://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P3-1591274061.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180903115025/https://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P3-1591274061.html|url-status=dead|archive-date=3 September 2018|work=Hindustan Times {{Subscription required|via=[[HighBeam Research]]}}|accessdate=23 September 2012|date=8 November 2008}}</ref> In 2009, Vidya was involved in a controversy when she mentioned a previous relationship in which \"caustic remarks\" were made at her due to her weight. She said, \"If someone who matters to you takes you down, it can break you. That someone whose approval mattered to me started to constantly find faults with me. At that point of time, it was important to walk away from that relationship.\"<ref>{{cite news |last=Lalwani |first=Vickey |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2009-11-14/news-interviews/28068480_1_weight-loss-paa-and-ishqiya-vidya-balan |title=Vidya opens up on Shahid |work=The Times of India |accessdate=11 May 2012 |date=14 November 2009 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131201075704/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2009-11-14/news-interviews/28068480_1_weight-loss-paa-and-ishqiya-vidya-balan |archivedate=1 December 2013 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref> Though she refused to name the person, [[tabloid (newspaper format)|tabloid]] reports suggested that she was referring to Shahid Kapoor (her co-star in ''Kismat Konnection'').<ref>\n{{cite web |last=Mahadevan |first=Sneha |title=W(eig)ht so funny?! |url=http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P3-2467778891.html |work=Daily News and Analysis {{Subscription required|via=[[HighBeam Research]]}} |accessdate=17 October 2012 |date=25 September 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140610083450/http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P3-2467778891.html |archivedate=10 June 2014  }}\n</ref> Kapoor, however, denied the allegations.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/brunch/shahid-kapoor-uncut/story-gpwx8WtTq85Hx8o8UB0etN.html |title=Shahid Kapoor, uncut |work=Hindustan Times |accessdate=11 May 2012 |date=22 June 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160203124326/http://www.hindustantimes.com/brunch/shahid-kapoor-uncut/story-gpwx8WtTq85Hx8o8UB0etN.html |archivedate= 3 February 2016 |df= }}</ref> During an interview in May 2012, Vidya announced that she was dating [[Siddharth Roy Kapur]], the CEO of [[UTV Motion Pictures]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/i-am-dating-siddharth-roy-kapoor-vidya-balan/256908-8-66.html |title=I am dating Siddharth Roy Kapoor: Vidya Balan |publisher=CNN-IBN |accessdate=11 May 2012 |date=11 May 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120512215215/http://ibnlive.in.com/news/i-am-dating-siddharth-roy-kapoor-vidya-balan/256908-8-66.html |archivedate=12 May 2012 |df= }}</ref> On 14 December 2012, the couple were married in a private ceremony in [[Bandra]], Mumbai.<ref>{{cite web|last=Prashar |first=Chandni |url=http://movies.ndtv.com/bollywood/vidya-balan-is-now-mrs-siddharth-roy-kapur-630432 |title=Vidya Balan is now Mrs. Siddharth Roy Kapur |publisher=NDTV |date=14 December 2012 |accessdate=14 December 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150103061313/http://movies.ndtv.com/bollywood/vidya-balan-is-now-mrs-siddharth-roy-kapur-630432 |archivedate= 3 January 2015 |df= }}</ref>\n\nVidya is trained in [[Carnatic music]] and briefly studied the dance forms of [[Bharatnatyam]] and [[Kathak]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report_the-right-man-hasn-t-come-along-yet-vidya-balan_1089724 |title=The right man hasn't come along yet: Vidya Balan|work=Daily News and Analysis|accessdate=24 September 2012|date=9 April 2007}}</ref> Regarding her religious affiliations, Vidya said, \"I am a person with a lot of faith and I have conversations [with God] all the time but I am not so religious in the conventional, organised sense\".<ref name=\"rules\"/> She practices vegetarianism and was listed as \"India's hottest vegetarian\" in polls conducted by [[PETA]] in 2011 and 2012.<ref>{{cite news |last=Vyavahare |first=Renuka |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-01-18/news-interviews/28366462_1_vegetarian-diet-vidya-balan-top-contender |title=Vidya's India's hottest vegetarian |work=The Times of India |accessdate=24 September 2012 |date=18 January 2011 |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20130104145534/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-01-18/news-interviews/28366462_1_vegetarian-diet-vidya-balan-top-contender |archivedate=4 January 2013 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref><ref>\n\"[http://www.indianexpress.com/news/amitabh-bachchan-vidya-balan-named-petas-hottest-vegetarian-celebrities/1053913 Amitabh Bachchan, Vidya Balan named PETA's hottest vegetarian celebrities] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130107072048/http://www.indianexpress.com/news/amitabh-bachchan-vidya-balan-named-petas-hottest-vegetarian-celebrities/1053913/ |date=7 January 2013 }} ,\" ''The Indian Express'', 3 January 2013.\n</ref> Her weight fluctuations over the years have been the subject of substantial media coverage in India.<ref>{{cite news |last=Baliga |first=Shashi |url=http://www.thehindu.com/arts/magazine/article3006462.ece |title=It was liberating to be Silk |work=The Hindu |accessdate=17 October 2012 |date=17 March 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120720210700/http://www.thehindu.com/arts/magazine/article3006462.ece |archivedate=20 July 2012  }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Vyavahare |first=Renuka |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-05-31/news-interviews/31920503_1_vidya-balan-marathi-films-curves |title=Why should women look like men: Vidya Balan |work=The Times of India |accessdate=17 October 2012 |date=31 May 2012 |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20130103172251/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-05-31/news-interviews/31920503_1_vidya-balan-marathi-films-curves |archivedate=3 January 2013 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://movies.ndtv.com/bollywood/fat-so-vidya-is-living-large-loving-it-625536 |title=Fat, so? Vidya is living large & loving it |publisher=NDTV |accessdate=18 October 2012 |date=5 June 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150103061150/http://movies.ndtv.com/bollywood/fat-so-vidya-is-living-large-loving-it-625536 |archivedate= 3 January 2015 |df= }}</ref>\n\nBesides acting in film, Vidya promotes humanitarian causes and supports charitable institutions. In March 2011, she endorsed [[World Wildlife Fund]]'s [[Earth Hour]] campaign in India.<ref>{{cite news |last=Wadhwa |first=Akash |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-03-17/news-interviews/28699077_1_earth-hour-vidya-balan-wwf |title=Vidya Balan to promote Earth Hour |work=The Times of India |accessdate=24 September 2012 |date=17 March 2011 |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20130103134342/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-03-17/news-interviews/28699077_1_earth-hour-vidya-balan-wwf |archivedate=3 January 2013 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref> She campaigned for the cause of nutrition in India for [[Child In Need Institute]] (CINI), a non-profit organisation based in Kolkata.<ref>{{cite news|last=Chatterjee |first=Chandreyee |url=http://www.telegraphindia.com/1120529/jsp/calcutta/story_15541666.jsp#.UF_9r40gejs |title=Canvas to canvass for nutrition cause |work=The Telegraph |accessdate=24 September 2012 |date=29 May 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131212163401/http://www.telegraphindia.com/1120529/jsp/calcutta/story_15541666.jsp |archivedate=12 December 2013 |df= }}</ref> In September 2012, Vidya visited a village in [[Mirzapur]], Uttar Pradesh, where she participated in a campaign to promote children's education and the empowerment of women.<ref>{{cite news|last=Udasi |first=Harshikaa |url=http://www.thehindu.com/arts/cinema/article3877583.ece |title=Doing her bit for society |work=The Hindu |accessdate=24 September 2012 |date=9 September 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120927003259/http://www.thehindu.com/arts/cinema/article3877583.ece |archivedate=27 September 2012 |df= }}</ref> For her attempts to empower women, Vidya was awarded The [[Prabha Khaitan]] Puraskar 2012 by the Calcutta Chamber of Commerce; she was the youngest recipient of the award.<ref>\n{{cite web |title=Vidya Balan bags another award, but not for a film! |url=http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P3-2675120141.html |work=Daily News and Analysis {{Subscription required|via=[[HighBeam Research]]}} |accessdate=24 September 2012 |date=1 June 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140610075855/http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P3-2675120141.html |archivedate=10 June 2014  }}\n</ref> In August 2013, she served as the grand marshal of the [[Independence Day (India)|India Day parade]] held in New York City.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/news-by-industry/et-cetera/anna-hazare-vidya-balan-lead-biggest-india-day-parade-in-united-states/articleshow/21910154.cms |title=Anna Hazare, Vidya Balan lead biggest India Day parade in United States |work=The Economic Times |accessdate=19 August 2013 |date=19 August 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150331145029/http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/news-by-industry/et-cetera/anna-hazare-vidya-balan-lead-biggest-india-day-parade-in-united-states/articleshow/21910154.cms |archivedate=31 March 2015 |df= }}</ref> In September that year, she launched a technology-based learning platform for underprivileged children in the Thanapur village of Uttar Pradesh.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://zeenews.india.com/entertainment/and-more/vidya-balan-launches-tech-based-learning-system_143258.html |title=Vidya Balan launches tech-based learning system |publisher=Zee News |accessdate=23 September 2013 |date=23 September 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130926174736/http://zeenews.india.com/entertainment/and-more/vidya-balan-launches-tech-based-learning-system_143258.html |archivedate=26 September 2013 |df= }}</ref> On the occasion of [[International Women's Day]] in 2015, Vidya wrote an opinion column in ''Hindustan Times'' on the issues faced by women in India.<ref>{{cite news|last=Balan |first=Vidya |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/vidya-balan-s-column-happy-women-s-day-or-is-it/article1-1324035.aspx |title=HT Exclusive: Happy women\u2019s day, or is it? Vidya Balan writes |work=Hindustan Times |accessdate=8 March 2015 |date=9 March 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150308095506/http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/vidya-balan-s-column-happy-women-s-day-or-is-it/article1-1324035.aspx |archivedate= 8 March 2015 |df= }}</ref> In August 2017, Vidya was made a member of the Indian [[Central Board of Film Certification]], to certify films for theatrical exhibition.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/bollywood/pahlaj-nihalani-gets-sacked-vidya-balan-joins-cbfc-headed-prasoon-joshi/ |title=After Pahlaj Nihalani gets sacked, Vidya Balan joins CBFC headed by Prasoon Joshi |publisher=Bollywood Hungama |accessdate=12 August 2017 |date=12 August 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170812143113/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/bollywood/pahlaj-nihalani-gets-sacked-vidya-balan-joins-cbfc-headed-prasoon-joshi/ |archivedate=12 August 2017  }}</ref> The following year, she became the goodwill ambassador of Arpan, an NGO that creates awareness on sexual abuse.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.mid-day.com/articles/vidya-balans-taking-her-own-sweet-time/19570163 |title=Vidya Balan's Taking Her Own Sweet Time! |work=Mid Day |accessdate=3 July 2018 |date=3 July 2018 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180703094908/https://www.mid-day.com/articles/vidya-balans-taking-her-own-sweet-time/19570163 |archivedate=3 July 2018}}</ref> In 2019, she collaborated with [[BIG FM 92.7]] to host a radio show named \"Dhun Badal Ke Toh Dekho\".<ref>{{cite news |last1=Vashisht |first1=Radhika |last2=Young |first2=Sean Colin |url=https://www.deccanchronicle.com/entertainment/bollywood/020319/celebrities-go-on-air.html |title=Celebrities go on air |work=Deccan Chronicle |accessdate=8 May 2019 |date=2 March 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190508094749/https://www.deccanchronicle.com/entertainment/bollywood/020319/celebrities-go-on-air.html |archive-date=8 May 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n==Media image and artistry==\nFollowing the success of ''Parineeta'' and ''Lage Raho Munna Bhai'', Vidya's film roles were subject to wide critical analysis.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.tribuneindia.com/2011/20110410/spectrum/main9.htm|title=The uniqueness of being Vidya|work=The Tribune|accessdate=17 October 2012|date=10 April 2011|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131121110907/http://www.tribuneindia.com/2011/20110410/spectrum/main9.htm|archivedate=21 November 2013 }}</ref> [[Vir Sanghvi]] noted that the films ''Heyy Babyy'' and ''Kismat Konnection'' were \"strange films [...] in which she tried to pretend to be what she is not&nbsp;\u2014 a Bollywood bimbette.\"<ref name=\"rules\"/> Vidya described that particular phase in her career as a \"struggle to be someone else\".<ref>{{cite news|last=Bhupta|first=Malini|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/its-a-constant-struggle-to-be-someone-else-vidya-67234-2010-02-12|title=It's a constant struggle to be someone else: Vidya|work=India Today|date=12 February 2010|accessdate=23 September 2012|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180218090211/https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/its-a-constant-struggle-to-be-someone-else-vidya-67234-2010-02-12|archivedate=18 February 2018}}</ref> Due to the criticism that her film choices evoked, Vidya decided to choose roles that she \"believed in\" rather than choose by convention.<ref name=\"men\">\n{{cite news |title=Why men love Vidya Balan |url=http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1G1-246310012.html |work=Hindustan Times {{Subscription required|via=[[HighBeam Research]]}} |accessdate=23 September 2012 |date=12 January 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131105233010/http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1G1-246310012.html |archivedate=5 November 2013  }}\n</ref> Members of the media have subsequently labelled her as \"bold\" and \"daring\" in her choices.<ref name=\"list\">{{cite web|last=Sen |first=Raja |title=Bollywood's best actresses of 2011 |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-bollywoods-best-actresses-of-the-year-yearend-2011/20111230.htm |publisher=Rediff |accessdate=23 September 2012 |date=30 December 2011 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120905162613/http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-bollywoods-best-actresses-of-the-year-yearend-2011/20111230.htm |archivedate= 5 September 2012 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Vidya Balan: Hindi cinema's new bold |url=http://www.indianexpress.com/news/vidya-balan-hindi-cinemas-new-bold/890115/0 |work=The Indian Express |accessdate=23 September 2012 |date=21 December 2011 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121204024459/http://www.indianexpress.com/news/vidya-balan-hindi-cinemas-new-bold/890115/0 |archivedate= 4 December 2012 |df= }}</ref>\n[[File:Vidya at GQ (cropped).jpg|thumb|upright=0.9|Vidya at the GQ Men of the Year Awards, 2013]]\nHer starring roles in ''Heyy Babyy'' and ''Kismat Konnection'' also led to considerable attention in the media for her \"questionable wardrobe\". Several publications listed her as the \"worst dressed actress\" and her costume designers attributed her failure to carry off western clothes due to her weight and body structure.<ref>{{cite news |last=Wadhwa |first=Akash |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2008-09-14/news-interviews/27891870_1_vidya-balan-parineeta-kismat-konnection |title=Look, it does matter! |work=The Times of India |accessdate=17 October 2012 |date=14 September 2008 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131023060456/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2008-09-14/news-interviews/27891870_1_vidya-balan-parineeta-kismat-konnection |archivedate=23 October 2013 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|publisher=Rediff |title=The worst dressed actresses of 2007 |date=4 December 2007 |url=http://specials.rediff.com/yearend/2007/dec/04yractress1.htm |accessdate=23 September 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121113155053/http://specials.rediff.com/yearend/2007/dec/04yractress1.htm |archivedate=13 November 2012 |df= }}</ref><ref>\n{{cite news |title=What was she thinking? |url=http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P3-1495143311.html |work=Hindustan Times {{Subscription required|via=[[HighBeam Research]]}} |accessdate=23 September 2012 |date=15 June 2008 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131105232949/http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P3-1495143311.html |archivedate=5 November 2013  }}\n</ref> She was later praised in the media for wearing [[sari]]s at public events; designer [[Niharika Khan]] explained, \"Vidya's beauty lies in her curves. She's comfortable in her voluptuousness, and therefore in a sari.\"<ref>{{cite news |last=Walia |first=Nona |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-04-26/designers/31144727_1_vidya-balan-sari-heyy-babyy |title=Is Vidya Balan trapped in a sari? |work=The Times of India |accessdate=23 September 2012 |date=26 April 2012 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131023061508/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-04-26/designers/31144727_1_vidya-balan-sari-heyy-babyy |archivedate=23 October 2013 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref> Vidya has since been identified as defying \"an anglicised idea of sexuality\" and embody the idea of \"raw Indian sexuality\".<ref name=\"men\"/>\n\nAfter portraying strong protagonists in ''Paa'', ''Ishqiya'', ''No One Killed Jessica'', ''The Dirty Picture'' and ''Kahaani'', Vidya was credited in the media for pioneering a movement that breaks the stereotypical portrayal of heroines in Bollywood.<ref>{{cite news|last=Chatterjee|first=Saibal|title=Power actors: Marking a clear shift in gender dynamics, Bollywood embraces films spearheaded by female protagonists|url=http://www.tribuneindia.com/2014/20140323/spectrum/enter1.htm|date=23 March 2014|accessdate=2 June 2014|work=The Tribune|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131121110907/http://www.tribuneindia.com/2014/20140323/spectrum/enter1.htm|archivedate=21 November 2013 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Dubey |first=Bharati |title=Gals, guts and glory: Women power reaches another high in Bollywood |url=http://www.mid-day.com/articles/gals-guts-and-glory-women-power-reaches-another-high-in-bollywood/15445182 |date=14 July 2014 |accessdate=15 July 2014 |work=Mid Day |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140716145949/http://www.mid-day.com/articles/gals-guts-and-glory-women-power-reaches-another-high-in-bollywood/15445182 |archivedate=16 July 2014 |df= }}</ref> The major commercial success of the latter two earned her the title of a \"female hero\"<ref name=\"Hero\">{{cite web|last1=N |first1=Patcy |last2=Dedhia |first2=Sonil |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-vidya-i-did-not-believe-that-i-could-be-so-sexy/20120228.htm |title=Vidya Balan: I didn't believe I could be so sexy |publisher=Rediff |accessdate=17 October 2012 |date=28 February 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121010150153/http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-vidya-i-did-not-believe-that-i-could-be-so-sexy/20120228.htm |archivedate=10 October 2012 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Naval-Shetye |first=Aakanksha |url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report_im-happy-being-called-a-heroine-vidya-balan_1623410 |title=I'm happy being called a heroine: Vidya Balan |work=Daily News and Analysis |accessdate=17 October 2012 |date=9 December 2011 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120110111053/http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report_im-happy-being-called-a-heroine-vidya-balan_1623410 |archivedate=10 January 2012 |df= }}</ref> and Kalpana Nair of ''[[Firstpost]]'' noted that with these two films Vidya spearheaded a change in the roles that were offered to actresses over 30.<ref>{{cite news|last=Nair |first=Kalpana |url=http://www.firstpost.com/blogs/thirty-and-fabulous-how-priyanka-vidya-and-kareena-redefined-aging-469433.html |title=Thirty and fabulous: How Priyanka, Vidya and Kareena redefined aging |work=[[Firstpost]] |accessdate=26 September 2012 |date=6 January 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120927224952/http://www.firstpost.com/blogs/thirty-and-fabulous-how-priyanka-vidya-and-kareena-redefined-aging-469433.html |archivedate=27 September 2012 |df= }}</ref> Critic [[Mayank Shekhar]] predicted, \"Just a few smart male actors can completely change the face of a commercial, star-driven film industry. Looking at [...] Vidya Balan [...] it appears, that change could well originate from the leading lady instead.\"<ref>\n{{cite news|last=Shekar|first=Mayank|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/movie-reviews/mayank-shekhar-s-review-the-dirty-picture/story-Y5u9LlV44FytJcLwBDQNmI.html|title=Mayank Shekhar's review: The Dirty Picture|work=Hindustan Times|accessdate=23 September 2012|date=2 December 2011|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171031113932/http://www.hindustantimes.com/movie-reviews/mayank-shekhar-s-review-the-dirty-picture/story-Y5u9LlV44FytJcLwBDQNmI.html|archive-date=31 October 2017|url-status=live}}\n</ref>\n\n''[[India Today]]'' featured Vidya in their 2012 listing of the nation's most powerful women and noted that \"she has toppled the all dominating hero, reducing him to a supporting role in a male dominated film industry\".<ref>{{cite news |url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/25-most-influential-women-vidya-balan-kareena-kapoor/1/177016.html |title=25 power women and their inspiring stories |work=India Today |accessdate=23 September 2012 |date=9 March 2012 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121101105921/http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/25-most-influential-women-vidya-balan-kareena-kapoor/1/177016.html |archivedate=1 November 2012 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref> Vidya was featured by ''[[Forbes India]]'' in their annual [[Forbes Celebrity 100|Celebrity 100]] list in 2012 and 2013.<ref>\n{{cite news |title=Vidya Balan |url=http://www.forbesindia.com/celebprofile/vidya-balan/1439/70 |work=[[Forbes]] |accessdate=8 July 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180707182620/http://www.forbesindia.com/celebprofile/vidya-balan/1439/70 |archive-date=7 July 2018 |url-status=live  }}\n</ref> She occupied the top slot in Rediff.com's annual listing of the year's best performances for two consecutive years (2010\u201311).<ref name=\"list\"/><ref>{{cite web|publisher=Rediff.com |title=Bollywood's best actresses, 2010 |date=31 December 2010 |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-bollywoods-best-ctresses-2010/20101231.htm |accessdate=23 September 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121025113233/http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-bollywoods-best-ctresses-2010/20101231.htm |archivedate=25 October 2012 |df= }}</ref> She also featured in the list for the years 2005, 2006, 2009, 2012, and 2016.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Rediff |title=Bollywood's best actresses, 2005 |date=23 December 2005 |url=http://specials.rediff.com/yearend/2005/dec/23yend9.htm |accessdate=23 September 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120922040641/http://specials.rediff.com/yearend/2005/dec/23yend9.htm |archivedate=22 September 2012 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|publisher=Rediff.com |title=Bollywood's top actresses, 2006 |date=25 August 2006 |url=http://specials.rediff.com/movies/2006/aug/25sd4.htm |accessdate=23 September 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131023055747/http://specials.rediff.com/movies/2006/aug/25sd4.htm |archivedate=23 October 2013 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|publisher=Rediff.com |title=Bollywood's best actresses, 2009 |date=31 December 2009 |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-best-actresses-of-2009/20091231.htm |accessdate=23 September 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130508212615/http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-best-actresses-of-2009/20091231.htm |archivedate= 8 May 2013 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|publisher=Rediff.com |title=Bollywood's best actresses, 2012 |date=21 December 2012 |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-yearend-special-bollywood-s-top-ten-actresses-of-2012/20121221.htm#8 |accessdate=29 March 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130127161020/http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-yearend-special-bollywood-s-top-ten-actresses-of-2012/20121221.htm |archivedate=27 January 2013 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Sen |first=Raja |publisher=Rediff.com |title=10 performances 2016 should be proud of! |date=30 December 2016 |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/special/10-performances-2016-should-be-proud-of/20161230.htm |accessdate=8 July 2018 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171112051113/http://www.rediff.com/movies/special/10-performances-2016-should-be-proud-of/20161230.htm |archivedate=12 November 2017  }}</ref> In 2012, the magazine ''[[Verve (Indian magazine)|Verve]]'' featured her as one of India's \"Young Power Women\" and wrote, \"In a reel world peopled by [[size zero]]-toned bodies and pretty-as-a-picture heroines, Vidya comes across as completely real and natural&nbsp;\u2013 a woman who has followed her own instincts and dared to live her destiny by being her own person and not morphing herself to fit into any conventional slot.\"<ref name=\"quote1\">{{cite journal|url=http://www.verveonline.com/109/people/power-women.shtml |title=Young power women |author=Mehta, S., Jahagirdar-Saxena, S., Modak, N. & Sah, M. |journal=[[Verve (Indian magazine)|Verve]] |volume=20 |issue=6 |accessdate=23 September 2012 |date=June 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120619051144/http://www.verveonline.com/109/people/power-women.shtml |archivedate=19 June 2012 |df= }}</ref> Two years later, the magazine listed her as a power icon.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.vervemagazine.in/people/power-icon-vidya-balan|title=Power Icon: Vidya Balan|accessdate=24 June 2014|date=8 July 2018|work=Verve|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140707200526/http://www.vervemagazine.in/people/power-icon-vidya-balan|archivedate=7 July 2014}}</ref> In 2018, ''[[The Economic Times]]'' considered Vidya to be one of the most prominent celebrity brand ambassadors in India.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/magazines/panache/face-of-advertising-vidya-balan-has-signed-nine-new-brands-in-the-past-10-months/articleshow/64821513.cms |title=Face of advertising: Vidya Balan has signed nine new brands in the past 10 months |work=The Economic Times |accessdate=2 July 2018 |date=8 July 2018 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180708095740/https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/magazines/panache/face-of-advertising-vidya-balan-has-signed-nine-new-brands-in-the-past-10-months/articleshow/64821513.cms |archivedate=8 July 2018  }}</ref>\n\nIn 2014, Vidya was awarded the [[Padma Shri]], the fourth highest civilian award in India, for her contributions to the entertainment industry.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/india/report-vidya-balan-paresh-rawal-get-padma-shri-1957062|title=Vidya Balan, Paresh Rawal get Padma Shri|work=Daily News and Analysis|accessdate=26 January 2014|date=25 January 2014|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140127013116/http://www.dnaindia.com/india/report-vidya-balan-paresh-rawal-get-padma-shri-1957062|archivedate=27 January 2014|df=}}</ref> The following year, she received an honorary Doctor of Arts degree from [[Rai Foundation|Rai University]]; the university also named a scholarship program for underprivileged girls after her.<ref>{{cite news|last=Das |first=Anirban |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/vidya-balan-to-be-awarded-honorary-doctorate/article1-1353488.aspx |title=Vidya Balan to be awarded honorary doctorate |work=Hindustan Times |accessdate=2 June 2015 |date=1 June 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150601070642/http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/vidya-balan-to-be-awarded-honorary-doctorate/article1-1353488.aspx |archivedate= 1 June 2015 |df= }}</ref> The chancellor of the university, Harbeen Arora said, \"Among the league of iconic actors, Vidya is a pioneer in every way. Her films epitomise a distinct Indianness and a powerful womanhood\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibnlive.com/news/movies/vidya-balan-gets-honorary-doctorate-for-her-contribution-to-indian-cinema-1000191.html |title=Vidya Balan gets honorary doctorate for her contribution to Indian cinema |publisher=CNN-IBN |accessdate=2 June 2015 |date=25 June 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150709092619/http://www.ibnlive.com/news/movies/vidya-balan-gets-honorary-doctorate-for-her-contribution-to-indian-cinema-1000191.html |archivedate= 9 July 2015 |df= }}</ref>\n\n==Accolades==\n{{Main|List of awards and nominations received by Vidya Balan}}\nAmong Vidya's film awards are a [[National Film Award for Best Actress]] for ''The Dirty Picture'' (2011);<ref name=\"national\"/> and six Filmfare Awards: [[Filmfare Award for Best Female Debut|Best Female Debut]] for ''Parineeta'' (2005);<ref name=\"oldawards\"/> [[Filmfare Award for Best Actress|Best Actress]] for ''Paa'' (2009),<ref name=\"oldawards\"/> ''The Dirty Picture'' (2011),<ref name=\"awards\"/> ''Kahaani'' (2012),<ref name=\"ff12\"/> and ''Tumhari Sulu'' (2017);<ref name=\"ff18\"/> and [[Filmfare Critics Award for Best Actress|Critics Award for Best Actress]] for ''Ishqiya'' (2010).<ref name=\"awards\"/>\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of Indian film actresses]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==Further reading==\n{{refbegin}}\n* {{cite news|url=http://www.thehindubusinessline.com/features/life/article2697851.ece|title=Vidya gets dirty... and how!|author=Baliga, Shashi|date=2 December 2011|work=The Hindu|accessdate=8 January 2012|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120108052604/http://www.thehindubusinessline.com/features/life/article2697851.ece|archivedate=8 January 2012}}\n* {{cite news|url= http://www.telegraphindia.com/1111203/jsp/entertainment/story_14833153.jsp|title=Bombaat!|author=Roy, Priyanka|date=3 December 2011|work=The Telegraph|accessdate=11 January 2012}}\n* {{cite news|url=http://www.livemint.com/Leisure/JbeZ73wYywoE67Zg7X3oLI/Profile--Why-everybody-loves-Vidya.html|title=Why everybody loves Vidya|author=Janardhan, Arun|date=2 March 2012|work=Hindustan Times|accessdate=17 October 2012}}\n* {{cite web|url= http://www.filmfare.com/interviews/the-artist-365.html |title=The&nbsp;Artist|author=Singh, Raghuvendra|date=23 April 2012|work=Filmfare|accessdate=24 September 2012}}\n{{refend}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category}}\n\n* {{IMDb name|id=1799038}}\n\n{{Portal bar|Biography|Bollywood|Film}}\n\n{{Navboxes\n| title = Awards for Vidya Balan\n| list =\n{{NationalFilmAwardBestActress}}\n{{FilmfareAwardBestActress 2001-2020}}\n{{FilmfareCriticsAwardBestActress}}\n{{FilmfareAwardBestFemaleDebut}}\n{{IIFAAwardBestActress}}\n{{IIFAAwardBestFemaleDebut}}\n{{ProducersGuildFilmAwardBestActress}}\n{{ScreenAwardBestActress}}\n{{ScreenAwardBestFemaleDebut}}\n{{StardustAwardBestActress}}\n{{StardustAwardFemaleActor}}\n{{ZeeCineAwardBestActorFemale}}\n{{Zee Cine Award for Best Female Debut}}\n}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Balan, Vidya}}\n[[Category:1979 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:21st-century Indian actresses]]\n[[Category:Actresses in Bengali cinema]]\n[[Category:Actresses in Hindi cinema]]\n[[Category:Female models from Mumbai]]\n[[Category:Indian film actresses]]\n[[Category:Indian television actresses]]\n[[Category:Actresses in Malayalam cinema]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Mumbai]]\n[[Category:Best Actress National Film Award winners]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Palakkad]]\n[[Category:St. Xavier's College, Mumbai alumni]]\n[[Category:University of Mumbai alumni]]\n[[Category:Zee Cine Awards winners]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the Padma Shri in arts]]\n[[Category:Filmfare Awards winners]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Indian film actress}}\n{{pp-blp|expiry=indef|small=yes}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2019}}\n{{featured article}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=May 2013}}\n{{Indian name|Vidya|Balan}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Vidya Balan\n| image              = Vidya Balan promoting Tumhari Sulu.jpg\n| alt                = Vidya Balan poses for the camera\n| caption            = Vidya promoting ''[[Tumhari Sulu]]'' in 2017\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1979|1|1|df=y}}\n| birth_place        = [[Bombay]], Maharashtra, India\n| alma_mater         = [[University of Mumbai]]\n| occupation         = Actress\n| yearsactive        = 1995, 2003\u2013present\n| spouse             = {{married|[[Siddharth Roy Kapur]]|2012}}\n| works              = [[Vidya Balan filmography|Full list]]\n| awards             = [[List of awards and nominations received by Vidya Balan|Full list]]\n| honours = [[Padma Shri]] (2014)\n}}\n\n'''Vidya Balan''' (pronounced {{IPA-hns|\u028b\u026ad\u032aja\u02d0 ba\u02d0l\u0259n|}}; born 1 January 1979) is an Indian actress. Known for pioneering a change in the portrayal of women in [[Bollywood|Hindi cinema]] with her roles in female-led films, she is the recipient of [[List of awards and nominations received by Vidya Balan|several awards]], including a [[National Film Awards|National Film Award]] and six [[Filmfare Awards]]. She was awarded the [[Padma Shri]] by the [[Government of India]] in 2014.\n\nVidya aspired to a career in film from a young age and had her first acting role in the 1995 sitcom ''[[Hum Paanch (TV series)|Hum Paanch]]''. She pursued a master's degree in sociology from the [[University of Mumbai]] and simultaneously made several unsuccessful attempts to start a career in film. She subsequently featured in television commercials and music videos. In 2003 she made her feature film debut by starring in the independent [[Cinema of West Bengal|Bengal]]i drama ''[[Bhalo Theko]]''. Vidya subsequently received praise for her first Hindi film, the drama ''[[Parineeta (2005 film)|Parineeta]]'', and followed it with a leading role in the top-grossing comedy film ''[[Lage Raho Munna Bhai]]'' (2006).\n\nThis breakthrough was followed by roles in the romantic comedies ''[[Heyy Babyy]]'' (2007) and ''[[Kismat Konnection]]'' (2008) which had negative reviews. Vidya went on to establish herself by playing five consecutive roles to critical acclaim in the 2009 drama ''[[Paa (film)|Paa]]'', the 2010 black comedy ''[[Ishqiya]]'', the 2011 semi-biographical thriller ''[[No One Killed Jessica]]'', the 2011 biopic ''[[The Dirty Picture]]'', and the 2012 thriller ''[[Kahaani]]'', winning several awards for each of them. She followed this with a series of films that performed poorly at the box office, although her performance in ''[[Kahaani 2: Durga Rani Singh]]'' (2016) was praised. This changed when she starred as a radio jockey in ''[[Tumhari Sulu]]'' (2017) and a scientist in ''[[Mission Mangal]]'' (2019). The latter ranks as her highest-grossing release.\n\nVidya also promotes humanitarian causes and supports the empowerment of women. She is a member of the Indian [[Central Board of Film Certification]] and hosts a radio show. She initially drew criticism for her fluctuating weight and dress sense, but was later credited in the media for her unconventionality. Vidya is married to the film producer [[Siddharth Roy Kapur]].\n\n==Early life and initial career struggles==\nVidya was born on 1 January 1979 in [[Mumbai|Bombay]] (present-day Mumbai),<ref>{{cite web |url=https://in.style.yahoo.com/real-age-vidya-balan-not-wikipedia-saying-100458995.html |title=This Is Real Age Of Vidya Balan And Not What Wikipedia Is Saying |publisher=Yahoo Lifestyle |accessdate=6 December 2016 |date=6 December 2016 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161206114826/https://in.style.yahoo.com/real-age-vidya-balan-not-wikipedia-saying-100458995.html |archivedate=6 December 2016 |df= }}</ref> to parents of [[Tamil people|Tamilian]] descent.<ref>{{cite web|title=Temple wedding for Vidya Balan and Siddharth Roy Kapur |url=http://movies.ndtv.com/bollywood/temple-wedding-for-vidya-balan-and-siddharth-roy-kapur-630333 |date=11 December 2012 |accessdate=24 May 2015 |publisher=NDTV |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150524154305/http://movies.ndtv.com/bollywood/temple-wedding-for-vidya-balan-and-siddharth-roy-kapur-630333 |archivedate=24 May 2015 |df= }}</ref> Her father, P. R. Balan, is the executive vice-president of Digicable and her mother, Saraswathy Balan, is a homemaker.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.digicable.in/index.php/about-us/management-team |title=Management team, Digicable |publisher=Digicable |accessdate=20 February 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130531084316/http://digicable.in/index.php/about-us/management-team |archivedate=31 May 2013 |df= }}</ref><ref name=\"something\"/><ref>\n{{cite news|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/over-the-years-vidya-balan-goes-from-geek-to-haute/story-CY7LmU3wv2Crat773i7dyL.html|title=Over the years: Vidya Balan from geek to haute!|author=Bansal, Robin|date=22 September 2012|work=Hindustan Times|accessdate=24 September 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171009195047/http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/over-the-years-vidya-balan-goes-from-geek-to-haute/story-CY7LmU3wv2Crat773i7dyL.html|archive-date=9 October 2017|url-status=live}}\n</ref> According to Vidya, they speak a mix of [[Tamil language|Tamil]] and [[Malayalam]] at home.<ref>{{cite news|work=The Hindu |url=http://www.hindu.com/fr/2007/02/16/stories/2007021600410100.htm |date=16 February 2007 |accessdate=9 August 2011 |author=Siddiqui, Rana |title=`It's a dream come true' |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120114155348/http://www.hindu.com/fr/2007/02/16/stories/2007021600410100.htm |archivedate=14 January 2012 |df= }}</ref> Her elder sister, Priya Balan, works in advertising.<ref name=\"something\">\n{{cite news |title=There's something about Vidya |url=http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P3-1168964461.html |work=Hindustan Times {{Subscription required|via=[[HighBeam Research]]}} |accessdate=23 September 2012 |date=25 November 2006 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131011162727/http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P3-1168964461.html |archivedate=11 October 2013  }}\n</ref> The actress [[Priyamani]] is her second cousin.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-filmi-family-tree-know-priyamanis-famous-relative/20131008.htm#1 |title=Filmi Family Tree: Know Priyamani's famous relative? |publisher=Rediff.com |date=8 October 2013 |accessdate=16 April 2014 |pages=2 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140203040650/http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-filmi-family-tree-know-priyamanis-famous-relative/20131008.htm |archivedate= 3 February 2014 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/tabloid/hyderabad/not-going-ask-vidya-balan-advice-priyamani-672 | title=Not going to ask Vidya Balan for advice: Priyamani | work=Deccan Chronicle | date=11 May 2012 | accessdate=16 April 2014 | author=Prakash, B. V. S. | archiveurl=https://wayback.archive-it.org/all/20120512011620/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/tabloid/hyderabad/not-going-ask-vidya-balan-advice-priyamani-672 | archivedate=12 May 2012}}</ref>\n\nVidya grew up in the suburban neighbourhood of [[Chembur]], Mumbai and attended St. Anthony Girls' High School.<ref>{{cite news|title=Celeb diary: Vidya Balan |url=http://www.mid-day.com/entertainment/2010/feb/040210-Celeb-Dairy-Vidya-Balan.htm |accessdate=24 May 2012 |work=Mid Day |date=4 February 2010 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130103041053/http://www.mid-day.com/entertainment/2010/feb/040210-Celeb-Dairy-Vidya-Balan.htm |archivedate= 3 January 2013 |df= }}</ref><ref>\n{{cite news|last=Gupta|first=Priya|title=I have never done a barter with God: Vidya Balan|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-09-17/news-interviews/42114811_1_ganpati-vidya-balan-aarti|accessdate=26 January 2014|work=The Times of India|date=17 September 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140202185556/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-09-17/news-interviews/42114811_1_ganpati-vidya-balan-aarti|archive-date=2 February 2014|url-status=live}}\n</ref> From a young age, she aspired to a career in film and was inspired by the work of actors [[Shabana Azmi]] and [[Madhuri Dixit]].<ref name=\"rules\"/><ref>{{cite web|publisher=CNN-IBN |url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/madhuri-was-my-inspiration-in-life-vidya-balan/218414-8-66.html |date=6 January 2012 |accessdate=13 October 2012 |title=Madhuri is my inspiration in life: Vidya Balan |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120420044855/http://ibnlive.in.com/news/madhuri-was-my-inspiration-in-life-vidya-balan/218414-8-66.html |archivedate=20 April 2012 |df= }}</ref> At the age of 16, she starred in the first season of [[Ekta Kapoor]]'s sitcom ''[[Hum Paanch (TV series)|Hum Paanch]]'' as Radhika, a bespectacled teenager.<ref>{{cite news |last=Ganguly |first=Pritwish |title=I said no to Ekta: Vidya Balan |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2010-10-22/news-interviews/28271540_1_tv-debut-vidya-balan-s-homepage-audition |accessdate=23 September 2012 |work=The Times of India |date=22 October 2010 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131023060327/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2010-10-22/news-interviews/28271540_1_tv-debut-vidya-balan-s-homepage-audition |archivedate=23 October 2013 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref><ref name=\"tree\">{{cite news|url=http://www.telegraphindia.com/1100725/jsp/7days/story_12723277.jsp |title=It could have been George Clooney or a tree. I would have made love to the tree if I had to |first=Draupadi |last=Rohera |work=The Telegraph |accessdate=19 November 2012 |date=25 June 2010 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130313102649/http://www.telegraphindia.com/1100725/jsp/7days/story_12723277.jsp |archivedate=13 March 2013 |df= }}</ref> After the series ended, Vidya refused director [[Anurag Basu]]'s offer to star in a television soap opera, as she wanted to concentrate on a film career.<ref name=\"native\">{{cite news |last=Bamzai |first=Kaveree |title=Return of the native |url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/Return+of+the+native/1/82489.html |accessdate=23 September 2012 |work=India Today |date=4 February 2010 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121023235254/http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/Return+of+the+native/1/82489.html |archivedate=23 October 2012 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref> Her parents were supportive of the decision but encouraged her to complete her education first.<ref name=\"rules\">\n{{cite news|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/why-vidya-balan-rules/story-kBrnl5alAyNYS51Hzl2JNL.html|title=Why Vidya Balan rules|author=Sanghvi, Vir|date=17 December 2011|work=Hindustan Times|accessdate=11 January 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180708081025/https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/why-vidya-balan-rules/story-kBrnl5alAyNYS51Hzl2JNL.html|archive-date=8 July 2018|url-status=live}}\n</ref> She attended [[St. Xavier's College, Mumbai|St. Xavier's College]] to pursue a bachelor's degree in [[sociology]] and later earned a master's degree from the [[University of Mumbai]].<ref>{{cite news |work=The Times of India |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-01-09/news-interviews/28367559_1_sociology-films-khar |date=9 January 2011 |accessdate=23 August 2012 |title=Sociology was my major subject: Vidya |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131023055734/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-01-09/news-interviews/28367559_1_sociology-films-khar |archivedate=23 October 2013 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Just how educated are our Bollywood heroines? |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-just-how-educated-are-bollywood-heroines/20120118.htm |publisher=Rediff |accessdate=20 November 2012 |date=18 January 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20130201061849/http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-just-how-educated-are-bollywood-heroines/20120118.htm |archivedate= 1 February 2013 |df= }}</ref>\n\nWhile pursuing her master's degree, Vidya was cast as the female lead in the [[Malayalam cinema|Malayalam film]] ''Chakram'', opposite [[Mohanlal]] and was subsequently signed on for 12 other Malayalam language films.<ref name=\"rules\"/> However, due to production difficulties, ''Chakram'' was shelved.<ref name=\"beginning\"/> The postponement of a film starring Mohanlal was an unheard occurrence in Malayalam cinema and producers blamed Vidya for bringing \"bad luck\" to the project; labelled her as a \"jinx\"; and replaced her in the films that she had been contracted for.<ref name=\"rules\"/> She shifted focus to [[Tamil cinema]]. In 2001, she was cast as the female lead in [[N. Linguswamy]]'s ''[[Run (2002 film)|Run]]'' (2002). However, after completing the first [[shooting schedule]], she was unceremoniously dropped and replaced by [[Meera Jasmine]].<ref>{{cite web|title=The Vidya magic! |publisher=Sify |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/the-vidya-magic-news-tamil-kkfv22bcabh.html |accessdate=23 November 2006 |date=7 July 2005 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131222210357/http://www.sify.com/movies/the-vidya-magic-news-tamil-kkfv22bcabh.html |archivedate=22 December 2013 |df= }}</ref> She was signed up under false pretences for a [[sex comedy]], a genre she was uncomfortable with, and decided to leave the project.<ref name=\"rules\"/> Thereafter, she signed on for a third Tamil film, ''[[Manasellam]]'' (2003), but was replaced by [[Trisha (actress)|Trisha]] as the director was dissatisfied with her work.<ref>{{cite news |title=When Vidya Balan was kicked out |work=The Times of India |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-03-13/did-you-know-/31160200_1_vidya-balan-hindi-films-south-filmmakers |accessdate=23 March 2012 |date=7 July 2005 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131023114243/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-07-13/did-you-know-/31160200_1_vidya-balan-hindi-films-south-filmmakers |archivedate=23 October 2013 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref> ''[[Kalari Vikraman]]'', another Malayalam film that she completed work for in 2003, failed to get a theatrical release.<ref>{{cite journal|title=Kalari Vikraman from Jail|journal=[[Vellinakshatram (magazine)|Vellinakshatram]]|date=5 January 2003}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=\u0d38\u0d3e\u0d15\u0d4d\u0d37\u0d30\u0d24\u0d2f\u0d41\u0d33\u0d4d\u0d33 \u0d15\u0d47\u0d30\u0d33\u0d24\u0d4d\u0d24\u0d3f\u0d7d \u0d05\u0d28\u0d4d\u0d27\u0d35\u0d3f\u0d36\u0d4d\u0d35\u0d3e\u0d38\u0d3f\u0d15\u0d7e \u0d15\u0d42\u0d1f\u0d41\u0d24\u0d32\u0d46\u0d28\u0d4d\u0d28\u0d4d\u200c \u0d35\u0d3f\u0d26\u0d4d\u0d2f\u0d3e\u0d2c\u0d3e\u0d32\u0d7b |url=http://www.malayalivartha.com/cinema/star-trek/35679 |publisher=[[Mangalam]] |accessdate=30 January 2017 |date=27 April 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170202041234/http://www.malayalivartha.com/cinema/star-trek/35679 |archivedate= 2 February 2017 |df= }}</ref> After failing to start a film career, Vidya appeared in approximately 60 television commercials and in music videos for [[Euphoria (Indian band)|Euphoria]] and [[Shubha Mudgal]]; a majority of these were directed by [[Pradeep Sarkar]].<ref name=\"native\"/><ref>\n{{cite news |title=Stand-out act four not-so-new newcomers have found critical acclaim in breakthrough roles this year. Now all they need is stardom |url=http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P2-10956992.html |work=India Today {{Subscription required|via=[[HighBeam Research]]}} |accessdate=23 September 2012 |date=18 July 2005 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131105232954/http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P2-10956992.html |archivedate=5 November 2013  }}\n</ref>\n\n==Career==\n{{see also|Vidya Balan filmography}}\n\n===Film debut and breakthrough (2003\u20132008)===\n[[File:Vidyabalan.jpg|left|upright=1.0|thumb|alt=Vidya Balan is looking directly at the camera.|Vidya at the launch of a book based on her film ''[[Lage Raho Munna Bhai]]'' (2006). The film ranks among her highest-grossing releases.<ref name=\"all-time\"/>]]\nIn 2003, Vidya was signed on by [[Goutam Halder]] for his independent [[Cinema of West Bengal|Bengali]] drama ''[[Bhalo Theko]]'': her first film release.<ref>{{cite news|title=Love for Bengal: A mystery in Vidya Balan's life|url= http://www.indianexpress.com/news/love-for-bengal-a-mystery-in-vidya-balans-life/819021/|work=The Indian Express|accessdate=24 October 2013|date=18 July 2011}}</ref> Her portrayal of Anandi, a young woman reminiscing about her past, won her an [[Anandalok Awards|Anandalok Purashkar]] for Best Actress.<ref>\n{{cite news|title=I feel I was Bengali in my last life: Vidya Balan|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/i-feel-i-was-bengali-in-my-last-life-vidya-balan/story-usw68eTdzeG4nxfJ6QAdkM.html|work=Hindustan Times|accessdate=23 March 2012|date=1 February 2008|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171203153803/http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/i-feel-i-was-bengali-in-my-last-life-vidya-balan/story-usw68eTdzeG4nxfJ6QAdkM.html|archive-date=3 December 2017|url-status=live}}\n</ref> Vidya made her Hindi film debut in 2005 with Pradeep Sarkar's musical drama ''[[Parineeta (2005 film)|Parineeta]]''. Before being cast, she had to undergo extensive auditions for six months.<ref name=\"beginning\">{{cite web|accessdate=23 October 2007 |first=Ronjita |last=Kulkarni |url=http://specials.rediff.com/movies/2005/jun/08vidya2.htm |title=Meet the new girl in Saif's life |publisher=Rediff |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071109164805/http://specials.rediff.com/movies/2005/jun/08vidya2.htm |archivedate= 9 November 2007 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|accessdate=20 November 2012 |date=1 January 2009 |url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/1158478/Small-people-with-big-egosnot-for-me-Vidhu-Vinod-Chopra |title=Small people with big egos, not for me! |publisher=Bollywood Hungama |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131023060206/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/1158478/Small-people-with-big-egosnot-for-me-Vidhu-Vinod-Chopra |archivedate=23 October 2013 |df= }}</ref> The film, an adaptation of [[Sarat Chandra Chattopadhyay]]'s [[Parineeta (novel)|novel of the same name]], narrated the love story of an idealist Lalita (Vidya) and a musician Shekhar ([[Saif Ali Khan]]), the son of a capitalist businessman.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.telegraphindia.com/1050611/asp/nation/story_4854277.asp |title=Parineeta breathes Bengal among the tulips |first=Pratim D. |last=Gupta |date=10 June 2005 |accessdate=9 August 2011 |work=The Telegraph |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110629155510/http://www.telegraphindia.com/1050611/asp/nation/story_4854277.asp |archivedate=29 June 2011 |df= }}</ref> Her performance in the film was praised by critics;<ref name=\"tree\"/> Derek Elley from ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'' wrote, \"An acting revelation is Tamil newcomer [Vidya] Balan, whose devoted but dignified Lalita is the picture's heart and soul.\"<ref>{{cite news|accessdate=27 October 2007|url=http://www.variety.com/review/VE1117929519.html?categoryId=31&cs=1 |title=Parineeta: Film review |first=Derek |last=Elley |work=Variety |date=7 February 2006}}</ref> ''Parineeta'' fetched her a [[Filmfare Best Female Debut Award|Best Female Debut]] award and a nomination for [[Filmfare Best Actress Award|Best Actress]] at the annual [[Filmfare Awards]] ceremony.<ref name=\"oldawards\">{{cite web|url=http://oldbh.bollywoodhungama.com/celebrities/awards/13469/index.html|title=Vidya Balan: Awards & nominations|accessdate=23 July 2010|publisher=Bollywood Hungama|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100409130237/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/celebrities/awards/13469/index.html|archivedate=9 April 2010 }}</ref> The following year, Vidya appeared opposite [[Sanjay Dutt]] in [[Rajkumar Hirani]]'s comedy film ''[[Lage Raho Munna Bhai]]''. She portrayed the role of Jhanvi, a [[Radio personality|radio jockey]] and the love interest of the protagonist [[Munna Bhai]]. To prepare for her role, she met with a couple of radio jockeys and watched them at work.<ref name=hindusiddiqui>{{Cite news |first=Rana |last=Siddiqui |title=The grace of Munnabhai |url=http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/fr/2006/09/01/stories/2006090102090100.htm |work=The Hindu |date=1 September 2006 |accessdate=20 April 2007 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071001001546/http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/fr/2006/09/01/stories/2006090102090100.htm |archivedate=1 October 2007 |df= }}</ref> Her performance was critically well received,<ref>{{cite web|last=Masand |first=Rajeev |url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/masands-verdict-lage-raho-munnabhai/20366-8.html |title=Masand's verdict: Lage Raho Munnabhai |publisher=CNN-IBN |accessdate=7 July 2011 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120331030411/http://ibnlive.in.com/news/masands-verdict-lage-raho-munnabhai/20366-8.html |archivedate=31 March 2012 |df= }}</ref> and the film emerged as a major financial success with earnings of {{INRConvert|1.19|b}}.<ref name=\"all-time\">{{cite web|url=http://boxofficeindia.com/arounddetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=3997&nCat=|title=Top All Time Worldwide Grossers Updated|publisher=BoxOfficeIndia|accessdate=13 October 2013|date=11 May 2012|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131105215110/http://www.boxofficeindia.com/arounddetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=4409&nCat=|archivedate=5 November 2013 }}</ref>\n\nIn 2007 Vidya featured in a supporting role in [[Mani Ratnam]]'s semi-biographical drama ''[[Guru (2007 film)|Guru]]'' as a woman suffering from [[multiple sclerosis]]. The film, which starred [[Mithun Chakraborty]], [[Abhishek Bachchan]], [[Aishwarya Rai Bachchan]], and [[R. Madhavan]] in leading roles, performed well at the box office.<ref name=\"lifetime\">{{cite web|title=Top Lifetime Grossers Worldwide |url=http://boxofficeindia.com/showProd.php?itemCat=312&catName=TGlmZXRpbWU= |publisher=BoxOfficeIndia |accessdate=9 January 2008 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131015223626/http://boxofficeindia.com/showProd.php?itemCat=312&catName=TGlmZXRpbWU%3D |archivedate=15 October 2013 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref> However, film critics [[Khalid Mohamed]] and [[Raja Sen]] noted that her \"talent was wasted\" in a \"minuscule role\".<ref>\n{{cite news|last=Mohamed|first=Khalid|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/india/review-guru-good-value-for-mani/story-Ud7i9oRKpeSnjsqEDkeVOI.html|title=Guru: Good value for Mani|work=Hindustan Times|date=12 January 2007|accessdate=6 July 2011|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171203172546/http://www.hindustantimes.com/india/review-guru-good-value-for-mani/story-Ud7i9oRKpeSnjsqEDkeVOI.html|archive-date=3 December 2017|url-status=live}}\n</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Sen |first=Raja |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/2007/jan/12guru.htm |title=Watch Guru for the actors |publisher=Rediff |date=12 January 2007 |accessdate=6 July 2011 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110123022904/http://www.rediff.com/movies/2007/jan/12guru.htm |archivedate=23 January 2011 |df= }}</ref> Her next release was [[Nikhil Advani]]'s ''[[Salaam-e-Ishq: A Tribute To Love]]'', a romantic comedy featuring an [[ensemble cast]], in which she was paired opposite [[John Abraham (actor)|John Abraham]]. The film, which narrated six love stories, saw Vidya play the role of a television reporter, Tehzeeb Hussain, suffering from a [[Amnesia|memory loss condition]]. The film, which was a critical and commercial failure,<ref name=\"lifetime\"/> generated positive reviews for Vidya. Sukanya Verma of [[Rediff.com]] wrote, \"Vidya's transformation from a self-assured working woman to a helpless, vulnerable person is superb.\"<ref>{{cite web|last=Verma |first=Sukanya |publisher=Rediff |title=Salaam-e-Ishq: Stars shine in mediocre film |url=http://in.rediff.com/movies/2007/jan/26salaam.htm |date=26 January 2007 |accessdate=2 May 2007 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070501151402/http://in.rediff.com/movies/2007/jan/26salaam.htm |archivedate= 1 May 2007 |df= }}</ref>\n\n[[File:Vidya Balan Bhool Bhulaiyaa.jpg|right|upright=1.0|thumb|alt=Vidya Balan is looking directly at the camera.|Vidya at a promotional event for ''[[Bhool Bhulaiyaa]]'' in 2007]]\n\nVidya then took a supporting role in [[Vidhu Vinod Chopra]]'s drama ''[[Eklavya: The Royal Guard]]'', alongside [[Amitabh Bachchan]], [[Boman Irani]], [[Sharmila Tagore]], Saif Ali Khan, and Sanjay Dutt. The film, which failed commercially, met with positive critical reviews and was selected as [[List of Indian submissions for the Academy Award for Best Foreign Language Film|India's official entry to the Oscars]] for the [[80th Academy Awards]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Eklavya sent to Oscars |last=Dasgupta |first=Priyanka |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2007-09-26/news-interviews/27996379_1_eklavya-official-entry-oscar-entry |accessdate=13 October 2012 |date=26 September 2007 |work=The Times of India |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130930075552/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2007-09-26/news-interviews/27996379_1_eklavya-official-entry-oscar-entry |archivedate=30 September 2013 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref> She was later cast as Isha Sahni, a single mother, in [[Sajid Khan (director)|Sajid Khan]]'s ''[[Heyy Babyy]]'', alongside co-stars [[Akshay Kumar]], [[Ritesh Deshmukh]], and [[Fardeen Khan]]. The comedy was a box-office success<ref name=\"lifetime\"/> but garnered negative reviews from critics, as did Vidya's performance; [[CNN-IBN]]'s [[Rajeev Masand]] criticised her wardrobe and make-up, and considered her the \"sore thumb\" of the film.<ref>{{cite web|last=Masand |first=Rajeev |url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/review-heyy-babyy--is-gross-comedy-overthetop-drama/47410-8.html |title=Masand's verdict: Heyy Babyy |publisher=CNN-IBN |accessdate=9 January 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120409052934/http://ibnlive.in.com/news/review-heyy-babyy--is-gross-comedy-overthetop-drama/47410-8.html |archivedate= 9 April 2012 |df= }}</ref><ref name=\"Publishing2008\">{{cite book|author=Outlook Publishing |title=Outlook |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=PjEEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA69 |accessdate=10 June 2012 |date=3 March 2008 |publisher=Outlook Publishing |page=68 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140107140526/http://books.google.com/books?id=PjEEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA69 |archivedate= 7 January 2014 |df= }}</ref>\n\nVidya's fifth and final film of 2007 was [[Priyadarshan]]'s ''[[Bhool Bhulaiyaa]]'', a remake of the Malayalam film ''[[Manichitrathazhu]]'' (1993). Vidya featured as Avani Chaturvedi (a character played by [[Shobana]] in the Malayalam original), a woman suffering from [[dissociative identity disorder]].<ref>{{cite web|accessdate=15 October 2012 |date=11 October 2007 |url=http://specials.rediff.com/movies/2007/oct/11sl3.htm |title=Who's who in Bhool Bhulaiyaa |publisher=Rediff |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131023055250/http://specials.rediff.com/movies/2007/oct/11sl3.htm |archivedate=23 October 2013 |df= }}</ref> Co-starring [[Shiney Ahuja]], Akshay Kumar, and [[Ameesha Patel]], ''Bhool Bhulaiyaa'' was a commercial success with a worldwide revenue of over {{INRConvert|830|m}}.<ref name=\"lifetime\"/> Reviewers, while being generally negative of the film, were appreciative of Vidya's performance. Writing for ''[[Hindustan Times]]'', Khalid Mohamed described her as \"bankably likeable\" and [[Bollywood Hungama]]'s [[Taran Adarsh]] labelled her as \"splendid\".<ref>\n{{cite news|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/movie-reviews/review-bhool-bhulaiya/story-265AQRIkqzKc6H9Fqc0baN.html|title=Review: Bhool Bhulaiya|first=Khalid|last=Mohamed|date=12 October 2007|accessdate=15 October 2012|work=Hindustan Times|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171203172546/http://www.hindustantimes.com/movie-reviews/review-bhool-bhulaiya/story-265AQRIkqzKc6H9Fqc0baN.html|archive-date=3 December 2017|url-status=live}}\n</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/moviemicro/criticreview/id/54360 |title=Bhool Bhulaiyaa review |publisher=Bollywood Hungama |author=Adarsh, Taran |accessdate=9 January 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121125060922/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/moviemicro/criticreview/id/54360 |archivedate=25 November 2012 |df= }}</ref> The role earned Vidya a second Filmfare nomination in the Best Actress category.<ref name=\"oldawards\"/>\n\nIn 2008's ''[[Halla Bol]]'', Vidya played a supporting role alongside [[Ajay Devgn]] and [[Pankaj Kapur]]. The story was based on the life of activist [[Safdar Hashmi]], who was killed by political rivals while performing in a street play (''Halla Bol'') in 1989.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/halla-bol-based-on-safdar-hashmi-rajkumar-santoshi/story-ER1YDLo2kud4osws2bH95L.html |title=Halla Bol based on Safdar Hashmi: Rajkumar Santoshi |work=Hindustan Times |date=12 July 2007 |accessdate=20 November 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160127022913/http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/halla-bol-based-on-safdar-hashmi-rajkumar-santoshi/story-ER1YDLo2kud4osws2bH95L.html |archivedate=27 January 2016 |df= }}</ref> The film was a critical failure.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/movie-reviews/review-halla-bol/story-CK0FF3CqKkN56HGVuYY6JP.html |title=Review: Halla Bol |work=Hindustan Times |author=Mohamed, Khalid |date=11 January 2008 |accessdate=9 January 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160127030751/http://www.hindustantimes.com/movie-reviews/review-halla-bol/story-CK0FF3CqKkN56HGVuYY6JP.html |archivedate=27 January 2016 |df= }}</ref> Later that year, she co-starred with [[Shahid Kapoor]] in [[Aziz Mirza]]'s romantic comedy ''[[Kismat Konnection]]''. Faring poorly at the box office,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.boxofficeindia.com/showProd.php?itemCat=215&catName=MjAwOA== |title=Box office 2008 |publisher=BoxOfficeIndia |accessdate=9 January 2012 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131014132123/http://boxofficeindia.com/showProd.php?itemCat=215&catName=MjAwOA%3D%3D |archivedate=14 October 2013 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref> the film and her performance generated a negative response; critic Sonia Chopra commented, \"[Balan] is made to look downright drab. The haircut is unflattering, the make-up too plain, the clothes usually in off-white or brown. Plus the character is repetitive and reminds us of the one she played in ''Lage Raho Munna Bhai''.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/review-2-kismat-konnection-review-bollywood-14719095.html |title=Review 2: Kismat Konnection |last=Chopra |first=Sonia |publisher=Sify |accessdate=9 January 2012 |date=18 July 2008 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131222174813/http://www.sify.com/movies/review-2-kismat-konnection-review-bollywood-14719095.html |archivedate=22 December 2013 |df= }}</ref>\n\n===Success (2009\u20132012)===\n[[File:VidyaBalan05.jpg|thumb|upright|left|Vidya at a promotional event for ''[[Paa (film)|Paa]]'' in 2009. She won her first [[Filmfare Award for Best Actress]] for the film.]]\nIn 2009 Vidya played the role of an unwed [[gynaecologist]] struggling with her 12-year-old son's [[progeria syndrome]], in the [[R. Balki]]-directed [[dramedy]] ''[[Paa (film)|Paa]]''. Amitabh Bachchan played the role of Vidya's son and Abhishek Bachchan played the title character. A critical and commercial success, the film has been described as a major turning point in her career.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://boxofficeindia.com/showProd.php?itemCat=288&catName=MjAwOQ== |title=Box office 2009 |publisher=BoxOfficeIndia |accessdate=9 January 2012 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131014131907/http://boxofficeindia.com/showProd.php?itemCat=288&catName=MjAwOQ%3D%3D |archivedate=14 October 2013 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Vidya Balan: Raring to go! |work=The Times of India |author=Kazmi, Nikhat |date=3 December 2009 |accessdate=25 August 2010 |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2010-01-01/news-interviews/28146207_1_vidya-balan-paa-happy-new-year |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130908172803/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2010-01-01/news-interviews/28146207_1_vidya-balan-paa-happy-new-year |archivedate=8 September 2013 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref> Sukanya Verma compared her acting style to that of [[Dimple Kapadia]] and noted, \"Balan is poignant yet restrained and projects an impressive figure of grace and integrity\";<ref>{{cite web|title=Watch Paa for Auro |publisher=Rediff |author=Verma, Sukanya |date=4 December 2009 |accessdate=25 August 2010 |url=http://movies.rediff.com/report/2009/dec/04/review-watch-paa-for-auro.htm |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100410161623/http://movies.rediff.com/report/2009/dec/04/review-watch-paa-for-auro.htm |archivedate=10 April 2010 |df= }}</ref> [[Nikhat Kazmi]] from ''[[The Times of India]]'' further argued that Vidya was successful in lending a \"rare dignity to the image of the Bollywood mom.\"<ref>{{cite news |title=Review: Paa |author=Kazmi, Nikhat |date=3 December 2009 |accessdate=25 August 2010 |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/movie-reviews/hindi/Paa/movie-review/5297226.cms |work=The Times of India |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131221134747/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/movie-reviews/hindi/Paa/movie-review/5297226.cms |archivedate=21 December 2013 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref> Her portrayal garnered her several awards, including a Filmfare Award for Best Actress and a [[Screen Award for Best Actress]].<ref name=\"oldawards\"/>\n\nVidya followed the success of ''Paa'' with the [[Vishal Bhardwaj]]-produced ''[[Ishqiya]]'' (2010), a [[black comedy]] directed by debutant [[Abhishek Chaubey]]; co-starring [[Naseeruddin Shah]], [[Arshad Warsi]], and [[Salman Shahid]]. Vidya's role was that of the sexually manipulative Krishna Verma. Vidya described her character as \"an epitome of grey\" and a departure from the conventional portrayal of women in cinema.<ref>{{cite news|title=Vidya Balan in never seen before role in 'Ishqiya' |date=26 January 2010 |accessdate=16 October 2012 |url=http://www.thehindu.com/arts/movies/article94956.ece |work=The Hindu |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131214155906/http://www.thehindu.com/arts/movies/article94956.ece |archivedate=14 December 2013 |df= }}</ref> In preparation for her part, she undertook professional training to speak in the local [[Uttar Pradesh]]-dialect.<ref>{{cite news|title=Vidya Balan takes acting lessons from Naseer|date=29 September 2008|accessdate=16 October 2012|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report_vidya-balan-takes-acting-lessons-from-naseer_1194161|work=Daily News and Analysis}}</ref> The feature as well as her performance received critical acclaim. [[Anupama Chopra]] of [[NDTV]] stated, \"Vidya Balan's smoldering looks scorch the screen even as her eyes hint at tragedy. She proves that she is miles ahead of the cookie cutter Barbie dolls that clutter Bollywood and that sensuality has very little to do with showing skin.\"<ref>{{cite web|title=Review : Ishqiya |url=http://movies.ndtv.com/movie-reviews/ishqiya-473 |author=Chopra, Anupama |date=29 January 2010 |publisher=NDTV |accessdate=9 January 2011 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140110090129/http://movies.ndtv.com/movie-reviews/ishqiya-473 |archivedate=10 January 2014 |df= }}</ref> Her work in the film earned Vidya a [[Filmfare Critics Award for Best Actress]], a second consecutive Best Actress award at Screen and a nomination for Best Actress at Filmfare.<ref name=\"awards\"/>\n\n[[Raj Kumar Gupta]]'s semi-biographical thriller ''[[No One Killed Jessica]]'' with [[Rani Mukerji]] was Vidya's first release of 2011. The film, based on the [[Jessica Lal]] murder case, saw her portray the real-life character of Sabrina Lal, Jessica's reticent sister. While preparing for the role, Vidya did not meet Lal on the insistence of Gupta as \"the Sabrina [...] today is different from the Sabrina a decade ago, [when] the story begins\".<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/arts/cinema/article960860.ece |title=Take Two |last=Devi Dundoo |first=Sangeetha |date=25 December 2010 |accessdate=11 January 2012 |work=The Hindu |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20120914062120/http://www.thehindu.com/arts/cinema/article960860.ece |archivedate=14 September 2012  }}</ref> ''No One Killed Jessica'' met with contrasting reviews from critics, but Vidya's performance was particularly praised. ''[[The Hindu]]'' remarked on Vidya's ability to be \"in sublime control over her emotions\"<ref>{{cite news |title=The sledgehammer wants to be subtle |url=http://www.thehindu.com/arts/cinema/article1073041.ece |last=Kamath |first=Sudhish |date=29 January 2012 |work=The Hindu |accessdate=8 January 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110111045134/http://www.thehindu.com/arts/cinema/article1073041.ece |archivedate=11 January 2011  }}</ref> and Savera Someshwar of Rediff.com added that \"her hesitant body language, her faith, her helplessness, her rage, her sorrow and her gratitude all come across beautifully\".<ref>{{cite web|title=Review: No One Killed Jessica could have been better |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/no-one-killed-jessica-review/20110106.htm |last=Someshwar |first=Savera |date=6 January 2012 |publisher=Rediff |accessdate=8 October 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121104044329/http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/no-one-killed-jessica-review/20110106.htm |archivedate= 4 November 2012 |df= }}</ref> The film had earnings of {{INRConvert|490|m}} and was noted for being a commercial success despite the absence of a male lead.<ref name=\"boxoffice2011\">{{cite web|url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/bollywood-rediscovered-mega-hits-in-2011/212464-8-66.html |title=Bollywood rediscovered mega hits in 2011 |publisher=CNN-IBN |accessdate=17 December 2011 |date=16 December 2011 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130726093958/http://ibnlive.in.com/news/bollywood-rediscovered-mega-hits-in-2011/212464-8-66.html |archivedate=26 July 2013 |df= }}</ref> Vidya earned another Filmfare nomination in the Best Actress category for the film.<ref>{{cite web|title=Nominations for 57th Idea Filmfare Awards 2011 |url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/celebrities/features/type/view/id/2974/2974 |publisher=Bollywood Hungama |accessdate=11 January 2011 |date=11 January 2011 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20120720224321/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/celebrities/features/type/view/id/2974/2974 |archivedate=20 July 2012 |df= }}</ref> In March 2011, a retrospective of Vidya's films was held in Australia, as part of the [[Bollywood and Beyond]] festival.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Bollywood Hungama |title=Indian film festival in Australia to screen retrospective of Vidya Balan's films |url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/1295329/Indian-Film-Festival-in-Australia-to-screen-retrospective-of-Vidya-Balans-films |date=15 March 2011 |accessdate=13 March 2011 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131023060505/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/1295329/Indian-Film-Festival-in-Australia-to-screen-retrospective-of-Vidya-Balans-films |archivedate=23 October 2013 |df= }}</ref> That same year, Vidya featured in a [[guest appearance]] in [[Santosh Sivan]]'s Malayalam language [[fantasy film]] ''[[Urumi (film)|Urumi]]''.<ref>{{cite news |title=Vidya to dub in Malayalam for Urumi |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-02-27/news-interviews/28637924_1_malayalam-film-vidya-balan-urumi |date=27 February 2012 |work=The Times of India |accessdate=20 November 2012 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131023060529/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-02-27/news-interviews/28637924_1_malayalam-film-vidya-balan-urumi |archivedate=23 October 2013 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref>\n\n[[File:Tusshar Kapoor, Vidya Balan, Emraan Hashmi at The Dirty Picture audio release (10).jpg|thumb|upright=1.0|alt=Tusshar Kapoor, Vidya Balan and Emraan Hashmi pose for the camera together.|Vidya with co-stars [[Tusshar Kapoor]] (left) and [[Emraan Hashmi]] at the audio release of ''[[The Dirty Picture (2011 film)|The Dirty Picture]]'' in 2011. Her performance earned her a [[National Film Award for Best Actress]].]]\n\nVidya's next appearance was in Ekta Kapoor's production ''[[The Dirty Picture (2011 film)|The Dirty Picture]]'', a biopic based on the life and death of the controversial Indian actress [[Silk Smitha]].<ref>{{cite news |work=The Hindu |author=Kumar, Anuj |title=What an odd one! |url=http://www.thehindu.com/arts/cinema/article1075100.ece |date=9 January 2011 |accessdate=9 January 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110112071923/http://www.thehindu.com/arts/cinema/article1075100.ece |archivedate=12 January 2011  }}</ref> Vidya was cast as Silk, who was\u2014in Vidya's words\u2014\"known for her brazenness and in-your-face sexuality.\"<ref>{{cite web|publisher=CNN-IBN |title=Silk is sexy, desirable, but not sleazy: Vidya |url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/silk-is-sexy-desirable-but-not-sleazy-vidya/206962-8-66.html |date=29 November 2011 |accessdate=3 December 2011 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111201213043/http://ibnlive.in.com/news/silk-is-sexy-desirable-but-not-sleazy-vidya/206962-8-66.html |archivedate= 1 December 2011 |df= }}</ref> She described the role as the \"boldest\" she had ever played, one that \"required a lot of mental preparation.\" To look the part, she gained {{convert|12|kg|lb|0}}.<ref>\n{{cite news|work=Hindustan Times|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/i-gained-12-kilograms-for-the-dirty-picture-vidya-balan/story-WivVWCiYJZMY7MN0RZcYDI.html|agency=ANI|date=30 November 2011|accessdate=2 December 2011|title=I gained 12 kilograms for The Dirty Picture: Vidya Balan|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170324212117/http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/i-gained-12-kilograms-for-the-dirty-picture-vidya-balan/story-WivVWCiYJZMY7MN0RZcYDI.html|archive-date=24 March 2017|url-status=live}}\n</ref> The film opened to major critical acclaim, and Vidya received unanimous praise for her portrayal which several reviewers regarded as her best performance to date.<ref name=\"Hero\"/><ref>{{cite news |work=The Times of India |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-01-03/news-interviews/30581535_1_vidya-balan-silk-smitha-sabrina-lal |date=5 January 2012 |accessdate=7 January 2012 |author=Iyer, Meena |title=What's left for Vidya Balan to do in 2012 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130908174032/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-01-03/news-interviews/30581535_1_vidya-balan-silk-smitha-sabrina-lal |archivedate=8 September 2013 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref><ref>\n{{cite news|last=Bhattacharya|first=Roshmila|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/vidya-balan-rules-bo-with-biggest-grossing-woman-centric-films/story-YztihFamFXeM6q5h8MzXKO.html|title=Vidya Balan rules BO with biggest grossing woman-centric films|work=Hindustan Times|accessdate=23 September 2012|date=12 April 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171203172546/http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/vidya-balan-rules-bo-with-biggest-grossing-woman-centric-films/story-YztihFamFXeM6q5h8MzXKO.html|archive-date=3 December 2017|url-status=live}}\n</ref> Khalid Mohamed observed, \"She's extraordinary: gutsy, consistently in character and unafraid of exposing her darker side. Here's the kind of complex performance which you haven't evidenced in years and years.\"<ref>\n{{cite news|work=Hindustan Times|title=Critics go gaga over The Dirty Picture|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/critics-go-gaga-over-the-dirty-picture/story-YblUtdRKbDsZMKc4r3iOPI.html|date=2 December 2011|accessdate=2 December 2011|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170319041916/http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/critics-go-gaga-over-the-dirty-picture/story-YblUtdRKbDsZMKc4r3iOPI.html|archive-date=19 March 2017|url-status=live}}\n</ref> Her director [[Milan Luthria]] described her as the contemporary claimant of the \"sex-symbol\" title and compared her \"voluptuousness\" to the likes of yesteryear actresses [[Sridevi]] and [[Vyjayanthimala]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-12-01/news-interviews/30459254_1_vidya-balan-naseeruddin-shah-milan-luthria |title=Vidya Balan has a unique sex-appeal: Milan Luthria |work=The Times of India |date=1 December 2011 |accessdate=1 December 2011 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130908175135/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-12-01/news-interviews/30459254_1_vidya-balan-naseeruddin-shah-milan-luthria |archivedate=8 September 2013 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref> With earnings of {{INRConvert|1.14|b}} worldwide, ''The Dirty Picture'' ranks among her most successful releases.<ref name=\"all-time\"/> Vidya won a second Filmfare Award, a third consecutive Screen Award, and a [[National Film Award for Best Actress]].<ref name=\"awards\">{{cite web|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/celebritymicro/awards/id/8098 |title=Vidya Balan&nbsp;\u2014 Awards |accessdate=25 August 2010 |publisher=Bollywood Hungama |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120129143424/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/celebritymicro/awards/id/8098 |archivedate=29 January 2012 |df= }}</ref><ref name=\"national\">{{cite web|title=National Awards: Vidya Balan gets best actress for 'The Dirty Picture' |url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/national-awards-vidya-balan-gets-best-actress/236998-8-66.html |publisher=CNN-IBN |accessdate=30 September 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120703041747/http://ibnlive.in.com/news/national-awards-vidya-balan-gets-best-actress/236998-8-66.html |archivedate= 3 July 2012 |df= }}</ref>\n\nFor her next feature film, Vidya starred as Vidya Bagchi, a pregnant woman in search of her missing husband in [[Sujoy Ghosh]]'s ''[[Kahaani]]'' (2012). The thriller, set in the city of [[Kolkata]] during the [[Durga Puja]] festivities, met with wide critical acclaim. To lend authenticity to her part, Vidya met several pregnant women and learnt about their lifestyle.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.indianexpress.com/news/vidya-balan-gets-into-character-of-pregnant-woman-for--kahaani-/905582|title=Vidya Balan gets into character of pregnant woman for 'Kahaani'|work=The Indian Express|accessdate=15 October 2012|date=30 January 2012}}</ref> She generated public and media attention by wearing a fake baby bump during the film's promotional activities.<ref>{{cite news |last=Kelkar Dabholkar |first=Reshma |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-02-21/news-interviews/31078998_1_kahaani-vidya-balan-sujoy-ghosh |title=Vidya Balan's baby bump? |work=The Times of India |accessdate=21 February 2012 |date=18 October 2012 |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20130103130955/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-02-21/news-interviews/31078998_1_kahaani-vidya-balan-sujoy-ghosh |archivedate=3 January 2013 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Vidya Balan rides BEST bus to promote her Kahaani |url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/vidya-balan-rides-best-bus-to-promote-her-kahaani/1/175688.html |date=28 February 2012 |work=India Today |accessdate=18 October 2012 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121030060134/http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/vidya-balan-rides-best-bus-to-promote-her-kahaani/1/175688.html |archivedate=30 October 2012 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref> Vidya received further appreciation for her performance in ''Kahaani''. Subhash K. Jha praised Vidya's portrayal of \"grace under pressure\" as \"measured and skilled\"; Pratim D. Gupta of ''[[The Telegraph (Calcutta)|The Telegraph]]'' added that she \"gets into the physicality of a pregnant woman with unfailing mastery\".<ref>{{cite web|title=Review: Kahaani |url=http://movies.ndtv.com/movie-reviews/review-kahaani-689 |author=Jha, Subhash K. |date=9 March 2012 |publisher=NDTV |accessdate=15 October 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150103061147/http://movies.ndtv.com/movie-reviews/review-kahaani-689 |archivedate= 3 January 2015 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.telegraphindia.com/1120310/jsp/entertainment/story_15231247.jsp#.T3F0dEoQgrU |title=What a ''Kahaani'' |first=Pratim D. |last=Gupta |work=The Telegraph |accessdate=27 March 2012 |date=10 March 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120313013944/http://www.telegraphindia.com/1120310/jsp/entertainment/story_15231247.jsp |archivedate=13 March 2012 |df= }}</ref> Once again, the film proved to be a success, grossing over {{INRConvert|1.04|b}} worldwide.<ref>\n{{cite news|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/vidya-balan-s-kahaani-completes-50-days-grosses-rs-104-cr-worldwide/story-8bAabZus5GJWR8fLwIoXQN.html|title=Vidya Balan's Kahaani completes 50 days, grosses Rs. 104 cr worldwide|work=Hindustan Times|accessdate=27 April 2012|date=27 April 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171112021436/http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/vidya-balan-s-kahaani-completes-50-days-grosses-rs-104-cr-worldwide/story-8bAabZus5GJWR8fLwIoXQN.html|archive-date=12 November 2017|url-status=live}}\n</ref> Vidya won a fourth consecutive Best Actress Award at Screen and a third Best Actress Award at Filmfare.<ref>{{cite news|last=Gupta |first=Shubhra |title=Night belongs to Paan Singh Tomar, Barfi!, Kahaani |url=http://www.indianexpress.com/news/night-belongs-to-paan-singh-tomar-barfi--kahaani/1058501/0 |date=13 January 2013 |work=The Indian Express |accessdate=13 January 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130116205054/http://www.indianexpress.com/news/night-belongs-to-paan-singh-tomar-barfi--kahaani/1058501/0 |archivedate=16 January 2013 |df= }}</ref><ref name=\"ff12\">{{cite web|title=Filmfare Awards: All the action from the awards night |url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/filmfare-awards-live-all-the-action-from-the-awards-night/316815-8-66.html |date=21 January 2013 |publisher=CNN-IBN |accessdate=21 January 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130121023308/http://ibnlive.in.com/news/filmfare-awards-live-all-the-action-from-the-awards-night/316815-8-66.html |archivedate=21 January 2013 |df= }}</ref>\n\n===Commercial struggles and resurgence (2013\u20132017)===\n\n[[File:Vidya Balan in 2013.jpg|thumb|upright|alt=Vidya Balan is smiling away from the camera|Vidya at a promotional event for ''[[Shaadi Ke Side Effects]]'' in 2014]]\n\nAfter completing the duties of a jury member at the [[2013 Cannes Film Festival]], Vidya starred opposite [[Emraan Hashmi]] as a boisterous [[Punjabi people|Punjabi woman]] in ''[[Ghanchakkar (film)|Ghanchakkar]]'', a comic-thriller from director Raj Kumar Gupta.<ref name=\"cannes\">{{cite news|last=Kulkarni |first=Onkar |title=Vidya Balan on ''Ghanchakkar'' and her first Cannes outing |url=http://www.indianexpress.com/news/vidya-balan-on-ghanchakkar-and-her-first-cannes-outing/1134594/0 |date=29 June 2013 |work=The Indian Express |accessdate=1 July 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130704030052/http://www.indianexpress.com/news/vidya-balan-on-ghanchakkar-and-her-first-cannes-outing/1134594/0 |archivedate= 4 July 2013 |df= }}</ref><ref>\n{{cite news|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-01-23/news-interviews/36485185_1_vidya-balan-siddharth-roy-kapur-rajkumar-gupta|title=Marriage won't affect my work: Vidya Balan|date=23 January 2013|work=The Times of India|accessdate=23 January 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131127162002/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-01-23/news-interviews/36485185_1_vidya-balan-siddharth-roy-kapur-rajkumar-gupta|archive-date=27 November 2013|url-status=live}}\n</ref> Critics were unenthusiastic about the film and it earned little at the box office.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.indianexpress.com/news/ghanchakkar-flops-emraan-hashmi-will-be-the-most-affected/1137791/ |title=Ghanchakkar flops, Emraan Hashmi will be the most affected |work=The Indian Express |author=Singh, Harneet |date=5 July 2013 |accessdate=5 July 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130708090603/http://www.indianexpress.com/news/ghanchakkar-flops-emraan-hashmi-will-be-the-most-affected/1137791 |archivedate= 8 July 2013 |df= }}</ref> Vidya then provided the voice of [[Draupadi]] for ''[[Mahabharat (2013 film)|Mahabharat]]'', a [[computer animation|3D animation film]] based on the Indian epic [[Mahabharata|of the same name]].<ref>\n{{cite news|title=Plan your weekend: movies releasing this Friday|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/plan-your-weekend-movies-releasing-this-friday/story-6iSDch5Lh32iSgAJSf8MOO.html|date=26 December 2013|work=Hindustan Times|accessdate=28 December 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171117174702/http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/plan-your-weekend-movies-releasing-this-friday/story-6iSDch5Lh32iSgAJSf8MOO.html|archive-date=17 November 2017|url-status=live}}\n</ref>\n\nThe romantic comedy ''[[Shaadi Ke Side Effects]]'' was Vidya's first film release of 2014. Directed by [[Saket Chaudhary]] and co-starring [[Farhan Akhtar]], the film is about a married couple who face a series of comic events after the birth of their child. Critics found the film to be a \"bit overstretched\", but praised both Akhtar and Vidya's performances.<ref>{{cite news|title=Movie review: Shaadi Ke Side Effects is a bit overstretched |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/reviews/movie-review-vidya-farhan-s-performances-enrich-shaadi-ke-side-effects/article1-1189011.aspx |date=27 February 2014 |work=Hindustan Times |accessdate=1 March 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140228201227/http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/reviews/movie-review-vidya-farhan-s-performances-enrich-shaadi-ke-side-effects/article1-1189011.aspx |archivedate=28 February 2014 |df= }}</ref> Also that year, Vidya featured as the host of ''No More Kamzor'', a television special on women empowerment.<ref>{{cite news|title=Vidya Balan hosts women's day special 'No More Kamzor' |url=http://www.deccanherald.com/content/389708/vidya-balan-hosts-women039s-day.html |date=4 March 2014 |work=Deccan Herald |accessdate=6 March 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140306130936/http://www.deccanherald.com/content/389708/vidya-balan-hosts-women039s-day.html |archivedate= 6 March 2014 |df= }}</ref> She then starred in the comedy-drama ''[[Bobby Jasoos]]'', in which she played the eponymous role of a [[Hyderabadi]] woman aspiring to be a detective. Vidya was drawn to the idea of playing a detective and identified with the character's struggle to prove herself.<ref>{{cite news|title=My character in 'Bobby Jasoos' does not know everything: Vidya Balan |url=http://www.financialexpress.com/news/my-character-in-bobby-jasoos-does-not-know-everything-vidya-balan/1264998 |date=28 June 2014 |work=The Financial Express |accessdate=4 July 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140701010745/http://www.financialexpress.com/news/my-character-in-bobby-jasoos-does-not-know-everything-vidya-balan/1264998 |archivedate= 1 July 2014 |df= }}</ref> It required her to sport twelve elaborate disguises, and she trained with a language coach to adopt a Hyderabadi accent.<ref>{{cite news|last=KBR |first=Upala |title=I really wanted to do a film with a Khan but I can't do it now: Vidya Balan |url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/interview-i-really-wanted-to-do-a-film-with-a-khan-but-i-can-t-do-it-now-vidya-balan-1996203 |date=18 June 2014 |work=Daily News and Analysis |accessdate=4 July 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714222805/http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/interview-i-really-wanted-to-do-a-film-with-a-khan-but-i-can-t-do-it-now-vidya-balan-1996203 |archivedate=14 July 2014 |df= }}</ref> Saumil Gandhi of ''[[Mumbai Mirror]]'' wrote that Vidya's \"effervescence rubs off on the proceedings and gives it an energy that drives the film\".<ref>{{cite news|last=Shetty-Saha |first=Shubha |title=Movie Review: 'Bobby Jasoos' |url=http://www.mid-day.com/articles/movie-review-bobby-jasoos/15424162 |date=4 July 2014 |work=Mid Day |accessdate=7 April 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150414011404/http://www.mid-day.com/articles/movie-review-bobby-jasoos/15424162 |archivedate=14 April 2015 |df= }}</ref> However, both ''Shaadi Ke Side Effects'' and ''Bobby Jasoos'' failed to find a wide audience.<ref>{{cite news |last=Pradhan |first=Bharathi S. |title=Three flops, and a kiss |url=http://www.telegraphindia.com/1140713/jsp/7days/18609788.jsp |date=13 July 2014 |work=The Telegraph |accessdate=12 June 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150614043516/http://www.telegraphindia.com/1140713/jsp/7days/18609788.jsp |archivedate=14 June 2015  }}</ref>\n\nIn 2015, Vidya reteamed with Hashmi in the [[Mohit Suri]]-directed romantic drama ''[[Hamari Adhuri Kahani]]''. Penned by [[Mahesh Bhatt]], the film tells the story of Vasudha, a single mother trapped in an abusive marriage, who has an extra-marital affair.<ref>{{cite web|last=Tuteja |first=Joginder |title=Book review - Mahesh Bhatt's All That Could Have Been (soon to be made as Hamaari Adhuri Kahaani) |url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/features/type/view/id/7953 |date=23 February 2015 |publisher=Bollywood Hungama |accessdate=19 March 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150331053301/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/features/type/view/id/7953 |archivedate=31 March 2015 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Das |first=Anirban |title=Vidya Balan to play Suchitra Sen |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/vidya-balan-to-play-suchitra-sen/article1-1326495.aspx |date=15 March 2015 |work=Hindustan Times |accessdate=19 March 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150317173610/http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/vidya-balan-to-play-suchitra-sen/article1-1326495.aspx |archivedate=17 March 2015 |df= }}</ref> Shubha Shetty-Saha of ''[[Mid Day]]'' commented that Vidya \"has shown us what she's capable of in her earlier movies. But here, saddled with a boring, outdated, weepy character, there was nothing much even she could do\".<ref>{{cite news|last=Shetty-Saha |first=Shubha |title='Hamari Adhuri Kahani' {{ndash}} Movie Review |url=http://www.mid-day.com/articles/hamari-adhuri-kahani---movie-review/16286150 |date=12 June 2015 |work=Mid Day |accessdate=12 June 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150613234058/http://www.mid-day.com/articles/hamari-adhuri-kahani---movie-review/16286150 |archivedate=13 June 2015 |df= }}</ref> Vidya next took on the part of a police officer in ''[[Te3n]]'' (2016), a thriller inspired by the 2013 South Korean film ''[[Montage (2013 film)|Montage]]'', co-starring Amitabh Bachchan and [[Nawazuddin Siddiqui]]. She identified with her character's \"silent aggression\" and drawn to the idea of playing a character who commands respect.<ref name=\"move\">{{cite news|last=Chatterjee|first=Alakananda|title=Constantly on the move|url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/mumbai/entertainment/constantly-on-the-move/article8699167.ece|date=7 June 2016|work=The Hindu|accessdate=9 June 2016}}</ref> NDTV's Saibal Chatterjee criticised the decision to bill Vidya's pivotal role as a special appearance and noted how much her presence benefited the film.<ref>{{cite web|last=Chatterjee|first=Saibal|title=Te3n Movie Review|url=http://movies.ndtv.com/movie-reviews/te3n-movie-review-1273|date=9 June 2016|publisher=NDTV|accessdate=3 December 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171204171118/http://movies.ndtv.com/movie-reviews/te3n-movie-review-1273|archivedate=4 December 2017}}</ref> Rajeev Masand was critical of the film's predictable denouement, but wrote that Vidya \"is reliably solid each time she's on screen, raising her brow, curling her lip to effectively communicate more than words can\".<ref>{{cite web|last=Masand |first=Rajeev |title='Te3n' Review: Compelling Thriller, Slowly Draws You Into Suspense |url=http://www.news18.com/news/movies/te3n-review-compelling-thriller-slowly-draws-you-into-suspense-1254559.html |date=10 June 2016 |publisher=CNN-IBN |accessdate=12 June 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160611132152/http://www.news18.com/news/movies/te3n-review-compelling-thriller-slowly-draws-you-into-suspense-1254559.html |archivedate=11 June 2016 |df= }}</ref> She then portrayed the actress [[Geeta Bali]] in multiple songs for ''[[Ekk Albela]]'', a [[Marathi cinema|Marathi]] language biopic of [[Bhagwan Dada]].<ref name=\"move\"/>\n\n[[File:Vidya Balan at the 63rd Filmfare Awards.jpg|thumb|upright=0.8|left|Vidya at the [[63rd Filmfare Awards]], where she won her fourth Best Actress award for ''[[Tumhari Sulu]]'' (2017)]]\n\nVidya's final release of 2016 was Sujoy Ghosh's ''[[Kahaani 2: Durga Rani Singh]]'', a sequel to ''Kahaani'', although it narrated a different story. The film was highly anticipated, and critics believed that Vidya's recent spate of poorly received films would come to an end.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/kahaani-2-vidya-balan-arjun-rampal-sujoy-ghosh-durga-rani-singh/1/823386.html |title=Between Kahaani and Kahaani 2, what accounts for Vidya Balan's lack of success? |last=Ghosh |first=Devarshi |work=India Today |date=30 November 2016 |accessdate=10 December 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161218064837/http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/kahaani-2-vidya-balan-arjun-rampal-sujoy-ghosh-durga-rani-singh/1/823386.html |archivedate=18 December 2016 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/kahaani-2-will-vidya-balan-recreate-the-kahaani-magic/story-gSPfkvNput5xoQOQdyrDvI.html |title=Kahaani 2: Will Vidya Balan recreate the Kahaani magic? |work=Hindustan Times |date=10 December 2016 |accessdate=10 December 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161209233820/http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/kahaani-2-will-vidya-balan-recreate-the-kahaani-magic/story-gSPfkvNput5xoQOQdyrDvI.html |archivedate= 9 December 2016 |df= }}</ref> ''Kahaani 2'', however, was not as well-received as the first film, although Vidya received a Best Actress nomination at Filmfare for her portrayal of a [[child sexual abuse]] survivor in the film.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/kahaani-2-review-roundup-heres-what-critics-have-say-about-vidya-balan-starrer-706509 |title=Kahaani 2 review roundup: Here's what critics have to say about the Vidya Balan-starrer |last=Goswami |first=Parismita |work=[[International Business Times]] |date=2 December 2016 |accessdate=10 December 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161202114311/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/kahaani-2-review-roundup-heres-what-critics-have-say-about-vidya-balan-starrer-706509 |archivedate= 2 December 2016 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=62nd Jio Filmfare Awards 2017 Nominations |url=http://www.filmfare.com/news/nominations-for-the-62nd-jio-filmfare-awards-17987.html |work=Filmfare |date=9 January 2017 |accessdate=13 January 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170113122217/http://www.filmfare.com/news/nominations-for-the-62nd-jio-filmfare-awards-17987.html |archivedate=13 January 2017 |df= }}</ref> Raja Sen thought that despite being an engaging thriller the film's denouement was predictable, but added that \"with tremendous commitment to the part, [Vidya] gives us a stirring performance free of vanity or obviousness\" and praised her \"knack for winning the audience over; when she gasps, we gasp\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/review-kahaani-2-is-let-down-by-predictability/20161202.htm |title=Review: Kahaani 2 is let down by predictability |last=Sen |first=Raja |publisher=Rediff.com |date=2 December 2016 |accessdate=13 January 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170113172230/http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/review-kahaani-2-is-let-down-by-predictability/20161202.htm |archivedate=13 January 2017 |df= }}</ref>\n\n[[Srijit Mukherji]]'s period drama ''[[Begum Jaan]]'' (2017) saw Vidya play the role of the titular [[procuring (prostitution)|procurer]]. A Hindi language remake of the Bengali film ''[[Rajkahini]]'' (2015), ''Begum Jaan'' tells the story of prostitutes who are affected by the [[partition of India]] in 1947.<ref>{{cite news|last=Ray |first=Dhritiman |title=Mahesh Bhatt\u2019s Rajkahini remake being shot in Jharkhand |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/Mahesh-Bhatts-Rajkahini-remake-being-shot-in-Jharkhand/articleshow/52890427.cms |date=23 June 2016 |work=The Times of India |accessdate=27 June 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160628031709/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/Mahesh-Bhatts-Rajkahini-remake-being-shot-in-Jharkhand/articleshow/52890427.cms |archivedate=28 June 2016 |df= }}</ref> In preparation, Vidya worked with Mukherji to provide a backstory to her character, and she researched the era by reading [[Urvashi Butalia]]\u2019s novel ''[[Urvashi Butalia#The Other Side of Silence|The Other Side of Silence]]''.<ref name=\"begum\">{{cite news|last=Jhunjhunwala |first=Udita |title=Vidya Balan on Begum Jaan: \u2018She\u2019s almost like Gabbar, she fears no one\u2019 |url=http://www.livemint.com/Leisure/Zr7riZyQ7UNmqwq93zf7cM/Vidya-Balan-I-have-not-played-a-character-who-is-so-inyou.html |date=13 April 2017 |work=[[Mint (newspaper)|Mint]] |accessdate=15 April 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170415154349/http://www.livemint.com/Leisure/Zr7riZyQ7UNmqwq93zf7cM/Vidya-Balan-I-have-not-played-a-character-who-is-so-inyou.html |archivedate=15 April 2017 |df= }}</ref> Filming in the barren landscape of rural [[Jharkhand]] proved to be a challenge for Vidya, and she said that the experience taught her that \"if push comes to shove, I can brave scorpions, snakes and whatever else\".<ref name=\"begum\"/> [[Anna M. M. Vetticad]] of ''[[Firstpost]]'' disliked the film and blamed the writing for Vidya's inability to \"dig deep and summon up a relatable human being\".<ref>{{cite web|last=Vetticad |first=Anna MM |title=Begum Jaan movie review: Vidya Balan and feminism deserve better than this soulless film |url=http://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/begum-jaan-movie-review-vidya-balan-and-feminism-deserve-better-than-this-soulless-film-3383716.html |date=14 April 2017 |website=[[Firstpost]] |accessdate=15 April 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170414232602/http://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/begum-jaan-movie-review-vidya-balan-and-feminism-deserve-better-than-this-soulless-film-3383716.html |archivedate=14 April 2017 |df= }}</ref>\n\nLater in 2017, Vidya played Sulu, a spirited housewife who moonlights as a relationship advice talk show host, in the comedy-drama ''[[Tumhari Sulu]]''. She identified with her character's enthusiastic personality and was challenged by the opportunity to play a rare comic part.<ref name=\"sulu\">{{cite web|last=Parikh|first=Urvi|url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/you-want-it-to-sound-sexy-na-vidya-balan-tumhari-sulu/20171106.htm|title='You want it to sound sexy, na?'|publisher=Rediff.com|date=6 November 2017|accessdate=25 January 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180126012536/http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/you-want-it-to-sound-sexy-na-vidya-balan-tumhari-sulu/20171106.htm|archivedate=26 January 2018}}</ref> She drew on her experience of playing a radio jockey in ''Lage Raho Munna Bhai'' and listened to late-night talk shows.<ref name=\"sulu\"/> Writing for ''The Times of India'', Neil Soans commended Vidya for \"infusing Sulu with an abundance of infectious optimism without being aggravating\", and Shubhra Gupta of ''[[The Indian Express]]'' took note of how well she channeled \"her distinctive voice and full-bellied laughter to invest Sulu with real warmth\".<ref>{{cite news |last=Soans |first=Neil |title=Tumhari Sulu Movie Review |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/movie-reviews/tumhari-sulu/movie-review/61668494.cms |date=16 November 2017 |work=The Times of India |accessdate=17 November 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171117093917/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/movie-reviews/tumhari-sulu/movie-review/61668494.cms |archivedate=17 November 2017  }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Gupta |first=Shubhra |title=Tumhari Sulu Movie Review |url=http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/movie-review/tumhari-sulu-movie-review-vidya-balan-manav-kaul-film-4940289/ |date=17 November 2017 |work=The Indian Express |accessdate=17 November 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171117174759/http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/movie-review/tumhari-sulu-movie-review-vidya-balan-manav-kaul-film-4940289/ |archivedate=17 November 2017  }}</ref> With earnings of over {{INRConvert|500|m}} on a {{INRConvert|200|m}} budget, ''Tumhari Sulu'' proved to be Vidya's first commercial success since ''Kahaani''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ndtv.com/entertainment/tumhari-sulu-box-office-collection-day-3-vidya-balans-film-had-a-super-strong-weekend-1777717|title=Tumhari Sulu Box Office Collection Day 3: Vidya Balan's film had a \"super-strong weekend\"|publisher=NDTV|date=20 November 2017|accessdate=20 November 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171121034525/https://www.ndtv.com/entertainment/tumhari-sulu-box-office-collection-day-3-vidya-balans-film-had-a-super-strong-weekend-1777717|archivedate=21 November 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/box-office-special-features/box-office-worldwide-collections-day-wise-break-tumhari-sulu/|title=Box Office: Worldwide collections and day wise break up of Tumhari Sulu|publisher=Bollywood Hungama|accessdate=18 December 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171201043132/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/box-office-special-features/box-office-worldwide-collections-day-wise-break-tumhari-sulu/|archivedate=1 December 2017}}</ref> NDTV listed her performance as the best by a Hindi film actress that year, and she won her fifth Screen Award and fourth Filmfare Award for Best Actress.<ref>{{cite web|last=Sen|first=Raja|url=https://www.ndtv.com/entertainment/zaira-wasim-to-vidya-balan-a-list-of-2017s-best-actresses-1795708|title=Zaira Wasim To Vidya Balan: A List Of 2017's Best Actresses|publisher=NDTV|date=4 January 2018|accessdate=25 January 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180126012450/https://www.ndtv.com/entertainment/zaira-wasim-to-vidya-balan-a-list-of-2017s-best-actresses-1795708|archivedate=26 January 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Star Screen Awards 2017 full Winners List: Irrfan Khan, Rajkummar Rao, Vidya Balan, Neha Dhupia & Dangal win big!|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/star-screen-awards-2017-full-winners-list-irrfan-khan-rajkummar-rao-vidya-balan-neha-dhupia-751790|work=International Business Times|accessdate=3 December 2017|date=3 December 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171205042010/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/star-screen-awards-2017-full-winners-list-irrfan-khan-rajkummar-rao-vidya-balan-neha-dhupia-751790|archivedate=5 December 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"ff18\">{{cite news|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/63rd-jio-filmfare-awards-2018-vidya-balan-wins-the-best-actor-in-a-leading-role-female-award/articleshow/62586291.cms|title=63rd Jio Filmfare Awards 2018: Vidya Balan wins the Best Actor In A Leading Role (Female) award|work=The Times of India|access-date=21 January 2018|date=21 January 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180121061556/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/63rd-jio-filmfare-awards-2018-vidya-balan-wins-the-best-actor-in-a-leading-role-female-award/articleshow/62586291.cms|archivedate=21 January 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Professional expansion (2019\u2013present)===\n[[File:Vidya Balan promoting Mission Mangal.jpg|thumb|upright=0.9|Vidya promoting ''[[Mission Mangal]]'' in 2019]]\nFollowing a year-long absence, Vidya returned to the screen in 2019 to play Basavatarakam, the first wife of actor, filmmaker and politician [[N. T. Rama Rao]] (played by [[Nandamuri Balakrishna]]) in a two-part Telugu-language biopic directed by [[Krish (director)|Krish]], titled ''[[N.T.R: Kathanayakudu]]'' and ''[[N.T.R: Mahanayakudu]]''.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/release-date-of-ntr-mahanayakudu-confirmed/articleshow/67160842.cms|title=Release date of NTR Mahanayakudu confirmed|date=19 December 2018|work=The Times of India|access-date=4 January 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190109010520/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/release-date-of-ntr-mahanayakudu-confirmed/articleshow/67160842.cms|archive-date=9 January 2019|url-status=live}}\n</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/ntr-biopic-starring-nandamuri-balakrishna-vidya-balan-rana-daggubati-to-release-on-9-january-2019-5316621.html|title=NTR biopic, starring Nandamuri Balakrishna, Vidya Balan, Rana Daggubati, to release on 9 January, 2019|date=4 October 2018|work=Firstpost|access-date=11 October 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181011174427/https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/ntr-biopic-starring-nandamuri-balakrishna-vidya-balan-rana-daggubati-to-release-on-9-january-2019-5316621.html|archive-date=11 October 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> Sangeetha Devi Dundoo of ''The Hindu'' found Vidya to be a \"treat to watch\", adding that \"her quietude and eyes [...] speak a thousand words contrasting NTR\u2019s histrionics\".<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/ntr-kathanayakudu-on-a-reverential-tone/article25949259.ece|title='NTR Kathanayakudu' review: On a reverential tone|date=9 January 2019|work=The Hindu|access-date=20 January 2019}}</ref> Writing for ''Firstpost'', Hemanth Kumar opined that \"there's something soothing about her mere presence that makes you want to respect her instantly\".<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/ntr-kathanayakudu-movie-review-balakrishnas-performance-stands-out-in-this-tribute-to-an-icon-5863661.html|title=NTR Kathanayakudu movie review: Balakrishna\u2019s performance stands out in this tribute to an icon|first=Hemanth|last=Kumar|work=Firstpost|date=9 January 2019|accessdate=19 January 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190120044625/https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/ntr-kathanayakudu-movie-review-balakrishnas-performance-stands-out-in-this-tribute-to-an-icon-5863661.html|archive-date=20 January 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Both films failed to perform well commercially.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ibtimes.co.in/ntr-kathanayakudu-box-office-collection-day-9-biopic-turns-first-big-disaster-2019-790314|title=NTR: Kathanayakudu box office collection day 9 - Biopic turns first big disaster of 2019|work=International Business Times|first=Shekhar|last=H Hooli|accessdate=19 January 2019|date=19 January 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190120043052/https://www.ibtimes.co.in/ntr-kathanayakudu-box-office-collection-day-9-biopic-turns-first-big-disaster-2019-790314|archive-date=20 January 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ibtimes.co.in/ntr-mahanayakudu-box-office-collection-it-biggest-failure-nandamuri-balakrishnas-career-792733|title=NTR: Mahanayakudu box office collection: It is the biggest failure of Nandamuri Balakrishna's career|first=Shekhar H.|last=Hooli|date=27 February 2019|work=International Business Times|accessdate=5 March 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190227123847/https://www.ibtimes.co.in/ntr-mahanayakudu-box-office-collection-it-biggest-failure-nandamuri-balakrishnas-career-792733|archive-date=27 February 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> In the same year, Vidya had her first Tamil film release in ''[[Nerkonda Paarvai]]'', a remake of the courtroom drama ''[[Pink (2016 film)|Pink]]'' (2016), in which she briefly played the wife of [[Ajith Kumar]]'s character.<ref>{{cite news|last=KBR|first=Upala|url=https://www.mid-day.com/articles/boney-kapoor-vidyas-role-is-a-powerful-one-in-pink-remake/403841|title=Boney Kapoor: Vidya's Role Is A Powerful One In Pink Remake|date=4 January 2019|work=Mid Day|access-date=4 January 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190104161213/https://www.mid-day.com/articles/boney-kapoor-vidyas-role-is-a-powerful-one-in-pink-remake/403841|archive-date=4 January 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Although not keen on remakes, she agreed to the project to bring attention to [[sexual consent]] to a different audience.<ref>{{cite news|last=S|first=Srivatsan|url=https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/vidya-balan-on-working-with-thala-ajith-in-nerkonda-paarvai/article28684451.ece|title=I was floored by Ajith\u2019s personality, says Vidya Balan on working in 'Nerkonda Paarvai'|date=23 July 2019|work=The Hindu|access-date=6 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190724113611/https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/vidya-balan-on-working-with-thala-ajith-in-nerkonda-paarvai/article28684451.ece|archive-date=24 July 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Srinivasa Ramanujam of ''The Hindu'' liked the film but thought that the portions involving Vidya \"doesn\u2019t quite sit with the narrative\".<ref>{{cite news|last=Ramanujam|first=Srinivasa|url=https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/reviews/nerkonda-paarvai-review-ajith-aces-this-courtroom-drama-which-reiterates-the-meaning-of-consent/article28833914.ece|title='Nerkonda Paarvai' movie review: Ajith aces this courtroom drama which reiterates the meaning of consent|date=6 August 2019|work=The Hindu|access-date=6 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190807132940/https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/reviews/nerkonda-paarvai-review-ajith-aces-this-courtroom-drama-which-reiterates-the-meaning-of-consent/article28833914.ece|archive-date=7 August 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> It emerged as one of the highest-grossing Tamil films of the year.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/bigil-petta-viswasam-kanchana-3-nerkonda-paarvai-kaithi-power-kollywoods-theatrical-takings-in-2019-to-rs-1000-cr-7736851.html|title=Bigil, Petta, Viswasam, Kanchana 3, Nerkonda Paarvai, Kaithi power Kollywood's theatrical takings in 2019 to Rs 1000 cr|work=Firstpost|date=4 December 2019 |accessdate=27 December 2019}}</ref>\n\nLater in 2019, Vidya starred alongside an ensemble cast, including Akshay Kumar and [[Taapsee Pannu]], in ''[[Mission Mangal]]'', a retelling of the [[Mars Orbiter Mission]] (which marked India's first interplanetary expedition).<ref>{{cite news|title=Akshay Kumar\u2019s Mission Mangal will star Vidya Balan, Taapsee Pannu, Nithya Menen, Sonakshi Sinha|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/akshay-kumar-signs-three-new-projects-to-start-shooting-for-mission-mangal-this-month/story-SJRWDHneqcNvDEBRBgHXMO.html|work=Hindustan Times|accessdate=5 November 2018|date=5 November 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181105061942/https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/akshay-kumar-signs-three-new-projects-to-start-shooting-for-mission-mangal-this-month/story-SJRWDHneqcNvDEBRBgHXMO.html|archive-date=5 November 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> She liked the idea of playing Tara Shinde, a seemingly ordinary homemaker who balances her family life with her work as a scientist.<ref>{{cite news|title=Mission Mangal actor Vidya Balan: Tara Shinde is not a superwoman|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/vidya-balan-mission-mangal-playing-tara-shinde-mars-orbiter-akshay-kumar-5905272/|work=The Indian Express|accessdate=15 August 2019|date=15 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190815060049/https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/vidya-balan-mission-mangal-playing-tara-shinde-mars-orbiter-akshay-kumar-5905272/|archive-date=15 August 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> She was also pleased to work with four other leading ladies, which she believed was rare in Hindi films.<ref>{{cite news|title=Vidya Balan gears up for Mission Mangal|url=https://www.telegraphindia.com/entertainment/vidya-balan-gears-up-for-mission-mangal/cid/1697859|work=The Telegraph|accessdate=15 August 2019|date=14 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190814195653/https://www.telegraphindia.com/entertainment/vidya-balan-gears-up-for-mission-mangal/cid/1697859|archive-date=14 August 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Joe Leydon]] of ''Variety'' found Vidya to be \"drop-dead perfect from wire to wire\" and Nandini Ramnath of [[Scroll.in]] wrote that she \"perfectly conveys Tara\u2019s optimism and dedication, and hers is the only female character who has agency in this space agency saga\".<ref>{{cite news|title=Film Review: \u2018Mission Mangal\u2019|url=https://variety.com/2019/film/reviews/mission-mangal-review-1203304480/|work=Variety|accessdate=16 August 2019|date=15 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190816082957/https://variety.com/2019/film/reviews/mission-mangal-review-1203304480/|archive-date=16 August 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=\u2018Mission Mangal\u2019 movie review: A space opera with a little bit of science|url=https://scroll.in/reel/933953/mission-mangal-movie-review-a-space-opera-with-a-little-bit-of-science|website=[[Scroll.in]]|accessdate=15 August 2019|date=15 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190815043836/https://scroll.in/reel/933953/mission-mangal-movie-review-a-space-opera-with-a-little-bit-of-science|archive-date=15 August 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> She received another Best Actress nomination at Filmfare.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.filmfare.com/awards/filmfare-awards-2020/nominations|title=Nominations for Filmfare Awards 2020|work=Filmfare|accessdate=3 February 2020}}</ref> With global earnings of {{INRConvert|2.9|b}}, ''Mission Mangal'' emerged as her highest-grossing release.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bollywoodhungama.com/box-office-collections/worldwide/all-time/page/2/|title=Bollywood Top Grossers Worldwide|website=Bollywood Hungama|access-date=10 September 2019}}</ref>\n\nVidya will next star in a short film about gender equality, entitled ''Natkhat'', which will also mark her first production venture.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/mail-today/story/reaching-for-the-sky-and-beyond-1581371-2019-08-16|title=Reaching for the sky and beyond|date=16 August 2019|work=India Today|access-date=16 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190816095936/https://www.indiatoday.in/mail-today/story/reaching-for-the-sky-and-beyond-1581371-2019-08-16|archive-date=16 August 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> She will then portray the [[mental calculator]] [[Shakuntala Devi]] in an [[Shakuntala Devi (film)|eponymous biopic]] and star in [[Amit V. Masurkar]]'s ''Sherni''.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/vidya-balan-to-play-math-genius-shakuntala-devi-says-i-am-extremely-excited-to-play-the-human-computer/story-13uBrYF18ONi5bbEjnwv4L.html|title=Vidya Balan is all set to play Shakuntala Devi on-screen|date=8 May 2019|work=Hindustan Times|access-date=8 May 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190508084631/https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/vidya-balan-to-play-math-genius-shakuntala-devi-says-i-am-extremely-excited-to-play-the-human-computer/story-13uBrYF18ONi5bbEjnwv4L.html|archive-date=8 May 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.mid-day.com/articles/after-shakuntala-devi-vidya-balan-is-all-set-to-turn-into-a-sherni/22600186|title=After Shakuntala Devi, Vidya Balan Is All Set To Turn Into A Sherni!|date=13 February 2020|work=Mid Day|access-date=13 February 2020}}</ref> Vidya has also committed to produce and star as [[Indira Gandhi]] in a yet-untitled web series based on [[Sagarika Ghose]]'s biography ''Indira \u2013 India's Most Powerful Prime Minister''.<ref>{{cite news|last=Iyer|first=Sanyukta|title=Vidya Balan: I always wanted to play Indira Gandhi|url=https://mumbaimirror.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/vidya-balan-i-always-wanted-to-play-indira-gandhi/articleshow/62449906.cms|work=Mumbai Mirror|accessdate=11 January 2018|date=11 January 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180111003923/https://mumbaimirror.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/vidya-balan-i-always-wanted-to-play-indira-gandhi/articleshow/62449906.cms|archivedate=11 January 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Revealed: Vidya Balan starrer Indira Gandhi biopic to now be a web-series|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/bollywood/revealed-vidya-balan-starrer-indira-gandhi-biopic-now-web-series/|publisher=Bollywood Hungama|accessdate=13 August 2018|date=11 August 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180813111137/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/bollywood/revealed-vidya-balan-starrer-indira-gandhi-biopic-now-web-series/|archive-date=13 August 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life and off-screen work==\n[[File:Vidya Siddharth cropped.jpg|thumb|left|upright=1.2|alt=Vidya Balan and Siddharth Roy Kapur are smiling at the camera.|Vidya and [[Siddharth Roy Kapur]] at their wedding ceremony in December 2012]]\nThe mass media has often speculated about a romantic relationship between Vidya and her co-actors, but she has strongly denied these reports.<ref>{{cite news |work=India Today |url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/Poor+Vidya+pays+price+of+link-ups+with+stars/1/98590.html |date=24 May 2010 |accessdate=7 October 2012 |title=Poor Vidya pays price of link-ups with stars |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141210095710/http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/Poor+Vidya+pays+price+of+link-ups+with+stars/1/98590.html |archivedate=10 December 2014 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Vidya happy she's not linked to Arshad|url=https://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P3-1591274061.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180903115025/https://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P3-1591274061.html|url-status=dead|archive-date=3 September 2018|work=Hindustan Times {{Subscription required|via=[[HighBeam Research]]}}|accessdate=23 September 2012|date=8 November 2008}}</ref> In 2009, Vidya was involved in a controversy when she mentioned a previous relationship in which \"caustic remarks\" were made at her due to her weight. She said, \"If someone who matters to you takes you down, it can break you. That someone whose approval mattered to me started to constantly find faults with me. At that point of time, it was important to walk away from that relationship.\"<ref>{{cite news |last=Lalwani |first=Vickey |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2009-11-14/news-interviews/28068480_1_weight-loss-paa-and-ishqiya-vidya-balan |title=Vidya opens up on Shahid |work=The Times of India |accessdate=11 May 2012 |date=14 November 2009 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131201075704/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2009-11-14/news-interviews/28068480_1_weight-loss-paa-and-ishqiya-vidya-balan |archivedate=1 December 2013 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref> Though she refused to name the person, [[tabloid (newspaper format)|tabloid]] reports suggested that she was referring to Shahid Kapoor (her co-star in ''Kismat Konnection'').<ref>\n{{cite web |last=Mahadevan |first=Sneha |title=W(eig)ht so funny?! |url=http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P3-2467778891.html |work=Daily News and Analysis {{Subscription required|via=[[HighBeam Research]]}} |accessdate=17 October 2012 |date=25 September 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140610083450/http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P3-2467778891.html |archivedate=10 June 2014  }}\n</ref> Kapoor, however, denied the allegations.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/brunch/shahid-kapoor-uncut/story-gpwx8WtTq85Hx8o8UB0etN.html |title=Shahid Kapoor, uncut |work=Hindustan Times |accessdate=11 May 2012 |date=22 June 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160203124326/http://www.hindustantimes.com/brunch/shahid-kapoor-uncut/story-gpwx8WtTq85Hx8o8UB0etN.html |archivedate= 3 February 2016 |df= }}</ref> During an interview in May 2012, Vidya announced that she was dating [[Siddharth Roy Kapur]], the CEO of [[UTV Motion Pictures]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/i-am-dating-siddharth-roy-kapoor-vidya-balan/256908-8-66.html |title=I am dating Siddharth Roy Kapoor: Vidya Balan |publisher=CNN-IBN |accessdate=11 May 2012 |date=11 May 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120512215215/http://ibnlive.in.com/news/i-am-dating-siddharth-roy-kapoor-vidya-balan/256908-8-66.html |archivedate=12 May 2012 |df= }}</ref> On 14 December 2012, the couple were married in a private ceremony in [[Bandra]], Mumbai.<ref>{{cite web|last=Prashar |first=Chandni |url=http://movies.ndtv.com/bollywood/vidya-balan-is-now-mrs-siddharth-roy-kapur-630432 |title=Vidya Balan is now Mrs. Siddharth Roy Kapur |publisher=NDTV |date=14 December 2012 |accessdate=14 December 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150103061313/http://movies.ndtv.com/bollywood/vidya-balan-is-now-mrs-siddharth-roy-kapur-630432 |archivedate= 3 January 2015 |df= }}</ref>\n\nVidya is trained in [[Carnatic music]] and briefly studied the dance forms of [[Bharatnatyam]] and [[Kathak]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report_the-right-man-hasn-t-come-along-yet-vidya-balan_1089724 |title=The right man hasn't come along yet: Vidya Balan|work=Daily News and Analysis|accessdate=24 September 2012|date=9 April 2007}}</ref> Regarding her religious affiliations, Vidya said, \"I am a person with a lot of faith and I have conversations [with God] all the time but I am not so religious in the conventional, organised sense\".<ref name=\"rules\"/> She practices vegetarianism and was listed as \"India's hottest vegetarian\" in polls conducted by [[PETA]] in 2011 and 2012.<ref>{{cite news |last=Vyavahare |first=Renuka |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-01-18/news-interviews/28366462_1_vegetarian-diet-vidya-balan-top-contender |title=Vidya's India's hottest vegetarian |work=The Times of India |accessdate=24 September 2012 |date=18 January 2011 |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20130104145534/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-01-18/news-interviews/28366462_1_vegetarian-diet-vidya-balan-top-contender |archivedate=4 January 2013 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref><ref>\n\"[http://www.indianexpress.com/news/amitabh-bachchan-vidya-balan-named-petas-hottest-vegetarian-celebrities/1053913 Amitabh Bachchan, Vidya Balan named PETA's hottest vegetarian celebrities] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130107072048/http://www.indianexpress.com/news/amitabh-bachchan-vidya-balan-named-petas-hottest-vegetarian-celebrities/1053913/ |date=7 January 2013 }} ,\" ''The Indian Express'', 3 January 2013.\n</ref> Her weight fluctuations over the years have been the subject of substantial media coverage in India.<ref>{{cite news |last=Baliga |first=Shashi |url=http://www.thehindu.com/arts/magazine/article3006462.ece |title=It was liberating to be Silk |work=The Hindu |accessdate=17 October 2012 |date=17 March 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120720210700/http://www.thehindu.com/arts/magazine/article3006462.ece |archivedate=20 July 2012  }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Vyavahare |first=Renuka |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-05-31/news-interviews/31920503_1_vidya-balan-marathi-films-curves |title=Why should women look like men: Vidya Balan |work=The Times of India |accessdate=17 October 2012 |date=31 May 2012 |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20130103172251/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-05-31/news-interviews/31920503_1_vidya-balan-marathi-films-curves |archivedate=3 January 2013 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://movies.ndtv.com/bollywood/fat-so-vidya-is-living-large-loving-it-625536 |title=Fat, so? Vidya is living large & loving it |publisher=NDTV |accessdate=18 October 2012 |date=5 June 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150103061150/http://movies.ndtv.com/bollywood/fat-so-vidya-is-living-large-loving-it-625536 |archivedate= 3 January 2015 |df= }}</ref>\n\nBesides acting in film, Vidya promotes humanitarian causes and supports charitable institutions. In March 2011, she endorsed [[World Wildlife Fund]]'s [[Earth Hour]] campaign in India.<ref>{{cite news |last=Wadhwa |first=Akash |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-03-17/news-interviews/28699077_1_earth-hour-vidya-balan-wwf |title=Vidya Balan to promote Earth Hour |work=The Times of India |accessdate=24 September 2012 |date=17 March 2011 |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20130103134342/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-03-17/news-interviews/28699077_1_earth-hour-vidya-balan-wwf |archivedate=3 January 2013 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref> She campaigned for the cause of nutrition in India for [[Child In Need Institute]] (CINI), a non-profit organisation based in Kolkata.<ref>{{cite news|last=Chatterjee |first=Chandreyee |url=http://www.telegraphindia.com/1120529/jsp/calcutta/story_15541666.jsp#.UF_9r40gejs |title=Canvas to canvass for nutrition cause |work=The Telegraph |accessdate=24 September 2012 |date=29 May 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131212163401/http://www.telegraphindia.com/1120529/jsp/calcutta/story_15541666.jsp |archivedate=12 December 2013 |df= }}</ref> In September 2012, Vidya visited a village in [[Mirzapur]], Uttar Pradesh, where she participated in a campaign to promote children's education and the empowerment of women.<ref>{{cite news|last=Udasi |first=Harshikaa |url=http://www.thehindu.com/arts/cinema/article3877583.ece |title=Doing her bit for society |work=The Hindu |accessdate=24 September 2012 |date=9 September 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120927003259/http://www.thehindu.com/arts/cinema/article3877583.ece |archivedate=27 September 2012 |df= }}</ref> For her attempts to empower women, Vidya was awarded The [[Prabha Khaitan]] Puraskar 2012 by the Calcutta Chamber of Commerce; she was the youngest recipient of the award.<ref>\n{{cite web |title=Vidya Balan bags another award, but not for a film! |url=http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P3-2675120141.html |work=Daily News and Analysis {{Subscription required|via=[[HighBeam Research]]}} |accessdate=24 September 2012 |date=1 June 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140610075855/http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P3-2675120141.html |archivedate=10 June 2014  }}\n</ref> In August 2013, she served as the grand marshal of the [[Independence Day (India)|India Day parade]] held in New York City.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/news-by-industry/et-cetera/anna-hazare-vidya-balan-lead-biggest-india-day-parade-in-united-states/articleshow/21910154.cms |title=Anna Hazare, Vidya Balan lead biggest India Day parade in United States |work=The Economic Times |accessdate=19 August 2013 |date=19 August 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150331145029/http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/news-by-industry/et-cetera/anna-hazare-vidya-balan-lead-biggest-india-day-parade-in-united-states/articleshow/21910154.cms |archivedate=31 March 2015 |df= }}</ref> In September that year, she launched a technology-based learning platform for underprivileged children in the Thanapur village of Uttar Pradesh.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://zeenews.india.com/entertainment/and-more/vidya-balan-launches-tech-based-learning-system_143258.html |title=Vidya Balan launches tech-based learning system |publisher=Zee News |accessdate=23 September 2013 |date=23 September 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130926174736/http://zeenews.india.com/entertainment/and-more/vidya-balan-launches-tech-based-learning-system_143258.html |archivedate=26 September 2013 |df= }}</ref> On the occasion of [[International Women's Day]] in 2015, Vidya wrote an opinion column in ''Hindustan Times'' on the issues faced by women in India.<ref>{{cite news|last=Balan |first=Vidya |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/vidya-balan-s-column-happy-women-s-day-or-is-it/article1-1324035.aspx |title=HT Exclusive: Happy women\u2019s day, or is it? Vidya Balan writes |work=Hindustan Times |accessdate=8 March 2015 |date=9 March 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150308095506/http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/vidya-balan-s-column-happy-women-s-day-or-is-it/article1-1324035.aspx |archivedate= 8 March 2015 |df= }}</ref> In August 2017, Vidya was made a member of the Indian [[Central Board of Film Certification]], to certify films for theatrical exhibition.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/bollywood/pahlaj-nihalani-gets-sacked-vidya-balan-joins-cbfc-headed-prasoon-joshi/ |title=After Pahlaj Nihalani gets sacked, Vidya Balan joins CBFC headed by Prasoon Joshi |publisher=Bollywood Hungama |accessdate=12 August 2017 |date=12 August 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170812143113/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/bollywood/pahlaj-nihalani-gets-sacked-vidya-balan-joins-cbfc-headed-prasoon-joshi/ |archivedate=12 August 2017  }}</ref> The following year, she became the goodwill ambassador of Arpan, an NGO that creates awareness on sexual abuse.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.mid-day.com/articles/vidya-balans-taking-her-own-sweet-time/19570163 |title=Vidya Balan's Taking Her Own Sweet Time! |work=Mid Day |accessdate=3 July 2018 |date=3 July 2018 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180703094908/https://www.mid-day.com/articles/vidya-balans-taking-her-own-sweet-time/19570163 |archivedate=3 July 2018}}</ref> In 2019, she collaborated with [[BIG FM 92.7]] to host a radio show named \"Dhun Badal Ke Toh Dekho\".<ref>{{cite news |last1=Vashisht |first1=Radhika |last2=Young |first2=Sean Colin |url=https://www.deccanchronicle.com/entertainment/bollywood/020319/celebrities-go-on-air.html |title=Celebrities go on air |work=Deccan Chronicle |accessdate=8 May 2019 |date=2 March 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190508094749/https://www.deccanchronicle.com/entertainment/bollywood/020319/celebrities-go-on-air.html |archive-date=8 May 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n==Media image and artistry==\nFollowing the success of ''Parineeta'' and ''Lage Raho Munna Bhai'', Vidya's film roles were subject to wide critical analysis.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.tribuneindia.com/2011/20110410/spectrum/main9.htm|title=The uniqueness of being Vidya|work=The Tribune|accessdate=17 October 2012|date=10 April 2011|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131121110907/http://www.tribuneindia.com/2011/20110410/spectrum/main9.htm|archivedate=21 November 2013 }}</ref> [[Vir Sanghvi]] noted that the films ''Heyy Babyy'' and ''Kismat Konnection'' were \"strange films [...] in which she tried to pretend to be what she is not&nbsp;\u2014 a Bollywood bimbette.\"<ref name=\"rules\"/> Vidya described that particular phase in her career as a \"struggle to be someone else\".<ref>{{cite news|last=Bhupta|first=Malini|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/its-a-constant-struggle-to-be-someone-else-vidya-67234-2010-02-12|title=It's a constant struggle to be someone else: Vidya|work=India Today|date=12 February 2010|accessdate=23 September 2012|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180218090211/https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/its-a-constant-struggle-to-be-someone-else-vidya-67234-2010-02-12|archivedate=18 February 2018}}</ref> Due to the criticism that her film choices evoked, Vidya decided to choose roles that she \"believed in\" rather than choose by convention.<ref name=\"men\">\n{{cite news |title=Why men love Vidya Balan |url=http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1G1-246310012.html |work=Hindustan Times {{Subscription required|via=[[HighBeam Research]]}} |accessdate=23 September 2012 |date=12 January 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131105233010/http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1G1-246310012.html |archivedate=5 November 2013  }}\n</ref> Members of the media have subsequently labelled her as \"bold\" and \"daring\" in her choices.<ref name=\"list\">{{cite web|last=Sen |first=Raja |title=Bollywood's best actresses of 2011 |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-bollywoods-best-actresses-of-the-year-yearend-2011/20111230.htm |publisher=Rediff |accessdate=23 September 2012 |date=30 December 2011 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120905162613/http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-bollywoods-best-actresses-of-the-year-yearend-2011/20111230.htm |archivedate= 5 September 2012 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Vidya Balan: Hindi cinema's new bold |url=http://www.indianexpress.com/news/vidya-balan-hindi-cinemas-new-bold/890115/0 |work=The Indian Express |accessdate=23 September 2012 |date=21 December 2011 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121204024459/http://www.indianexpress.com/news/vidya-balan-hindi-cinemas-new-bold/890115/0 |archivedate= 4 December 2012 |df= }}</ref>\n[[File:Vidya at GQ (cropped).jpg|thumb|upright=0.9|Vidya at the GQ Men of the Year Awards, 2013]]\nHer starring roles in ''Heyy Babyy'' and ''Kismat Konnection'' also led to considerable attention in the media for her \"questionable wardrobe\". Several publications listed her as the \"worst dressed actress\" and her costume designers attributed her failure to carry off western clothes due to her weight and body structure.<ref>{{cite news |last=Wadhwa |first=Akash |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2008-09-14/news-interviews/27891870_1_vidya-balan-parineeta-kismat-konnection |title=Look, it does matter! |work=The Times of India |accessdate=17 October 2012 |date=14 September 2008 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131023060456/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2008-09-14/news-interviews/27891870_1_vidya-balan-parineeta-kismat-konnection |archivedate=23 October 2013 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|publisher=Rediff |title=The worst dressed actresses of 2007 |date=4 December 2007 |url=http://specials.rediff.com/yearend/2007/dec/04yractress1.htm |accessdate=23 September 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121113155053/http://specials.rediff.com/yearend/2007/dec/04yractress1.htm |archivedate=13 November 2012 |df= }}</ref><ref>\n{{cite news |title=What was she thinking? |url=http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P3-1495143311.html |work=Hindustan Times {{Subscription required|via=[[HighBeam Research]]}} |accessdate=23 September 2012 |date=15 June 2008 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131105232949/http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P3-1495143311.html |archivedate=5 November 2013  }}\n</ref> She was later praised in the media for wearing [[sari]]s at public events; designer [[Niharika Khan]] explained, \"Vidya's beauty lies in her curves. She's comfortable in her voluptuousness, and therefore in a sari.\"<ref>{{cite news |last=Walia |first=Nona |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-04-26/designers/31144727_1_vidya-balan-sari-heyy-babyy |title=Is Vidya Balan trapped in a sari? |work=The Times of India |accessdate=23 September 2012 |date=26 April 2012 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131023061508/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-04-26/designers/31144727_1_vidya-balan-sari-heyy-babyy |archivedate=23 October 2013 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref> Vidya has since been identified as defying \"an anglicised idea of sexuality\" and embody the idea of \"raw Indian sexuality\".<ref name=\"men\"/>\n\nAfter portraying strong protagonists in ''Paa'', ''Ishqiya'', ''No One Killed Jessica'', ''The Dirty Picture'' and ''Kahaani'', Vidya was credited in the media for pioneering a movement that breaks the stereotypical portrayal of heroines in Bollywood.<ref>{{cite news|last=Chatterjee|first=Saibal|title=Power actors: Marking a clear shift in gender dynamics, Bollywood embraces films spearheaded by female protagonists|url=http://www.tribuneindia.com/2014/20140323/spectrum/enter1.htm|date=23 March 2014|accessdate=2 June 2014|work=The Tribune|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131121110907/http://www.tribuneindia.com/2014/20140323/spectrum/enter1.htm|archivedate=21 November 2013 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Dubey |first=Bharati |title=Gals, guts and glory: Women power reaches another high in Bollywood |url=http://www.mid-day.com/articles/gals-guts-and-glory-women-power-reaches-another-high-in-bollywood/15445182 |date=14 July 2014 |accessdate=15 July 2014 |work=Mid Day |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140716145949/http://www.mid-day.com/articles/gals-guts-and-glory-women-power-reaches-another-high-in-bollywood/15445182 |archivedate=16 July 2014 |df= }}</ref> The major commercial success of the latter two earned her the title of a \"female hero\"<ref name=\"Hero\">{{cite web|last1=N |first1=Patcy |last2=Dedhia |first2=Sonil |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-vidya-i-did-not-believe-that-i-could-be-so-sexy/20120228.htm |title=Vidya Balan: I didn't believe I could be so sexy |publisher=Rediff |accessdate=17 October 2012 |date=28 February 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121010150153/http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-vidya-i-did-not-believe-that-i-could-be-so-sexy/20120228.htm |archivedate=10 October 2012 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Naval-Shetye |first=Aakanksha |url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report_im-happy-being-called-a-heroine-vidya-balan_1623410 |title=I'm happy being called a heroine: Vidya Balan |work=Daily News and Analysis |accessdate=17 October 2012 |date=9 December 2011 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120110111053/http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report_im-happy-being-called-a-heroine-vidya-balan_1623410 |archivedate=10 January 2012 |df= }}</ref> and Kalpana Nair of ''[[Firstpost]]'' noted that with these two films Vidya spearheaded a change in the roles that were offered to actresses over 30.<ref>{{cite news|last=Nair |first=Kalpana |url=http://www.firstpost.com/blogs/thirty-and-fabulous-how-priyanka-vidya-and-kareena-redefined-aging-469433.html |title=Thirty and fabulous: How Priyanka, Vidya and Kareena redefined aging |work=[[Firstpost]] |accessdate=26 September 2012 |date=6 January 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120927224952/http://www.firstpost.com/blogs/thirty-and-fabulous-how-priyanka-vidya-and-kareena-redefined-aging-469433.html |archivedate=27 September 2012 |df= }}</ref> Critic [[Mayank Shekhar]] predicted, \"Just a few smart male actors can completely change the face of a commercial, star-driven film industry. Looking at [...] Vidya Balan [...] it appears, that change could well originate from the leading lady instead.\"<ref>\n{{cite news|last=Shekar|first=Mayank|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/movie-reviews/mayank-shekhar-s-review-the-dirty-picture/story-Y5u9LlV44FytJcLwBDQNmI.html|title=Mayank Shekhar's review: The Dirty Picture|work=Hindustan Times|accessdate=23 September 2012|date=2 December 2011|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171031113932/http://www.hindustantimes.com/movie-reviews/mayank-shekhar-s-review-the-dirty-picture/story-Y5u9LlV44FytJcLwBDQNmI.html|archive-date=31 October 2017|url-status=live}}\n</ref>\n\n''[[India Today]]'' featured Vidya in their 2012 listing of the nation's most powerful women and noted that \"she has toppled the all dominating hero, reducing him to a supporting role in a male dominated film industry\".<ref>{{cite news |url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/25-most-influential-women-vidya-balan-kareena-kapoor/1/177016.html |title=25 power women and their inspiring stories |work=India Today |accessdate=23 September 2012 |date=9 March 2012 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121101105921/http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/25-most-influential-women-vidya-balan-kareena-kapoor/1/177016.html |archivedate=1 November 2012 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref> Vidya was featured by ''[[Forbes India]]'' in their annual [[Forbes Celebrity 100|Celebrity 100]] list in 2012 and 2013.<ref>\n{{cite news |title=Vidya Balan |url=http://www.forbesindia.com/celebprofile/vidya-balan/1439/70 |work=[[Forbes]] |accessdate=8 July 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180707182620/http://www.forbesindia.com/celebprofile/vidya-balan/1439/70 |archive-date=7 July 2018 |url-status=live  }}\n</ref> She occupied the top slot in Rediff.com's annual listing of the year's best performances for two consecutive years (2010\u201311).<ref name=\"list\"/><ref>{{cite web|publisher=Rediff.com |title=Bollywood's best actresses, 2010 |date=31 December 2010 |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-bollywoods-best-ctresses-2010/20101231.htm |accessdate=23 September 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121025113233/http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-bollywoods-best-ctresses-2010/20101231.htm |archivedate=25 October 2012 |df= }}</ref> She also featured in the list for the years 2005, 2006, 2009, 2012, and 2016.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Rediff |title=Bollywood's best actresses, 2005 |date=23 December 2005 |url=http://specials.rediff.com/yearend/2005/dec/23yend9.htm |accessdate=23 September 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120922040641/http://specials.rediff.com/yearend/2005/dec/23yend9.htm |archivedate=22 September 2012 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|publisher=Rediff.com |title=Bollywood's top actresses, 2006 |date=25 August 2006 |url=http://specials.rediff.com/movies/2006/aug/25sd4.htm |accessdate=23 September 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131023055747/http://specials.rediff.com/movies/2006/aug/25sd4.htm |archivedate=23 October 2013 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|publisher=Rediff.com |title=Bollywood's best actresses, 2009 |date=31 December 2009 |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-best-actresses-of-2009/20091231.htm |accessdate=23 September 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130508212615/http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-best-actresses-of-2009/20091231.htm |archivedate= 8 May 2013 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|publisher=Rediff.com |title=Bollywood's best actresses, 2012 |date=21 December 2012 |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-yearend-special-bollywood-s-top-ten-actresses-of-2012/20121221.htm#8 |accessdate=29 March 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130127161020/http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-yearend-special-bollywood-s-top-ten-actresses-of-2012/20121221.htm |archivedate=27 January 2013 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Sen |first=Raja |publisher=Rediff.com |title=10 performances 2016 should be proud of! |date=30 December 2016 |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/special/10-performances-2016-should-be-proud-of/20161230.htm |accessdate=8 July 2018 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171112051113/http://www.rediff.com/movies/special/10-performances-2016-should-be-proud-of/20161230.htm |archivedate=12 November 2017  }}</ref> In 2012, the magazine ''[[Verve (Indian magazine)|Verve]]'' featured her as one of India's \"Young Power Women\" and wrote, \"In a reel world peopled by [[size zero]]-toned bodies and pretty-as-a-picture heroines, Vidya comes across as completely real and natural&nbsp;\u2013 a woman who has followed her own instincts and dared to live her destiny by being her own person and not morphing herself to fit into any conventional slot.\"<ref name=\"quote1\">{{cite journal|url=http://www.verveonline.com/109/people/power-women.shtml |title=Young power women |author=Mehta, S., Jahagirdar-Saxena, S., Modak, N. & Sah, M. |journal=[[Verve (Indian magazine)|Verve]] |volume=20 |issue=6 |accessdate=23 September 2012 |date=June 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120619051144/http://www.verveonline.com/109/people/power-women.shtml |archivedate=19 June 2012 |df= }}</ref> Two years later, the magazine listed her as a power icon.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.vervemagazine.in/people/power-icon-vidya-balan|title=Power Icon: Vidya Balan|accessdate=24 June 2014|date=8 July 2018|work=Verve|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140707200526/http://www.vervemagazine.in/people/power-icon-vidya-balan|archivedate=7 July 2014}}</ref> In 2018, ''[[The Economic Times]]'' considered Vidya to be one of the most prominent celebrity brand ambassadors in India.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/magazines/panache/face-of-advertising-vidya-balan-has-signed-nine-new-brands-in-the-past-10-months/articleshow/64821513.cms |title=Face of advertising: Vidya Balan has signed nine new brands in the past 10 months |work=The Economic Times |accessdate=2 July 2018 |date=8 July 2018 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180708095740/https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/magazines/panache/face-of-advertising-vidya-balan-has-signed-nine-new-brands-in-the-past-10-months/articleshow/64821513.cms |archivedate=8 July 2018  }}</ref>\n\nIn 2014, Vidya was awarded the [[Padma Shri]], the fourth highest civilian award in India, for her contributions to the entertainment industry.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/india/report-vidya-balan-paresh-rawal-get-padma-shri-1957062|title=Vidya Balan, Paresh Rawal get Padma Shri|work=Daily News and Analysis|accessdate=26 January 2014|date=25 January 2014|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140127013116/http://www.dnaindia.com/india/report-vidya-balan-paresh-rawal-get-padma-shri-1957062|archivedate=27 January 2014|df=}}</ref> The following year, she received an honorary Doctor of Arts degree from [[Rai Foundation|Rai University]]; the university also named a scholarship program for underprivileged girls after her.<ref>{{cite news|last=Das |first=Anirban |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/vidya-balan-to-be-awarded-honorary-doctorate/article1-1353488.aspx |title=Vidya Balan to be awarded honorary doctorate |work=Hindustan Times |accessdate=2 June 2015 |date=1 June 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150601070642/http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/vidya-balan-to-be-awarded-honorary-doctorate/article1-1353488.aspx |archivedate= 1 June 2015 |df= }}</ref> The chancellor of the university, Harbeen Arora said, \"Among the league of iconic actors, Vidya is a pioneer in every way. Her films epitomise a distinct Indianness and a powerful womanhood\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibnlive.com/news/movies/vidya-balan-gets-honorary-doctorate-for-her-contribution-to-indian-cinema-1000191.html |title=Vidya Balan gets honorary doctorate for her contribution to Indian cinema |publisher=CNN-IBN |accessdate=2 June 2015 |date=25 June 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150709092619/http://www.ibnlive.com/news/movies/vidya-balan-gets-honorary-doctorate-for-her-contribution-to-indian-cinema-1000191.html |archivedate= 9 July 2015 |df= }}</ref>\n\n==Accolades==\n{{Main|List of awards and nominations received by Vidya Balan}}\nAmong Vidya's film awards are a [[National Film Award for Best Actress]] for ''The Dirty Picture'' (2011);<ref name=\"national\"/> and six Filmfare Awards: [[Filmfare Award for Best Female Debut|Best Female Debut]] for ''Parineeta'' (2005);<ref name=\"oldawards\"/> [[Filmfare Award for Best Actress|Best Actress]] for ''Paa'' (2009),<ref name=\"oldawards\"/> ''The Dirty Picture'' (2011),<ref name=\"awards\"/> ''Kahaani'' (2012),<ref name=\"ff12\"/> and ''Tumhari Sulu'' (2017);<ref name=\"ff18\"/> and [[Filmfare Critics Award for Best Actress|Critics Award for Best Actress]] for ''Ishqiya'' (2010).<ref name=\"awards\"/>\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of Indian film actresses]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==Further reading==\n{{refbegin}}\n* {{cite news|url=http://www.thehindubusinessline.com/features/life/article2697851.ece|title=Vidya gets dirty... and how!|author=Baliga, Shashi|date=2 December 2011|work=The Hindu|accessdate=8 January 2012|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120108052604/http://www.thehindubusinessline.com/features/life/article2697851.ece|archivedate=8 January 2012}}\n* {{cite news|url= http://www.telegraphindia.com/1111203/jsp/entertainment/story_14833153.jsp|title=Bombaat!|author=Roy, Priyanka|date=3 December 2011|work=The Telegraph|accessdate=11 January 2012}}\n* {{cite news|url=http://www.livemint.com/Leisure/JbeZ73wYywoE67Zg7X3oLI/Profile--Why-everybody-loves-Vidya.html|title=Why everybody loves Vidya|author=Janardhan, Arun|date=2 March 2012|work=Hindustan Times|accessdate=17 October 2012}}\n* {{cite web|url= http://www.filmfare.com/interviews/the-artist-365.html |title=The&nbsp;Artist|author=Singh, Raghuvendra|date=23 April 2012|work=Filmfare|accessdate=24 September 2012}}\n{{refend}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category}}\n\n* {{IMDb name|id=1799038}}\n\n{{Portal bar|Biography|Bollywood|Film}}\n\n{{Navboxes\n| title = Awards for Vidya Balan\n| list =\n{{NationalFilmAwardBestActress}}\n{{FilmfareAwardBestActress 2001-2020}}\n{{FilmfareCriticsAwardBestActress}}\n{{FilmfareAwardBestFemaleDebut}}\n{{IIFAAwardBestActress}}\n{{IIFAAwardBestFemaleDebut}}\n{{ProducersGuildFilmAwardBestActress}}\n{{ScreenAwardBestActress}}\n{{ScreenAwardBestFemaleDebut}}\n{{StardustAwardBestActress}}\n{{StardustAwardFemaleActor}}\n{{ZeeCineAwardBestActorFemale}}\n{{Zee Cine Award for Best Female Debut}}\n}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Balan, Vidya}}\n[[Category:1979 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:21st-century Indian actresses]]\n[[Category:Actresses in Bengali cinema]]\n[[Category:Actresses in Hindi cinema]]\n[[Category:Female models from Mumbai]]\n[[Category:Indian film actresses]]\n[[Category:Indian television actresses]]\n[[Category:Actresses in Malayalam cinema]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Mumbai]]\n[[Category:Best Actress National Film Award winners]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Palakkad]]\n[[Category:St. Xavier's College, Mumbai alumni]]\n[[Category:University of Mumbai alumni]]\n[[Category:Zee Cine Awards winners]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the Padma Shri in arts]]\n[[Category:Filmfare Awards winners]]\n", "name_user": "Not to mention", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vidya_Balan"}
{"title_page": "Kangana Ranaut, roles and awards", "text_new": "{{EngvarB|date=April 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2020}}\n[[File:Kangana Ranaut at 2019 Cannes (cropped).jpg|thumb|alt=Kangana Ranaut is smiling at the camera|Ranaut at the [[2019 Cannes Film Festival]]]]\n[[Kangana Ranaut]] (also credited as Kangna Ranaut) is an Indian actress who appears predominantly in [[Bollywood|Hindi films]]. She has received several awards, including the [[Padma Shri]], fourth highest civilian award in the [[Republic of India]], three [[National Film Awards]], four [[Filmfare Awards]], three [[International Indian Film Academy Awards]], and one award each from the [[Screen Awards|Screen]], [[Zee Cine Awards|Zee Cine]] and [[Producers Guild Film Awards|Producers Guild]] award ceremonies.\n\nRanaut made her acting debut in 2006 with a leading role in the thriller ''[[Gangster (2006 film)|Gangster]]'', for which she was awarded the [[Filmfare Award for Best Female Debut]], among other debut awards.<ref name=\"bio\">{{cite news|title=Kangana Ranaut |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/chunk-ht-ui-entertainmentsectionpage-celebrityintro/kangana-ranaut/article1-894273.aspx |accessdate=28 January 2015 |newspaper=[[Hindustan Times]] |date=23 July 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150205105648/http://www.hindustantimes.com/chunk-ht-ui-entertainmentsectionpage-celebrityintro/kangana-ranaut/article1-894273.aspx |archivedate= 5 February 2015 }}</ref> Her portrayals of a character based on actress [[Parveen Babi]] in  ''[[Woh Lamhe]]'' (2006) and a shrewd socialite in ''[[Life in a... Metro]]'' (2007) were lauded,<ref name=\"journey\">{{cite news|title=Kangana Ranaut's impressive Bollywood journey |url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/kangana-ranauts-impressive-bollywood-journey/1/321907.html |accessdate=9 March 2014 |work=[[India Today]] |date=6 November 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140309061446/http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/kangana-ranauts-impressive-bollywood-journey/1/321907.html |archivedate= 9 March 2014 }}</ref> with the latter earning her a [[Stardust Award for Breakthrough Performance \u2013 Female]].<ref name=\"bio\"/> Ranaut won numerous awards, including the [[National Film Award for Best Supporting Actress]] and a Filmfare Award [[Filmfare Award for Best Supporting Actress|in the same category]] for her role as a [[Substance dependence|substance abusing]] supermodel in the drama ''[[Fashion (2008 film)|Fashion]]'' (2008).<ref name=\"bio\"/><ref>{{cite web |url=http://iffi.nic.in/Dff2011/Frm56NFAAward.aspx?PdfName=56NFA.pdf |title=56th National Film Awards |publisher=[[Directorate of Film Festivals]] |accessdate=29 March 2014 |format=PDF |page=40 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130130000605/http://iffi.nic.in/Dff2011/Frm56NFAAward.aspx?PdfName=56NFA.pdf |archivedate=30 January 2013 }}</ref> Also in 2008, she featured as a village girl in ''[[Dhaam Dhoom]]'', her first Tamil film.<ref name=\"dhaam\">{{cite news |title=Last work of a talented director |url=http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1G1-188902335.html |work=[[Post (South Africa)|Post]] |url-access=subscription  |via=[[HighBeam Research]] |accessdate=20 March 2014 |date=12 November 2008 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140611094757/http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1G1-188902335.html |archivedate=11 June 2014  }}</ref>\n\nRanaut subsequently featured in several commercially successful films, including the supernatural thriller ''[[Raaz: The Mystery Continues]]'' (2009), the crime film ''[[Once Upon a Time in Mumbaai]]'' (2010), the romantic comedy ''[[Tanu Weds Manu]]'' (2011), and the comedy ''[[Double Dhamaal]]'' (2011).<ref name=\"box office\">{{cite web|title=Kangana Ranaut: Box Office Details and Filmography |url=http://boxofficeindia.com/Star_Cast/actor_detail/kangana_ranaut |publisher=[[Box Office India]] |accessdate=9 March 2014 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150918191957/http://www.boxofficeindia.com/Star_Cast/actor_detail/kangana_ranaut |archivedate=18 September 2015 |url-status=dead }}</ref> For her role in ''Tanu Weds Manu'', she received nominations for the [[Screen Award for Best Actress]] and the [[Zee Cine Award for Best Actor \u2013 Female]], among others.<ref name=\"screen\">{{cite web|title=Nominations for 18th Annual Colors Screen Awards 2012 |url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/features/type/view/id/2951 |publisher=[[Bollywood Hungama]] |accessdate=9 March 2014 |date=6 January 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160121053726/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/features/type/view/id/2951 |archivedate=21 January 2016 }}</ref><ref name=\"zee\">{{cite web|title=Zee Cine Awards 2012-Nomination List |url=http://zeenews.india.com/entertainment/bollywood/zee-cine-awards-2012-nomination-list_104104.html |publisher=[[Zee News]] |accessdate=9 March 2014 |date=18 January 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131029202203/http://zeenews.india.com/entertainment/bollywood/zee-cine-awards-2012-nomination-list_104104.html |archivedate=29 October 2013 }}</ref> She followed this by playing brief roles in a series of box office flops that failed to propel her career forward.<ref name=\"bad\">{{cite web|title=Films like 'Rascals' didn't badly affect my career: Kangana Ranaut |url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/films-like-rascals-didnt-badly-affect-my-career-kangana-ranaut/428733-8-66.html |accessdate=10 March 2014 |publisher=[[CNN-IBN]] |date=16 October 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140320174206/http://ibnlive.in.com/news/films-like-rascals-didnt-badly-affect-my-career-kangana-ranaut/428733-8-66.html |archivedate=20 March 2014 }}</ref> She said that she did some of these films due to a dearth of good roles.<ref name=\"bad\"/><ref>{{cite news|last=Singh |first=Raghuvendra |title=I have faced rejection like Rani in Queen |url=http://www.filmfare.com/interviews/i-have-faced-rejection-like-rani-in-queen-5549.html |accessdate=10 March 2014 |work=[[Filmfare]] |date=7 March 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140310005627/http://www.filmfare.com/interviews/i-have-faced-rejection-like-rani-in-queen-5549.html |archivedate=10 March 2014 }}</ref>\n\nIn 2013 Ranaut played Kaya, a [[shapeshifting]] [[mutant (fiction)|mutant]], in the science fiction film ''[[Krrish 3]]'', which ranks among the [[List of highest-grossing Bollywood films|highest-grossing Bollywood films of all time]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.boxofficeindia.com/boxnewsdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=6308&nCat= |title=Worldwide Top Ten 2013 |publisher=Box Office India |accessdate=12 December 2013 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140104212753/http://www.boxofficeindia.com/boxnewsdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=6308&nCat= |archivedate= 4 January 2014 |url-status=dead }}</ref> She received an [[IIFA Award for Best Supporting Actress]] nomination for the film.<ref name=\"iifa\">{{cite web|title=Nominations for IIFA Awards 2014 |url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/features/type/view/id/6193 |publisher=Bollywood Hungama |accessdate=21 February 2014 |date=20 February 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140221101141/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/features/type/view/id/6193 |archivedate=21 February 2014 }}</ref> Ranaut garnered critical acclaim for portraying the protagonist in the [[coming-of-age story|coming-of-age]] film ''[[Queen (2014 film)|Queen]]'' (2014),<ref name=\"box office\"/><ref name=\"queen\">{{cite news|last=Mehta |first=Ankita |title='Queen' Review Roundup: Watch it for Kangana's Superb Performance |url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/articles/542085/20140306/queen-movie-reviews-critics-kangana-ranaut-songs.htm |accessdate=10 March 2014 |work=[[International Business Times]] |date=6 March 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140310011304/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/articles/542085/20140306/queen-movie-reviews-critics-kangana-ranaut-songs.htm |archivedate=10 March 2014 }}</ref> for which she also co-wrote the dialogues with [[Anvita Dutt Guptan]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Pathak |first=Ankur |title=Queen and I |url=http://www.mumbaimirror.com/entertainment/bollywood/Queen-and-I/articleshow/32388674.cms |accessdate=21 March 2014 |newspaper=[[Mumbai Mirror]] |date=21 March 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140323050429/http://www.mumbaimirror.com/entertainment/bollywood/Queen-and-I/articleshow/32388674.cms |archivedate=23 March 2014 }}</ref> She won several awards for ''Queen'', including the [[Filmfare Award for Best Actress|Filmfare]] and the [[National Film Award for Best Actress|National Film Award]] for Best Actress.<ref name=\"ff15\">{{cite news|title=60th Britannia Filmfare Awards 2014: Complete list of winners |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/60th-Britannia-Filmfare-Awards-2014-Complete-list-of-winners/articleshow/46080277.cms |work=The Times of India |date=31 January 2015 |accessdate=31 January 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150203081332/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/60th-Britannia-Filmfare-Awards-2014-Complete-list-of-winners/articleshow/46080277.cms |archivedate= 3 February 2015 }}</ref><ref name=\"nfa15\">{{cite news|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/62nd-national-film-awards-winners-haider-wins-five-queen-two/ |title=62nd National Film Awards\u2019 winners: \u2018Haider\u2019 wins five, Kangana Ranaut\u2019s \u2018Queen\u2019 two |work=The Indian Express |date=24 March 2015 |accessdate=24 March 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150325062007/http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/62nd-national-film-awards-winners-haider-wins-five-queen-two/ |archivedate=25 March 2015 }}</ref> Ranaut played dual roles in a sequel to ''Tanu Weds Manu'', entitled ''[[Tanu Weds Manu Returns]]'' (2015), which became the first Bollywood film with a female protagonist to earn over {{INRConvert|1|b}} in India.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/box-office/special-features/id/496 |title=Box Office: Tanu Weds Manu Returns becomes first Women Centric film to enter the Rs. 100 cr club |publisher=Bollywood Hungama |accessdate=2 June 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150602183754/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/box-office/special-features/id/496 |archivedate= 2 June 2015 }}</ref> She received a second consecutive National Film Award for Best Actress and a [[Filmfare Critics Award for Best Actress]] for her role.<ref name=\"critic\">{{cite news|title=Full list of winners of the 61st Britannia Filmfare Awards |url=http://www.filmfare.com/news/full-list-of-winners-of-the-61st-britannia-filmfare-awards-11841.html |work=Filmfare |date=15 January 2016 |accessdate=16 January 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160316165017/http://www.filmfare.com/news/full-list-of-winners-of-the-61st-britannia-filmfare-awards-11841.html |archivedate=16 March 2016 }}</ref>\n\n==Films==\n[[File:Kangana Ranaut graces the special screening of Manikarnika \u2013 The Queen Of Jhansi at Sunny Super Sound in Juhu (16).jpg|alt=Kangana Ranaut is posing for the camera|thumb|Ranaut in 2019]]\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+Key\n| style=\"background:#FFFFCC;\"| {{dagger|alt=Films that have not yet been released}}\n| Denotes films that have not yet been released\n|}\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable mw-collapsible plainrowheaders\"\n|- style=\"background:#ccc; text-align:center;\"\n! scope=\"col\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\"| Year\n! scope=\"col\"| Role\n! scope=\"col\"| Director(s)\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | {{Tooltip|Ref(s)|Reference(s)}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Gangste