iveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160611155741/http://www.news18.com/news/movies/kangana-ranaut-rajamouli-honoured-with-indian-of-the-year-award-1254238.html |archivedate=11 June 2016 }}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |2018\n|[[Rangoon (2017 Hindi film)|''Rangoon'']]\n|[[Filmfare Awards]]\n|[[Filmfare Critics Award for Best Actress|Best Actress (Critics)]]\n|{{nom}}\n|align=\"center\"|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.filmfare.com/awards/filmfare-awards-2018/nominations/critics-best-actor-female|title=Critics Best Actor in Leading Role Female 2017 Nominees {{!}}  Filmfare Awards|work=Filmfare|access-date=20 January 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180121071515/https://www.filmfare.com/awards/filmfare-awards-2018/nominations/critics-best-actor-female|archivedate=21 January 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n|''[[Simran (film)|Simran]]''\n|[[Screen Awards]]\n|[[Screen Award for Best Actress|Best Actress]]\n|{{Nom}}\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\" |2019\n|''[[Manikarnika: The Queen of Jhansi]]''\n|[[Screen Awards]]\n|[[Screen Award for Best Actress|Best Actress]]\n|{{Nom}}\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" | 2020\n|[[Orders, decorations, and medals of India|Civilian Awards]]\n|[[Padma Shri]]\n|For excellence in the field of performing arts\n|{{Won}}\n|\n|-\n|[[Judgementall Hai Kya]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Filmfare Awards]]\n|[[Filmfare Critics Award for Best Actress|Best Actress (Critics)]]\n|{{Nom}}\n|\n|-\n|''[[Manikarnika: The Queen of Jhansi]]''\n|[[Filmfare Award for Best Actress|Best Actress]]\n|{{Nom}}\n|\n|-\n|}\n\n==Footnotes==\n{{notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb name|id=2144007|name=Kangana Ranaut}}\n* [http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/celebritymicro/index/id/85048 Kangana Ranaut] on [[Bollywood Hungama]]\n{{featured list}}\n{{Portal bar|Bollywood|Film}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ranaut, Kangana filmography}}\n[[Category:Indian filmographies]]\n[[Category:Actress filmographies]]\n[[Category:Lists of awards received by actor]]\n", "text_old": "{{EngvarB|date=April 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2020}}\n[[File:Kangana Ranaut at 2019 Cannes (cropped).jpg|thumb|alt=Kangana Ranaut is smiling at the camera|Ranaut at the [[2019 Cannes Film Festival]]]]\n[[Kangana Ranaut]] (also credited as Kangna Ranaut) is an Indian actress who appears predominantly in [[Bollywood|Hindi films]]. She has received several awards, including the [[Padma Shri]], fourth highest civilian award in the [[Republic of India]], three [[National Film Awards]], four [[Filmfare Awards]], three [[International Indian Film Academy Awards]], and one award each from the [[Screen Awards|Screen]], [[Zee Cine Awards|Zee Cine]] and [[Producers Guild Film Awards|Producers Guild]] award ceremonies.\n\nRanaut made her acting debut in 2006 with a leading role in the thriller ''[[Gangster (2006 film)|Gangster]]'', for which she was awarded the [[Filmfare Award for Best Female Debut]], among other debut awards.<ref name=\"bio\">{{cite news|title=Kangana Ranaut |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/chunk-ht-ui-entertainmentsectionpage-celebrityintro/kangana-ranaut/article1-894273.aspx |accessdate=28 January 2015 |newspaper=[[Hindustan Times]] |date=23 July 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150205105648/http://www.hindustantimes.com/chunk-ht-ui-entertainmentsectionpage-celebrityintro/kangana-ranaut/article1-894273.aspx |archivedate= 5 February 2015 }}</ref> Her portrayals of a character based on actress [[Parveen Babi]] in  ''[[Woh Lamhe]]'' (2006) and a shrewd socialite in ''[[Life in a... Metro]]'' (2007) were lauded,<ref name=\"journey\">{{cite news|title=Kangana Ranaut's impressive Bollywood journey |url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/kangana-ranauts-impressive-bollywood-journey/1/321907.html |accessdate=9 March 2014 |work=[[India Today]] |date=6 November 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140309061446/http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/kangana-ranauts-impressive-bollywood-journey/1/321907.html |archivedate= 9 March 2014 }}</ref> with the latter earning her a [[Stardust Award for Breakthrough Performance \u2013 Female]].<ref name=\"bio\"/> Ranaut won numerous awards, including the [[National Film Award for Best Supporting Actress]] and a Filmfare Award [[Filmfare Award for Best Supporting Actress|in the same category]] for her role as a [[Substance dependence|substance abusing]] supermodel in the drama ''[[Fashion (2008 film)|Fashion]]'' (2008).<ref name=\"bio\"/><ref>{{cite web |url=http://iffi.nic.in/Dff2011/Frm56NFAAward.aspx?PdfName=56NFA.pdf |title=56th National Film Awards |publisher=[[Directorate of Film Festivals]] |accessdate=29 March 2014 |format=PDF |page=40 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130130000605/http://iffi.nic.in/Dff2011/Frm56NFAAward.aspx?PdfName=56NFA.pdf |archivedate=30 January 2013 }}</ref> Also in 2008, she featured as a village girl in ''[[Dhaam Dhoom]]'', her first Tamil film.<ref name=\"dhaam\">{{cite news |title=Last work of a talented director |url=http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1G1-188902335.html |work=[[Post (South Africa)|Post]] |url-access=subscription  |via=[[HighBeam Research]] |accessdate=20 March 2014 |date=12 November 2008 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140611094757/http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1G1-188902335.html |archivedate=11 June 2014  }}</ref>\n\nRanaut subsequently featured in several commercially successful films, including the supernatural thriller ''[[Raaz: The Mystery Continues]]'' (2009), the crime film ''[[Once Upon a Time in Mumbaai]]'' (2010), the romantic comedy ''[[Tanu Weds Manu]]'' (2011), and the comedy ''[[Double Dhamaal]]'' (2011).<ref name=\"box office\">{{cite web|title=Kangana Ranaut: Box Office Details and Filmography |url=http://boxofficeindia.com/Star_Cast/actor_detail/kangana_ranaut |publisher=[[Box Office India]] |accessdate=9 March 2014 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150918191957/http://www.boxofficeindia.com/Star_Cast/actor_detail/kangana_ranaut |archivedate=18 September 2015 |url-status=dead }}</ref> For her role in ''Tanu Weds Manu'', she received nominations for the [[Screen Award for Best Actress]] and the [[Zee Cine Award for Best Actor \u2013 Female]], among others.<ref name=\"screen\">{{cite web|title=Nominations for 18th Annual Colors Screen Awards 2012 |url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/features/type/view/id/2951 |publisher=[[Bollywood Hungama]] |accessdate=9 March 2014 |date=6 January 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160121053726/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/features/type/view/id/2951 |archivedate=21 January 2016 }}</ref><ref name=\"zee\">{{cite web|title=Zee Cine Awards 2012-Nomination List |url=http://zeenews.india.com/entertainment/bollywood/zee-cine-awards-2012-nomination-list_104104.html |publisher=[[Zee News]] |accessdate=9 March 2014 |date=18 January 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131029202203/http://zeenews.india.com/entertainment/bollywood/zee-cine-awards-2012-nomination-list_104104.html |archivedate=29 October 2013 }}</ref> She followed this by playing brief roles in a series of box office flops that failed to propel her career forward.<ref name=\"bad\">{{cite web|title=Films like 'Rascals' didn't badly affect my career: Kangana Ranaut |url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/films-like-rascals-didnt-badly-affect-my-career-kangana-ranaut/428733-8-66.html |accessdate=10 March 2014 |publisher=[[CNN-IBN]] |date=16 October 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140320174206/http://ibnlive.in.com/news/films-like-rascals-didnt-badly-affect-my-career-kangana-ranaut/428733-8-66.html |archivedate=20 March 2014 }}</ref> She said that she did some of these films due to a dearth of good roles.<ref name=\"bad\"/><ref>{{cite news|last=Singh |first=Raghuvendra |title=I have faced rejection like Rani in Queen |url=http://www.filmfare.com/interviews/i-have-faced-rejection-like-rani-in-queen-5549.html |accessdate=10 March 2014 |work=[[Filmfare]] |date=7 March 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140310005627/http://www.filmfare.com/interviews/i-have-faced-rejection-like-rani-in-queen-5549.html |archivedate=10 March 2014 }}</ref>\n\nIn 2013 Ranaut played Kaya, a [[shapeshifting]] [[mutant (fiction)|mutant]], in the science fiction film ''[[Krrish 3]]'', which ranks among the [[List of highest-grossing Bollywood films|highest-grossing Bollywood films of all time]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.boxofficeindia.com/boxnewsdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=6308&nCat= |title=Worldwide Top Ten 2013 |publisher=Box Office India |accessdate=12 December 2013 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140104212753/http://www.boxofficeindia.com/boxnewsdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=6308&nCat= |archivedate= 4 January 2014 |url-status=dead }}</ref> She received an [[IIFA Award for Best Supporting Actress]] nomination for the film.<ref name=\"iifa\">{{cite web|title=Nominations for IIFA Awards 2014 |url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/features/type/view/id/6193 |publisher=Bollywood Hungama |accessdate=21 February 2014 |date=20 February 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140221101141/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/features/type/view/id/6193 |archivedate=21 February 2014 }}</ref> Ranaut garnered critical acclaim for portraying the protagonist in the [[coming-of-age story|coming-of-age]] film ''[[Queen (2014 film)|Queen]]'' (2014),<ref name=\"box office\"/><ref name=\"queen\">{{cite news|last=Mehta |first=Ankita |title='Queen' Review Roundup: Watch it for Kangana's Superb Performance |url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/articles/542085/20140306/queen-movie-reviews-critics-kangana-ranaut-songs.htm |accessdate=10 March 2014 |work=[[International Business Times]] |date=6 March 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140310011304/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/articles/542085/20140306/queen-movie-reviews-critics-kangana-ranaut-songs.htm |archivedate=10 March 2014 }}</ref> for which she also co-wrote the dialogues with [[Anvita Dutt Guptan]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Pathak |first=Ankur |title=Queen and I |url=http://www.mumbaimirror.com/entertainment/bollywood/Queen-and-I/articleshow/32388674.cms |accessdate=21 March 2014 |newspaper=[[Mumbai Mirror]] |date=21 March 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140323050429/http://www.mumbaimirror.com/entertainment/bollywood/Queen-and-I/articleshow/32388674.cms |archivedate=23 March 2014 }}</ref> She won several awards for ''Queen'', including the [[Filmfare Award for Best Actress|Filmfare]] and the [[National Film Award for Best Actress|National Film Award]] for Best Actress.<ref name=\"ff15\">{{cite news|title=60th Britannia Filmfare Awards 2014: Complete list of winners |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/60th-Britannia-Filmfare-Awards-2014-Complete-list-of-winners/articleshow/46080277.cms |work=The Times of India |date=31 January 2015 |accessdate=31 January 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150203081332/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/60th-Britannia-Filmfare-Awards-2014-Complete-list-of-winners/articleshow/46080277.cms |archivedate= 3 February 2015 }}</ref><ref name=\"nfa15\">{{cite news|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/62nd-national-film-awards-winners-haider-wins-five-queen-two/ |title=62nd National Film Awards\u2019 winners: \u2018Haider\u2019 wins five, Kangana Ranaut\u2019s \u2018Queen\u2019 two |work=The Indian Express |date=24 March 2015 |accessdate=24 March 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150325062007/http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/62nd-national-film-awards-winners-haider-wins-five-queen-two/ |archivedate=25 March 2015 }}</ref> Ranaut played dual roles in a sequel to ''Tanu Weds Manu'', entitled ''[[Tanu Weds Manu Returns]]'' (2015), which became the first Bollywood film with a female protagonist to earn over {{INRConvert|1|b}} in India.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/box-office/special-features/id/496 |title=Box Office: Tanu Weds Manu Returns becomes first Women Centric film to enter the Rs. 100 cr club |publisher=Bollywood Hungama |accessdate=2 June 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150602183754/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/box-office/special-features/id/496 |archivedate= 2 June 2015 }}</ref> She received a second consecutive National Film Award for Best Actress and a [[Filmfare Critics Award for Best Actress]] for her role.<ref name=\"critic\">{{cite news|title=Full list of winners of the 61st Britannia Filmfare Awards |url=http://www.filmfare.com/news/full-list-of-winners-of-the-61st-britannia-filmfare-awards-11841.html |work=Filmfare |date=15 January 2016 |accessdate=16 January 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160316165017/http://www.filmfare.com/news/full-list-of-winners-of-the-61st-britannia-filmfare-awards-11841.html |archivedate=16 March 2016 }}</ref>\n\n==Films==\n[[File:Kangana ranaut 2012.jpg|thumb|alt=Kangana Ranaut is posing for the camera|Ranaut in 2012]]\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+Key\n| style=\"background:#FFFFCC;\"| {{dagger|alt=Films that have not yet been released}}\n| Denotes films that have not yet been released\n|}\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable mw-collapsible plainrowheaders\"\n|- style=\"background:#ccc; text-align:center;\"\n! scope=\"col\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\"| Year\n! scope=\"col\"| Role\n! scope=\"col\"| Director(s)\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | {{Tooltip|Ref(s)|Reference(s)}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Gangster (2006 film)|gangster]]''\n| 2006\n| Simran\n|{{Sort|Basu|[[Anurag Basu]]}}\n| [[Filmfare Award for Best Female Debut]]\n| align=\"center\"|<ref name=\"bio\"/>\