about bedroom pop wonder beabadoobee|last=Kheraj|first=Alim|date=April 30, 2019|website=[[i-D]]|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190501052219/https://i-d.vice.com/en_us/article/bj9nd3/10-things-you-need-to-know-about-bedroom-pop-wonder-beabadoobee|archive-date=May 1, 2019|access-date=November 19, 2019}}</ref>}}\n| years_active     = 2017\u2013present\n}}\n\n'''Beatrice Kristi Laus''' (born 3 June 2000), also known as '''Bea Kristi''' or professionally as '''beabadoobee''',<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://open.spotify.com/artist/35l9BRT7MXmM8bv2WDQiyB|title=beabadoobee|website=[[Spotify]]|url-status=live}}</ref> is a [[Filipino-British]] indie singer-songwriter. Since 2018, she has released 5 extended plays under [[Dirty Hit]], and is set to support [[The 1975]] on the UK leg of their [[Music for Cars Tour]] in February 2020 as well as their [[Notes on a Conditional Form]] tour of North America in April 2020. As of March 2020, Beabadoobee has over 125 million accumulative [[Streaming media|streams]] on [[Spotify]].\n\nKristi was nominated for the [[Rising Star (Brit Award)|Rising Star Award]] at the [[2020 Brit Awards]], and was predicted as a breakthrough act for 2020 in an annual [[BBC]] poll of music critics, [[Sound of 2020]].\n\n== Early life ==\nLaus was born in [[Iloilo City]], Philippines on 3 June 2000 and moved to London with her parents at the age of 3.<ref name=\"NME1\" /><ref name=\"Vice1\" /> She grew up in West London listening to [[Music of the Philippines#Popular music (original Pilipino music)|OPM]] (original Pinoy music) as well as pop and rock music from the 1980s. While she was a teenager, she listened to [[indie rock]] including [[Karen O]], [[Yeah Yeah Yeahs]], [[Florist (band)|Florist]] and [[Alex G]].<ref name=\"AllMusic\" /> She attended [[Sacred Heart High School, Hammersmith|Sacred Heart High School]] for her high school education and [[Hammersmith Academy]] for her [[sixth form]] education.{{Citation needed|date=November 2019}} Kristi spent seven years learning to play the violin, before getting her first guitar second-hand at the age of 17.<ref name=\"Guardian\" /> She taught herself how to play the instrument using [[YouTube]] tutorials.<ref name=\"AllMusic\" /> She was inspired by [[Kimya Dawson]] and the [[Juno (soundtrack)|''Juno'' soundtrack]] to start making music.<ref name=\"Vice1\" />\n\n==Career==\n\n=== 2017\u20132019: ''Lice'', ''Patched Up'', ''Loveworm'' and ''Space Cadet'' ===\nThe first song Kristi wrote on her guitar was \"Coffee\".<ref name=\"Complex1\" /> She released the song as well as a [[cover version|cover]] of [[Karen O]]'s \"[[The Moon Song]]\" in September 2017. \"Coffee\" gained over 300,000 views on YouTube,<ref name=\"Vice1\" /> as well as the attention of [[Dirty Hit|Dirty Hit Records]].<ref name=\"Teen Vogue1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.teenvogue.com/story/beabadoobee-space-cadet-touring-with-clairo-writing-songs-for-bff|title=19-Year-Old Beabadoobee on Her Pop-Punk Phase, Touring With Clairo, and Writing Songs for Her BFF|last=Russell|first=Erica|date=October 22, 2019|website=[[Teen Vogue]]|url-status=live|access-date=November 19, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191104002702/https://www.teenvogue.com/story/beabadoobee-space-cadet-touring-with-clairo-writing-songs-for-bff|archive-date=November 4, 2019}}</ref> This was followed by the release of her debut EP ''Lice'' in March 2018 and her second EP ''Patched Up'' in December 2018.<ref name=\"Vice1\" /><ref name=\"diymagazine\">{{cite web|url=http://diymag.com/2018/12/07/beabadoobee-patched-up-ep-review|title=Beabadoobee - Patched Up {{!}} EP Review|last1=Finn|first1=Rachel|date=August 2019|publisher=[[DIY (magazine)|DIY]]|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190829044643/http://diymag.com/2018/12/07/beabadoobee-patched-up-ep-review|archive-date=August 29, 2019|accessdate=August 29, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn January 2019, Kristi was placed with [[Billie Eilish]] on [[NME]]'s list of \"Essential New Artists for 2019\".<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.nme.com/blogs/nme-blogs/the-nme-100-essential-new-artists-for-2019-2426835|title=The NME 100: Essential new artists for 2019|last=Smith|first=Thomas|date=January 8, 2019|website=[[NME]]|language=en-GB|url-status=live|access-date=December 2, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn early 2019, Kristi released her third EP titled ''Loveworm''.<ref name=\"Billboard\">{{cite web |last1=Rowley |first1=Glenn |title=U.K. Teen Beabadoobee Breaks Down Her 'Loveworm' EP: Exclusive |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/rock/8508811/uk-teen-beabadoobee-breaks-down-loveworm-ep-exclusive |date=April 26, 2019|publisher=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |accessdate=August 29, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"Complex1\" /><ref name=\"Clash1\">{{cite web |last1=Murray |first1=Robin |title=Beabadoobee Shares Gamechanger New 'Loveworm' EP |url=https://www.clashmusic.com/news/beabadoobee-shares-gamechanger-new-loveworm-ep |date=April 26, 2019|publisher=[[Clash (magazine)|Clash]] |accessdate=August 29, 2019}}</ref> In July 2019, Kristi released an acoustic version of the EP and titled it ''Loveworm (Bedroom Sessions)''.<ref name=\"OTW2\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.onestowatch.com/blog/beabadoobee-imbues-loveworm-bedroom-sessions|title=Beabadoobee Imbues \u2018Loveworm (Bedroom Sessions)\u2019 With a Comfortable Warmth / Ones To Watch|last=Myers|first=Jess|date=July 9, 2019|website=Ones To Watch|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190920200251/https://www.onestowatch.com/blog/beabadoobee-imbues-loveworm-bedroom-sessions|archive-date=September 20, 2019|access-date=September 20, 2019}}</ref> As of August 2019, Kristi reached over 36 million streams on Spotify according to ''The Prelude Press''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://thepreludepress.com/news/2019/8/21/beabadoobee-releases-new-single-she-plays-bass|title=Beabadoobee Releases New Single, \"She Plays Bass\"|last=Vigil|first=Dom|date=August 22, 2019|website=The Prelude Press|language=en-US|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191121142411/https://thepreludepress.com/news/2019/8/21/beabadoobee-releases-new-single-she-plays-bass|archive-date=November 21, 2019|access-date=November 21, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn September 2019, she commenced her first tour supporting [[Clairo]] on her [[Immunity (Clairo album)|''Immunity'' Tour]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://pitchfork.com/news/clairo-announces-north-american-tour/|title=Clairo Announces North American Tour|last=Kim|first=Michelle|date=August 5, 2019|website=[[Pitchfork (magazine)|Pitchfork]]|language=en|url-status=live|access-date=November 19, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190805173601/https://pitchfork.com/news/clairo-announces-north-american-tour|archive-date=August 5, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"i-D2\">{{Cite web|url=https://i-d.vice.com/en_us/article/qvgne5/how-beabadoobee-went-from-bedroom-artist-to-indie-rock-wunderkind|title=How Beabadoobee went from bedroom artist to indie rock wunderkind|last=DeMarco|first=Nicole|date=October 18, 2019|website=i-D|language=en|access-date=November 19, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191021223405/https://i-d.vice.com/en_us/article/qvgne5/how-beabadoobee-went-from-bedroom-artist-to-indie-rock-wunderkind|archive-date=October 21, 2019}}</ref> Kristi is signed to the record label Dirty Hit,<ref name=\"NME2\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/no-rome-beabadoobee-oscar-lang-dirty-hit-2019-uk-tour-2554486|title=No Rome, Beabadoobee and Oscar Lang for Dirty Hit 2019 UK tour|last=Trendell|first=Andrew|date=October 7, 2019|website=[[NME]]|language=en-US|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191121140638/https://www.nme.com/news/music/no-rome-beabadoobee-oscar-lang-dirty-hit-2019-uk-tour-2554486|archive-date=November 21, 2019|access-date=November 19, 2019}}</ref> where she released her fourth EP, ''Space Cadet'' in October 2019. The five-track EP included songs like \u201cShe Plays Bass\u201d, \u201cI Wish I Was Stephen Malkmus\u201d and the title track.<ref name=\"Krol\">{{cite web|url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/beabadoobee-space-cadet-ep-arrives-early-listen-now-2557100|title=Beabadoobee's 'Space Cadet' EP arrives early \u2013 listen now|last1=Krol|first1=Charlotte|date=October 14, 2019|website=[[NME]]|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191015030632/https://www.nme.com/news/music/beabadoobee-space-cadet-ep-arrives-early-listen-now-2557100|archive-date=October 15, 2019|accessdate=October 27, 2019}}</ref> Kristi made the [[List of NME covers|front cover of NME]] on 25 October 2019.\n\nBeabadoobee was shortlisted for the [[Rising Star (Brit Award)|Rising Star Award]] at the [[2020 Brit Awards]],<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2019/dec/06/soul-singer-celeste-named-winner-of-brits-rising-star-award|title=Soul singer Celeste named winner of Brits rising star award|last=Snapes|first=Laura|date=2019-12-06|work=The Guardian|access-date=2019-12-06|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077}}</ref> an award previously crowned by names like [[Adele]], [[Florence and the Machine]], [[Ellie Goulding]] and [[Sam Smith]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://planetradio.co.uk/hits-radio/entertainment/television/brit-awards-critics-choice/|title=The BRIT Awards announce 2020 shortlist for the new Rising Star Award|last=Dodds|first=Emma|date=November 27, 2019|website=[[Hits Radio]]|language=en|url-status=live|access-date=November 27, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn February 2019, a sample of her song \"Coffee\" was used on [[Powfu]]'s single, \"[[Death Bed]]\". A year later, the song became a [[sleeper hit]] after going viral on the app [[TikTok]]. The song reached the top 20 in numerous regions, including Australia, Italy, New Zealand, and the United Kingdom.\n\nIn November 2019, Kristi released a pair of [[Spotify Singles]], one being a cover of \"[[Don't You (Forget About Me)|Don't You Forget About Me]]\" by [[Simple Minds]] as well as a version of \"She Plays Bass\" recorded in [[Abbey Road Studios]] in London.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.clashmusic.com/news/beabadoobee-covers-simple-minds-classic-dont-you-forget-about-me|title=Beabadoobee Covers Simple Minds' Classic 'Don't You (Forget About Me)'|last=Murray|first=Robin|date=November 20, 2019|website=[[Clash (magazine)|Clash]]|language=en|url-status=live|access-date=December 2, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"Spotify Singles\">{{Cite web|url=https://ventsmagazine.com/2019/11/20/beabadoobee-releases-spotify-singles-covers-simple-minds-dont-you-forget-about-me/|title=Beabadoobee Releases Spotify Singles {{!}} Covers Simple Minds\u2019 \u201cDon\u2019t You Forget About Me\u201d|last=Frometa|first=RJ|date=November 20, 2019|website=Vents Magazine|language=en-US|url-status=live|access-date=December 2, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn December 2019, Kristi was longlisted in the annual [[BBC]] poll of music critics, [[Sound of 2020]].<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/entertainment-arts-50741299|title=Yungblud and Celeste make BBC Sound of 2020 list|last=Savage|first=Mark|date=12 December 2019|work=[[BBC]]|access-date=13 December 2019|language=en-GB}}</ref>\n\n=== 2020\u2013present: Debut album ===\nIn February 2020, Kristi performed at the 2020 [[NME Awards]] after winning the Radar Award.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-nme-awards-are-back-for-2020-with-yungblud-beabadoobee-and-many-more-2586045|title=The NME Awards are back for 2020 \u2013 see the line-up and get tickets|last=Trendell|first=Andrew|date=December 11, 2019|website=[[NME]]|language=en-GB|url-status=live|access-date=December 11, 2019}}</ref> She will support labelmates [[The 1975]] on the UK leg of their [[Music for Cars Tour]] in February 2020,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/beabadoobee-support-1975-uk-arena-tour-2569750|title=Beabadoobee to support The 1975 on UK arena tour|last=Reilly|first=Nick|date=2019-11-20|website=NME|language=en-US|access-date=2019-11-24}}</ref> as well as their [[Notes on a Conditional Form]] tour of North America in April 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-1975-announce-massive-run-of-north-american-shows-with-phoebe-bridgers-and-beabadoobee-2597730|title=The 1975 announce massive run of North American shows with Phoebe Bridgers and Beabadoobee|last=Clarke|first=Patrick|date=16 January 2020|website=[[NME]]|language=en-GB|url-status=live|access-date=18 January 2020}}</ref> Kristi wrote on [[Instagram]] that she would be releasing an album this year.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B6_xAJlp5TP/|title=beabadoobee on Instagram: \u201cim makin an album dis year\u201d|website=Instagram|language=en|access-date=2020-01-10}}</ref> Kristi has told ''[[Vice (magazine)|Vice]]'' that she plans on making film soundtracks in the future, as they heavily inspired her to make music.<ref name=\"Vice1\" />\n\n== Artistry ==\nKristi has cited [[Elliott Smith]], [[The Moldy Peaches|The Mouldy Peaches]], [[Pavement (band)|Pavement]], [[Mazzy Star]], [[The Beatles]], [[Simon & Garfunkel|Simon and Garfunkel]] and [[Daniel Johnston]] as her musical influences.<ref name=\"i-D1\" /><ref name=\"Vice1\" />\n\n[[Khalid (singer)|Khalid]], [[Jaden Smith]] and [[Matty Healy]] of [[The 1975]] have named themselves as fans of Beabadoobee.<ref name=\"Khalid\">{{Cite tweet|number=1129512170784530434|author=[[Khalid (singer)|Khalid]] [confirmed account]|user=thegreatkhalid|title=if you wanna look out the window and create your own music video listen to this :(|date=May 18, 2019|access-date=November 21, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191121144013/https://twitter.com/thegreatkhalid/status/1129512170784530434|archive-date=November 21, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/newsbeat-50098938|title=Beabadoobee: Meet Matty Healy's favourite singer|last=[[Newsbeat]]|date=October 24, 2019|work=[[BBC News]]|access-date=November 19, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191024115209/https://www.bbc.com/news/newsbeat-50098938|archive-date=October 24, 2019|language=en-GB}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n===Extended plays===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\" id=\"epstable\"\n|+ List of extended plays\n! rowspan=\"2\" scope=\"col\" style=\"width:16em;\" | Title\n! rowspan=\"2\" scope=\"col\" style=\"width:20em;\" | EP details\n!Peak chart positions\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:85%;\"| [[UK Independent Singles and Album Breakers Charts|UK<br>Breakers]]<br><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/charts/independent-albums-breakers-chart/20191213/255/|title=Official Independent Album Breakers Chart Top 20: 13 December 2019|website=[[Official Charts Company]]|language=en|url-status=live|access-date=30 December 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''Lice''\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" | \n*Released: February 28, 2018<ref>{{Citation|title=Lice - EP by beabadoobee|url=https://music.apple.com/us/album/lice-ep/1435260751|work=[[Apple Music]]}}</ref>\n*Label: [[Dirty Hit]]\n*Formats: Digital download, streaming\n|\u2013\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''Patched Up''\n|\n* Released: December 7, 2018<ref>{{Citation|title=Patched Up by beabadoobee|url=https://music.apple.com/us/album/patched-up/1444723295|work=[[Apple Music]]}}</ref>\n* Label: Dirty Hit\n* Formats: [[Phonograph record|LP]], [[Cassette tape|CS]], digital download, streaming\n|\u2013\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''Loveworm''\n|\n* Released: April 26, 2019<ref>{{Citation|title=Loveworm by beabadoobee|url=https://music.apple.com/us/album/loveworm/1459718896|work=[[Apple Music]]}}</ref>\n* Label: Dirty Hit\n* Formats: LP, CS, digital download, streaming\n|\u2013\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''Loveworm (Bedroom Sessions)''\n|\n* Released: July 9, 2019<ref>{{Citation|title=Loveworm (Bedroom Sessions) by beabadoobee|url=https://music.apple.com/us/album/loveworm-bedroom-sessions/1471335369|work=[[Apple Music]]}}</ref>\n* Label: Dirty Hit\n* Formats: digital download, streaming\n|\u2013\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''Space Cadet''\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" | \n*Released: October 15, 2019<ref>{{Citation|title=Space Cadet - EP by beabadoobee|url=https://music.apple.com/us/album/space-cadet-ep/1482163543|work=[[Apple Music]]}}</ref>\n*Label: Dirty Hit\n*Formats: LP, digital download, streaming\n|14\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |''Spotify Singles''{{efn-ua|A [[Spotify]]-exclusive live EP consisting of live performances of \"She Plays Bass\" live from [[Abbey Road Studios]] and a cover version of [[Simple Minds]]' \"[[Don't You (Forget About Me)]]\"<ref name=\"Spotify Singles\" />}}\n|\n* Released: November 20, 2019\n* Label: Dirty Hit\n* Formats: Streaming\n|\u2013\n|}\n\n===Singles===\n\n==== As lead artist ====\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! rowspan=\"2\" scope=\"col\" |Year\n! rowspan=\"2\" scope=\"col\" |Title\n! scope=\"col\" |Peak chart positions\n! rowspan=\"2\" scope=\"col\" |Album\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Ultratop|BEL<br />(FL)]]<br /><ref name=\"Ultratop\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.ultratop.be/nl/song/1d15ae/Beabadoobee-I-Wish-I-Was-Stephen-Malkmus|title=BEABADOOBEE \u2013 I WISH I WAS STEPHEN MALKMUS|website=[[Ultratop]]|url-status=live|access-date=October 19, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |2017\n! scope=\"row\" | \"Coffee\"\n|\u2014\n| rowspan=\"3\" {{n/a|Non-album singles}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"The Moon Song\"\n|\u2014\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |2018\n! scope=\"row\" | \"Susie May\"\n|\u2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"Dance with Me\"\n| \u2014\n| rowspan=\"2\" |''Patched Up''\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\" |2019\n! scope=\"row\" | \"If You Want To\"\n|\u2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"Disappear\"\n|\u2014\n|''Loveworm''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"She Plays Bass\"\n| \u2014\n| rowspan=\"2\" |''Space Cadet''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"I Wish I Was Stephen Malkmus\"\n| \u2014{{efn|\"I Wish I Was Stephen Malkmus\" did not enter the ''[[Ultratop]] Top 50'', but spent 4 weeks as an extra tip on the ''Ultratop Bubbling Under'' chart.|group=upper-alpha|name=}}\n|-\n|}\n\n==== As featured artist ====\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"| Year\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"10\"| Peak chart positions\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"| Certifications\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"| Album\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:90%;\"|[[UK Singles Chart|UK]]<br><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/artist/57147/powfu-ft-beabadoobee/|title=POWFU FT BEABADOOBEE {{!}} full Official Chart History|website=[[Official Charts Company]]|url-status=live|access-date=4 March 2020}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:90%;\"|[[ARIA Charts|AUS]]<br><ref name=\"ARIA\">{{cite web|url=http://www.ariacharts.com.au/charts/singles-chart|title=ARIA Australian Top 50 Singles|publisher=[[Australian Recording Industry Association]]|date=13 April 2020|accessdate=11 April 2020}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:90%;\"|[[Canadian Hot 100|CAN]]<br><ref name=\":3\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/Beabadoobee/chart-history/CAN|title=Beabadoobee Chart History (Canadian Hot 100)|website=Billboard|access-date=8 April 2020}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:90%;\"|[[The Official Finnish Charts|FIN]]<br><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ifpi.fi/lista/artistit/powfu%2C+beabadoobee/death+bed+/|title=Powfu, Beabadoobee: Death Bed|website=[[Musiikkituottajat|Musiikkituottajat \u2013 IFPI Finland]]|language=fi-FI|url-status=live|access-date=23 March 2020}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:90%;\"|[[Irish Singles Chart|IRE]]<br><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://irish-charts.com/showinterpret.asp?interpret=Beabadoobee|title=Discography Beabadoobee|website=irish-charts.com|url-status=live|access-date=3 March 