| misc       = {{External music video|{{YouTube|jJPMnTXl63E|\"Death Bed\"}}}}\n}}\n\"'''Death Bed'''\", released in later versions as \"'''Death Bed (Coffee for Your Head)'''\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://open.spotify.com/track/7eJMfftS33KTjuF7lTsMCx|title=\"death bed (coffee for your head) (feat. beabadoobee)\" on Spotify}}</ref> (stylized in [[Letter case#All lowercase|all lowercase]]) is a song by Canadian rapper [[Powfu]], featuring Filipino-British singer-songwriter [[Beabadoobee]]. The song was initially uploaded to [[SoundCloud]] in 2019; following Powfu signing to [[Columbia Records]], the song was released on streaming services on February 8, 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://genius.com/a/powfu-breaks-down-the-meaning-of-death-bed|title=Powfu Breaks Down The Meaning Of \"Death Bed\"|website=[[Genius (website)|Genius]]|last=Reneau|first=Steven|date=March 6, 2020|accessdate=March 18, 2020}}</ref> The song samples the 2017 song \"Coffee\" by Beabadoobee, who is credited as a feature.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://headlineplanet.com/home/2020/03/08/powfu-beabadoobees-death-bed-picks-up-pop-radio-airplay-reaches-50-million-spotify-streams/|title=Powfu & Beabadoobee's \"Death Bed\" Picks Up Pop Radio Airplay, Reaches 50 Million Spotify Streams|website=Headline Planet|last=Cantor|first=Brian|date=March 8, 2020|accessdate=March 18, 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe song went viral on the video sharing app [[TikTok]] in early 2020.<ref name=\"Genius BG\">{{cite web|url=https://genius.com/a/powfu-s-death-bed-samples-beabadoobee-s-coffee|title=Powfu's Viral Hit \"Death Bed\" Arrives On Streaming Services After Lengthy Sample Clearance Delay|website=Genius|last=Fu|first=Eddie|date=February 13, 2020|accessdate=March 18, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Background==\nThe song's commercial release was delayed by a year due to the clearance of the [[Sampling (music)|sample]] of Beabadoobee's 2017 song \"Coffee\". Powfu said on [[Twitter]] in April 2019 that he had not put it on [[Spotify]] because he was \"scared [he'd] get in trouble from the sample [he] use[s] in it\", but said he \"would upload it anyway\" and told his followers to give him \"a week and a half\". It was finally released to streaming and download services in February 2020.<ref name=\"Genius BG\"/>\n\n==Composition==\nColumbia's British subsidiary [[Sony Music UK]] described it as a \"lo-fi hip hop single\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pressparty.com/pg/newsdesk/sonymusicuk/view/205330/|title=Powfu \u2013 New Single 'Death Bed' Feat Beabadoobee Out Now|publisher=[[Sony Music UK]]|via=[[Pressparty]]|date=March 2, 2020|accessdate=March 18, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Charts==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2020)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Australia ([[ARIA Charts|ARIA]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ariacharts.com.au/charts/singles-chart|title=ARIA Australian Top 50 Singles|publisher=[[Australian Recording Industry Association]]|date=April 13, 2020|accessdate=April 11, 2020}}</ref>\n| 5\n|-\n{{single chart|Austria|16|artist=Powfu|song=Death Bed|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 2, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Flanders|34|artist=Powfu feat. Beabadoobee|song=Death Bed|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 10, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Wallonia|46|artist=Powfu feat. Beabadoobee|song=Death Bed|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 4, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Canada|20|artist=Beabadoobee|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 8, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Czechdigital|17|year=2020|week=14|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 7, 2020}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Denmark ([[Tracklisten]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://hitlisten.nu/default.asp?w=13&y=2020&list=t40|title=Track Top-40 Uge 13, 2020|publisher=[[Hitlisten]]|accessdate=April 8, 2020}}</ref>\n| 10\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Estonia ([[Eesti Tipp-40]])<ref name=\"estonianchart\">{{Cite web|url=https://ekspress.delfi.ee/areen/eesti-tipp-40-muusikas-selle-nadala-kangelased-on-the-weeknd-ja-a