\n{{Efs player|name=[[Jimmy Scott (footballer, born 1927)|Jimmy Scott]]|pos=FW|nat=SCO|27|14|2|2|6|1|2|1|4|2}}\n{{Efs player|name=[[Duncan Smith (footballer)|Duncan Smith]]|pos=FW|nat=SCO|26|2|2|0|2|0|2|0|4|0}}\n|}\n\n<small>Source:<ref>{{cite book |last=McAllister |first=Jim |title=The Sons of the Rock - The Official History of Dumbarton Football Club |publisher=J&J Robertson Printers |year=2002 |location=Dumbarton}}</ref></small>\n\n===International===\nAndy Tait and Duncan Smith were selected to play for the Scottish League B XI against the Irish League B side on 15 April 1952 - Smith scored one of the goals in the 6-0 win.\n\n===Transfers===\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n==== Players in ====\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center; font-size:95%;width:98%; text-align:left\"\n|-\n!Player\n!From\n!Date\n|-\n| {{flagicon|SCO}} Ally Johnstone\n| {{flagicon|SCO}} [[Clydebank F.C.|Clydebank]] \n| 16 Jul 1951\n|-\n| {{flagicon|SCO}} [[Jimmy Scott (footballer, born 1927)|Jimmy Scott]]\n| {{flagicon|SCO}} [[Armadale Thistle F.C.|Armadale Thistle]] \n| 16 Jul 1951\n|-\n| {{flagicon|SCO}} [[Hugh Shaw (footballer, born 1929)|Hugh Shaw]]\n| {{flagicon|SCO}} [[Duntocher Hibernian F.C.|Duntocher Hibs]] \n| 16 Jul 1951\n|-\n| {{flagicon|SCO}} Jimmy Forbes\n| {{flagicon|SCO}} [[Rangers F.C.|Rangers]] (loan) \n| 14 Sep 1951\n|-\n| {{flagicon|SCO}} Eddie Beaton\n| {{flagicon|SCO}} [[Aberdeen F.C.|Aberdeen]] (loan) \n| 18 Sep 1951\n|-\n| {{flagicon|SCO}} Peter Murphy\n| {{flagicon|SCO}} [[Clydebank F.C.|Clydebank]] \n| 3 Oct 1951\n|-\n| {{flagicon|SCO}} Gerry McCaffrey\n| {{flagicon|SCO}} Campsie BW \n| 1 Mar 1952\n|}\n{{col-2}}\n\n==== Players out ====\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center; font-size:95%;width:98%; text-align:left\"\n|-\n!Player\n!To\n!Date\n|-\n| {{flagicon|SCO}} Willie Johnstone\n| {{flagicon|SCO}} Freed\n| 30 Apr 1952\n|-\n| {{flagicon|SCO}} Ally Johnstone\n| {{flagicon|SCO}} Freed\n| 30 Apr 1952\n|-\n| {{flagicon|SCO}} Willie McLaren\n| {{flagicon|SCO}} Freed\n| 30 Apr 1952\n|-\n| {{flagicon|SCO}} John Sharp\n| {{flagicon|SCO}} Freed\n| 30 Apr 1952\n|}\n{{col-end}}\n\n<small>Source:<ref>{{cite book | last = Litster | first = John | title = Record of Pre-War Scottish League Players | publisher = PM Publications | location = Norwich}}</ref></small>\n\n==Reserve team==\nDumbarton played a reserve team in Division C (South West) and finished 12th out of 16, recording 11 wins and 4 draws from 30 matches.  Note that in addition to the reserve sides of the bigger Division A teams in South and West Scotland, the first teams of East Stirlingshire (relegated from Division B three seasons previously) and Stranraer also competed in this league.\n\nIn the Second XI Cup, Dumbarton lost in the second round to Dundee United.\n\nFinally in the Reserve League Cup, Dumbarton could only manage a win and a draw from their 6 sectional matches and failed to progress to the knock-out stages.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{1951\u201352 in Scottish football}}\n{{Dumbarton F.C. seasons}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Dumbarton}}\n[[Category:Dumbarton F.C. seasons]]\n[[Category:Scottish football clubs 1951\u201352 season]]\n[[Category:1951\u201352 in Scottish football]]\n", "name_user": "Aitkegs", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1951%E2%80%9352_Dumbarton_F.C._season"}
{"title_page": "Marco Silvestri", "text_new": "{{Infobox football biography\n| name               = Marco Silvestri\n| fullname           = Marco Silvestri<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.efl.com/documents/professional-retained-report-2015-16549-3151378.pdf |title=EFL: Retained list: 2015/16 |publisher=English Football League |page=29 |accessdate=29 June 2016 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161202052144/http://www.efl.com/documents/professional-retained-report-2015-16549-3151378.pdf |archivedate=2 December 2016 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n| image              = \n| birth_date          = {{Birth date and age|1991|3|2|df=y}}\n| birth_place         = [[Castelnovo ne' Monti]], Italy\n| height              = {{Height|m=1.91}}\n| position            = [[Goalkeeper (association football)|Goalkeeper]]\n| currentclub         = [[Hellas Verona F.C.|Hellas Verona]]\n| clubnumber          = 1\n| youthyears1         = 2009\u20132011 | youthclubs1  = [[Modena F.C.|Modena]]\n| youthyears2         = 2010\u20132011 | youthclubs2  = \u2192 [[A.C. ChievoVerona|Chievo]] (loan)\n| clubs1  = [[A.C. ChievoVerona|Chievo]]\n| clubs2  = \u2192 [[A.C. Reggiana 1919|Reggiana]] (loan)\n| years1              = 2011\u20132014 \n| years2              = 2011\u20132012 \n| caps1  = 0  \n| caps2  = 27 \n| goals1  = 0 \n| goals2  = 0 \n| nationalteam1       = [[Italy national under-20 football team|Italy U20]]\n| nationalteam2       = [[Italy national under-21 football team|Italy U21]]\n| nationalyears1      = 2009\u20132011\n| nationalyears2      = 2011\n| nationalcaps1       = 5\n| nationalcaps2       = 1\n| nationalgoals1      = 0\n| nationalgoals2      = 0\n| club-update         = 18:01, 8 November 2019 (UTC)\n| nationalteam-update =\n| years3              = 2012\u20132013 \n| caps3  = 25 \n| goals3  = 0 \n| clubs3  = \u2192 [[Calcio Padova|Padova]] (loan)\n| years4              = 2014      \n| caps4  = 3  \n| goals4  = 0 \n| clubs4  = \u2192 [[Cagliari Calcio|Cagliari]] (loan) \n| years5              = 2014\u20132017     \n| caps5  = 88 \n| goals5  = 0 \n| clubs5  = [[Leeds United F.C.|Leeds United]]\n| years6              = 2017\u2013     \n| caps6  = 53\n| goals6  = 0 \n| clubs6  = [[Hellas Verona F.C.|Hellas Verona]]\n}}\n'''Marco Silvestri''' (born 2 March 1991) is an Italian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for Italian club [[Hellas Verona F.C.|Hellas Verona]]. Before joining Verona in 2017, he played in England for [[Leeds United F.C.|Leeds United]] and in Italy for [[A.C. ChievoVerona|Chievo]], [[A.C. Reggiana 1919|Reggiana]], [[Calcio Padova|Padova]] and [[Cagliari Calcio|Cagliari]]. Silvestri has represented his country at [[Italy national under-20 football team|under-20]] and [[Italy national under-21 football team|under-21 level]].\n\n==Club career==\n\n===Modena===\nBorn in [[Castelnovo ne' Monti]], the [[Province of Reggio Emilia]], Emilia\u2013Romagna, Silvestri started his career at [[Emilia (region of Italy)|Emilia]] club [[Modena F.C.|Modena]]. He was the third keeper behind [[Enrico Alfonso]] and [[Antonio Narciso]] in 2009\u201310 season.\n\n===Chievo===\nIn August 2010, Silvestri was signed by [[Serie A]] club [[A.C. ChievoVerona|Chievo]] on a temporary deal, with an option to purchase half of his registration rights.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.chievocalcio.tv/it/content/mercato-9|title=MERCATO|date=18 August 2010|accessdate=28 August 2010|work=AC ChievoVerona|language=Italian|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101122075607/http://chievocalcio.tv/it/content/mercato-9|archivedate=22 November 2010|df=dmy-all}}</ref> He was the third keeper of the team, behind [[Stefano Sorrentino]] and [[Lorenzo Squizzi]]. Silvestri also became the first choice keeper at [[Campionato Nazionale Primavera|the \"spring\" under-20 team]]. In June 2011 Chievo exercised the option to sign Silvestri in a [[co-ownership (football)|co-ownership deal]], for \u20ac300,000.<ref name=Chievo2011bilancio>AC ChievoVerona Report and Accounts on 30 June 2011 {{in lang|it}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.chievoverona.tv/it/news/compropriet%C3%A0-parolo-al-cesena-riscattato-silvestri|title=Compropriet\u00e0: Parolo al Cesena, riscattato Silvestri|trans-title=Co-ownership: Parolo to Cesena, redeemed Silvestri|date=22 June 2011|accessdate=24 June 2011|work=AC ChievoVerona|language=Italian|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110625021808/http://www.chievoverona.tv/it/news/compropriet%C3%A0-parolo-al-cesena-riscattato-silvestri|archivedate=25 June 2011|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n====Reggiana loan====\nSilvestri returned to [[Reggio Emilia]] for [[A.C. Reggiana 1919|Reggiana]] in July to replace [[Niccol\u00f2 Manfredini]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.chievoverona.tv/it/news/marco-silvestri-prestito-alla-reggiana|title=Marco Silvestri in prestito alla Reggiana|trans-title=Marco Silvestri temporary to Reggiana|date=4 July 2011|accessdate=8 July 2011|work=AC ChievoVerona|language=Italian|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120321093352/http://www.chievoverona.tv/it/news/marco-silvestri-prestito-alla-reggiana|archivedate=21 March 2012|df=dmy-all}}</ref> However Silvestri became the backup of Niccol\u00f2 Bellucci since round 12. After the winter break Silvestri re-affirmed as first choice. In June 2012 Chievo signed Silvestri outright for another \u20ac150,000.<ref>AC ChievoVerona Srl ''bilancio'' (financial report and accounts) on 30 June 2012 {{in lang|it}}, [http://www.registroimprese.it PDF purchased from Italian CCIAA]</ref>\n\n====Padova loan====\nIn July 2012 he left for [[Calcio Padova|Padova]]. The club failed to renew the loan of fellow U21 internationals [[Mattia Perin]]. Silvestri wore no.1 shirt for Padova in new season and would compete with ex-internationals [[Ivan Pelizzoli]] who acted as second-choice last season. However, on the last day of the transfer window, Pelizzoli rejoined Perin in [[Delfino Pescara 1936|Pescara]] and [[Luca Anania]], who became second choice in the same club, left for Padova.\n\n====Cagliari loan====\nOn 30 January 2014, Silvestri signed for [[Cagliari Calcio|Cagliari]] on loan, including the option for [[Cagliari Calcio|Cagliari]] to acquire half his ownership rights at the end of the season, the move saw [[Cagliari Calcio|Cagliari]] first choice Goalkeeper [[Michael Agazzi]] join [[A.C. Chievo Verona|Chievo]] on a permanent deal.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cagliaricalcio.net/news/15547/silvestri-al-cagliari.html|title=Silvestri al Cagliari|date=30 January 2014|accessdate=22 May 2014|publisher=Cagliari Calcio|language=Italian}}</ref>\n\nSilverstri was given the number 1 shirt. He made his debut for the club in the [[Serie A]] match against [[Parma F.C.|Parma]] on 27 April, coming into the side for [[Vlada Avramov]], keeping a clean sheet on his debut in a 1\u20130 win. On 6 May, Silvestri started the match against [[S.S.C. Napoli]], a game in which Silvestri was given a straight red card in a 3\u20130 loss after fouling [[Goran Pandev]]. After returning from suspension he returned for the final match of the season in a 3\u20130 loss against [[Juventus F.C.|Juventus]].\n\nOn 27 June, Silvestri's agent [[Francesco Romano (footballer)|Francesco Romano]], revealed that Silvestri was in talks over a move to English club Leeds United, owned by former [[Cagliari Calcio|Cagliari]] owner [[Massimo Cellino]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://translate.google.com/translate?hl=en&sl=it&u=http://gazzettadireggio.gelocal.it/sport/2014/06/23/news/marco-silvestri-oggi-firma-per-il-leeds-1.9479779&prev=/search%3Fq%3DMarco%2BSilvestri%2Bleeds%26biw%3D1525%26bih%3D674|title=marco-silvestri-oggi-firma-per-il-leeds|date=27 June 2014|accessdate=27 June 2014|work=Gazzetta Di Reggio|language=Italian}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.express.co.uk/sport/football/485254/Leeds-close-in-on-TRIPLE-swoop-with-Ross-McCormack-future-still-uncertain|title=The Italian job! Leeds close in on TRIPLE swoop with Ross McCormack future still uncertain|date=27 June 2014|accessdate=27 June 2014|work=The Express}}</ref>\n\n===Leeds United===\n\n====2014\u201315 Season====\nOn 8 July 2014, Silvestri left Chievo for a fee of \u20ac1&nbsp;million,<ref>{{cite book|title=A.C. Chievo-Verona S.r.l. bilancio al 30-06-2015|trans-title=A.C. Chievo-Verona S.r.l. financial report on 30-06-2015|date=2015|publisher=Italian C.C.I.A.A.|language=Italian|page=24}}</ref> and signed a four-year contract with English club Leeds United along with fellow Italian [[Tommaso Bianchi]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.yorkshireeveningpost.co.uk/sport/leeds-united/latest-whites-news/leeds-united-complete-silvestri-and-bianchi-signings-1-6718003|title=Leeds United complete Silvestri and Bianchi signings|date=8 July 2014|accessdate=8 July 2014|work=Yorkshire Evening Post}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.yorkshireeveningpost.co.uk/sport/leeds-united/latest-whites-news/leeds-united-new-faces-highlight-fresh-approach-to-transfer-market-1-6730859|title=Leeds United: New faces highlight fresh approach to transfer market|date=15 July 2014|accessdate=15 July 2014|work=Yorkshire Evening Post}}</ref> Silvestri's first appearance for Leeds came on 11 July in Leeds' first pre\u2013season game, which resulted in a 16\u20130 victory against Italian side FC Gherdeina.<ref name=\"Leeds United hammer Italian minnows FC Gherdeina 16-0\">{{Cite news\n| title = Leeds United hammer Italian minnows FC Gherdeina 16\u20130\n| url = http://www.yorkshireeveningpost.co.uk/sport/leeds-united/latest-whites-news/leeds-united-hammer-italian-minnows-fc-gherdeina-16-0-1-6723461\n| publisher = YEP\n| date = 11 July 2014\n| accessdate = 11 July 2014}}</ref> On 1 August, Silvestri was assigned the Leeds number 1 shirt for the 2014\u201315 season.<ref name=\"SQUAD NUMBERS RELEASED\">{{cite web |url=http://www.leedsunited.com/news/article/1wncxa2kw0zr11fmlyjr0m3t53/title/squad-numbers-released|title=SQUAD NUMBERS RELEASED|publisher=Leeds United|date=1 August 2014 |first=|last=|accessdate=1 August 2014}}</ref> Silvestri made his debut for Leeds on 9 August against [[Millwall F.C.|Millwall]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Millwall v Leeds|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/28646426|publisher=BBC Sport|accessdate=9 August 2014}}</ref> Silvestri kept his first clean sheet for Leeds in his home debut at [[Elland Road]] on 16 August in Leeds' 1\u20130 victory against [[Middlesbrough F.C.|Middlesbrough]] after a goal by [[Billy Sharp]].<ref>{{cite web|title=DEBUTANT SHARP BLUNTS BORO|url=http://www.leedsunited.com/news/article/5q0uro0bzx4a1ry3sxp6c1hkz/title/debutant-sharp-blunts-boro|publisher=Leeds United Official Site|accessdate=16 August 2014}}</ref>\n\nSilvestri kept a clean sheet and won the man of the match award after a string of saves in Leeds' 1\u20130 win on 30 August against [[Bolton Wanderers F.C.|Bolton Wanderers]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Leeds Vs Bolton Wanderers|date=30 August 2014|accessdate=30 August 2014|url=http://www.leedsunited.com/news/article/3fqrhs11d9xa18kq62h7zlkrz/title/bolton-live!|publisher=Leeds United official website|author=}}</ref> The performance led to him being named in the Football League team of the week.<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20140904004129/http://www.football-league.co.uk/features/20140901/sky-bet-football-league-team-of-the-week-300814-310814_2293307_4113706 Sky Bet Football League Team of the Week 30/08/14 \u2013 31/08/14]. Football-league.co.uk. 1 September 2014.</ref> Silvestri's impressive form continued against [[A.F.C. Bournemouth|Bournemouth]] in a 3\u20131 win.<ref>{{cite news|title= Bournemouth 1 \u2013 3 Leeds |date=16 September 2014|accessdate=16 September 2014|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/29120574|publisher=BBC Sport|author=}}</ref> With Silvestri earning praise from Caretaker Head Coach [[Neil Redfearn]] after a string of impressive saves to help keep Leeds in the game when they were 1\u20130 down.<ref>{{cite news|title= Neil Redfearn praised Leeds after win over Bournemouth |date=17 September 2014|accessdate=17 September 2014|url=http://www1.skysports.com/football/news/11688/9474081/redfearns-talking-italian|publisher=Sky Sports|author=}}</ref>\n\nSilvestri received the Man of the Match Award after keeping a clean sheet against the then league leaders Middlesbrough 1\u20130 on 21 February 2015.<ref>{{cite news |title=Middlesbrough 0 Leeds United 1: Mowatt shocks leaders Boro|url=http://www.yorkshirepost.co.uk/sport/football/leeds-utd/middlesbrough-0-leeds-unted-1-mowatt-shocks-leaders-boro-1-7119053 |date=21 February 2015 |accessdate=21 February 2015 |publisher=Yorkshire Evening Post}}</ref> On 4 March, Silvestri saved a late penalty from [[Daryl Murphy]] to help earn Leeds a 2\u20131 victory against [[Ipswich Town F.C.|Ipswich Town]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Leeds United: Mowatt is becoming a free-kick specialist|url=http://www.yorkshireeveningpost.co.uk/sport/leeds-united/latest-whites-news/leeds-united-mowatt-is-becoming-a-free-kick-specialist-1-7141861 |date=4 March 2015 |accessdate=4 March 2015 |publisher=Yorkshire Evening Post}}</ref>\n\nOn 18 April 2015, Silvestri was one of six [[Massimo Cellino]] signings (alongside [[Mirco Antenucci]], [[Giuseppe Bellusci]], [[Souleymane Doukara]], [[Dario Del Fabro]], [[Edgar \u00c7ani]]) who controversially pulled out of the squad with an 'injury' the day before a 2\u20131 loss against [[Charlton Athletic F.C.|Charlton Athletic]].<ref>{{cite news|title= Leeds United striker Steve Morison left bemused by latest chaos at Elland Road |date=19 April 2015|accessdate=|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-3046059/Leeds-United-striker-Steve-Morrison-left-bemused-latest-chaos-Elland-Road.html|publisher=Daily Mail|author= Press Association}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title= Neil Redfearn:'freakish events' caused six Leeds players to miss game |date=19 April 2015|accessdate=|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2015/apr/19/leeds-united-neil-redfearn|publisher=The Guardian|author= Press Association}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title= Leeds United should sack six players who pulled out of Charlton game at short notice, says former Whites captain Trevor Cherry |date=19 April 2015|accessdate=|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-3045573/Leeds-United-sack-six-players-pulled-Charlton-game-short-notice-says-former-Whites-captain-Trevor-Cherry.html|publisher=Daily Mail|author= Press Association}}</ref>\n\nOn 2 May 2015, Silvestri was one of five players nominated for the Fans Player Of The Year Award at Leeds United's official end of 2014\u201315 season awards ceremony, but lost out to eventual winner [[Alex Mowatt]].<ref>{{cite news|title= Mowatt scoops awards night double |date=2 May 2015|accessdate=|url=http://www.leedsunited.com/news/article/slzwndu1a9wb1kdweft4sskxz/title/mowatt-scoops-awards-night-double|publisher=Leeds United|author=}}</ref> After the end of the 2014\u201315 season, Silvestri after an impressive debut season proclaimed ''Life in Leeds is good. Me and my wife feel at home here''.''<ref>{{cite news|title= Goalkeeper reflects on his debut season at Elland Road|date=1 June 2015|accessdate=|url=http://www.leedsunited.com/news/article/1qzp8ek1zrw5w1pv4fm5468fy8/title/marco-hopeful-of-201516-improvement|publisher=Leeds United|author=}}</ref>\n\n====2015\u201316 season====\nAfter the signing of Goalkeeper [[Ross Turnbull]] on 15 July 2015, head coach [[Uwe R\u00f6sler]] revealed Silvestri would still be the club's number 1 goalkeeper.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/33540646|title=Ross Turnbull: Leeds United sign Barnsley goalkeeper|publisher=BBC Sport|date=15 July 2015|accessdate=15 July 2015}}</ref> Turnbull revealed he was going to challenge Silvestri for the Number 1 shirt.<ref>{{cite news|date=16 July 2015|accessdate=16 July 2015|url=http://www.leedsunited.com/news/article/2ne699mn7h3917n3ya2d5ngty/title/turnbull-vows-to-challenge-for-no1|publisher=Leeds United Official Site|title=TURNBULL VOWS TO CHALLENGE FOR NO.1}}</ref>\n\n====2016\u201317 season====\nAfter the signing of [[Robert Green]] as the club's first choice Goalkeeper, Silvestri on 5 August was given the squad number 12 shirt for the 2016\u201317 season.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.leedsunited.com/news/article/1d34ltj8uw4g21hgi949e2pbl8/title/201617-squad-numbers-confirmed |title=2016/17 SQUAD NUMBERS CONFIRMED |publisher=Leeds United |date=6 August 2016 |accessdate=6 August 2016 }}</ref> He made his first appearance of the season for Leeds on 23 August 2016, starting in Leeds' League Cup fixture against [[Luton Town]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.leedsunited.com/news/article/15gtq6yt2p00z193z1zfdakcla/title/matchday-luton-town-live!|title=MATCHDAY: LUTON- LIVE! |publisher=Leeds United |date=23 August 2016 |accessdate=23 August 2016 }}</ref> On 26 October 2016, Silvestri was the hero for Leeds, after saving 3 penalties for Leeds in their victory against [[Norwich City]] in the English League Cup, with a dramatic penalty shootout victory after a 2\u20132 draw in extra time.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.leedsunited.com/news/team-news/21284/norwich-match-report-title |title=NORWICH CITY: PENALTIES SEE LEEDS EDGE CLASSIC |work=Leeds United  |publisher= |date=26 October 2016 |accessdate=26 October 2016}}</ref>\n\nOn 29 November 2016, Silvestri started for Leeds in [[2016\u201317 EFL Cup|EFL Cup]] quarter-final match against [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]] at [[Anfield]] in a 2\u20130 defeat.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/38059968|title=Liverpool 2\u20130 Leeds United|publisher=[[BBC Sport]]|first=Jonathan|last=Jurejko|date=29 November 2016|accessdate=29 November 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Hellas Verona===\nOn 18 July 2017, Silvestri played the full 90 minutes of a closed-door friendly between Leeds and [[Bursaspor]],<ref>{{cite news|author=Phil Hay|publisher=Yorkshire Evening Post|date=18 July 2017|accessdate=19 July 2017|title=WATCH: Leeds United beaten by Bursaspor in last-minute friendly - report|url=http://www.yorkshireeveningpost.co.uk/sport/football/leeds-united/watch-leeds-united-beaten-by-bursaspor-in-last-minute-friendly-report-1-8654943}}</ref> but the next day he travelled to [[Verona]] to complete a transfer to [[Serie A]] club [[Hellas Verona F.C.|Hellas Verona]], for an undisclosed fee.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.leedsunited.com/news/team-news/22084/silvestri-makes-serie-a-move|date=19 July 2017|accessdate=19 July 2017|publisher=Leeds United|title=SILVESTRI MAKES SERIE A MOVE}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nSilvestri started his national career in the 2008 goalkeeper training camp.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.figc.it/it/204/20038/2008/11/News.shtml|title=Per rilanciare la scuola italiana, a Coverciano stage per 23 giovani |date=26 November 2008|accessdate=15 December 2011|work=FIGC|language=Italian}}</ref>\n\nSilvestri received his first cap in December 2009 from [[Francesco Rocca]] for the [[Italy national under-20 football team|Italy U20 team]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.figc.it/it/204/22834/2009/12/News.shtml|title=Quattro Nazioni: a Taranto arriva la Germania. Rocca ne convoca 18 |date=1 December 2009|accessdate=15 December 2011|work=FIGC|language=Italian}}</ref> He played that match, the round 3 of 2009\u201310 [[Italy/Germany/Switzerland under-20 Four Nations Tournament|Four Nations Tournament]], replacing [[Antonio Piccolo (footballer born 1990)|Antonio Piccolo]] in the second half. He also played the last round (round 6) in that tournament. Silvestri played twice (out of 6 games) in the 2010\u201311 edition.\n\nIn June 2011, he was picked for the [[Italy national under-21 football team|Italy Under 21s team]] by [[Ciro Ferrara]] to represent his country in the [[2011 Toulon Tournament]], serving as backup to [[Sergio Viotti (footballer)|Sergio Viotti]]. Silvestri only played once in the bronze match. After the tournament he did not receive a call-up for the [[2013 UEFA European Under-21 Football Championship qualification]].\n\nOn 17 July 2015, Ermes Fulgoni who was [[Gianluigi Buffon]]'s former goalkeeping coach at [[Parma F.C.|Parma]] described Silvestri as the heir to Buffon and tipped him to be [[Italy national football team|Italy]]'s future number 1 goalkeeper.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.figc.it/it/204/20038/2008/11/News.shtml|title=Serie A sides urged to sign Silvestri |date=17 July 2015|accessdate=17 July 2015|work=Team Talk}}</ref>\n\n==Trivia==\nSilvestri's partner is Moroccan [[Givenchy]] fashion model Sofia Jamal Eddine.<ref name = \"YP\">{{cite news|url=http://www.yorkshirepost.co.uk/sport/football/leeds-utd/leeds-united-v-wolves-silvestri-living-up-to-high-billing-of-cellino-1-6916474|title=Silvestri living up to high billing of Cellino|date=25 October 2014|accessdate=25 October 2014|work=Yorkshire Post}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://fashioncopious.typepad.com/fashioncopious/2013/12/sofia-jamal-eddine.html|title=Sofia Jamal Eddine|date=3 December 2013|accessdate=3 December 2013|work=Fashion Copious}}</ref> Silvestri also revealed that Eddine (who speaks fluent Italian and English) had been helping teach him [[English language|English]].<ref name = \"YP\"/>\n\n==Career statistics==\n{{updated|match played 3 November 2019}}<ref>{{Cite web |title= Statistics |url=http://www.soccerbase.com/players/player.sd?player_id=72015 |publisher=[[Soccerbase]] |accessdate=1 December 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"MSSW\">{{soccerway|marco-silvestri/95180|accessdate=12 October 2017}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!colspan=\"3\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|National Cup<ref>Includes [[Coppa Italia]] and [[FA Cup]]</ref>\n!colspan=\"2\"|League Cup<ref>Includes [[Football League Cup]] and [[Coppa Italia Lega Pro]]</ref>\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!Division!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|[[Modena F.C.|Modena]]\n|[[:it:Modena Football Club 2009-2010|2009\u201310]]\n|[[Serie B]]\n|0||0||1||0||0||0||1||0\n|-\n|[[A.C. ChievoVerona|Chievo]]\n|[[:it:Associazione Calcio ChievoVerona 2010-2011|2010\u201311]]\n|[[Serie A]]\n|0||0||0||0||1||0||1||0\n|-\n|[[A.C. Reggiana 1919|Reggiana]]\n|[[:it:Associazione Calcio Reggiana 1919 2011-2012|2011\u201312]]\n|[[Lega Pro Prima Divisione|Lega Pro]]\n|27||0||1||0||1||0||29||0\n|-\n|[[Calcio Padova|Padova]]\n|[[:it:Calcio Padova 2012-2013|2012\u201313]]\n|Serie B\n|25||0||0||0||0||0||25||0\n|-\n|[[A.C. ChievoVerona|Chievo]]\n|[[2013\u201314 Serie A|2013\u201314]]\n|Serie A\n|0||0||2||0||0||0||2||0\n|-\n|[[Cagliari Calcio|Cagliari]]\n|[[2013\u201314 Serie A|2013\u201314]]\n|Serie A\n|3||0||0||0||0||0||3||0\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\"|[[Leeds United F.C.|Leeds United]]\n|[[2014\u201315 Leeds United F.C. season|2014\u201315]]\n| rowspan=\"3\"|[[EFL Championship|Championship]]\n|43||0||1||0||0||0||44||0\n|-\n|[[2015\u201316 Leeds United F.C. season|2015\u201316]]\n|45||0||3||0||0||0||48||0\n|-\n|[[2016\u201317 Leeds United F.C. season|2016\u201317]]\n|0||0||2||0||4||0||6||0\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n!88!!0!!6!!0!!4!!0!!98!!0\n|-\n|rowspan=\"4\"|[[Hellas Verona F.C.|Verona]]\n|[[2017\u201318 Hellas Verona F.C. season|2017\u201318]]\n|Serie A\n|2||0||2||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||4||0\n|-\n|[[2018\u201319 Serie B|2018\u201319]]\n|Serie B\n|40||0||1||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||41||0\n|-\n|[[2019\u201320 Serie A|2019\u201320]]\n|Serie A\n|11||0||1||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||12||0\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n!53!!0!!4!!0!!0!!0!!57!!0\n|-\n!colspan=\"3\"|Career total\n!196!!0!!14!!0!!6!!0!!215!!0\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://aic.football.it/scheda/23006/silvestri-marco.htm Football.it Profile] {{in lang|it}}\n* [http://www.legaserieb.it/it/serie-bwin/calciatore;jsessionid=4E0AF3C759AE88154FF1DDBCE0BD8DF0?p_p_id=BDC_dettaglio_calciatore_WAR_LegaCalcioBDC&p_p_lifecycle=0&p_p_state=normal&p_p_mode=view&p_p_col_id=column-1&p_p_col_count=1&_BDC_dettaglio_calciatore_WAR_LegaCalcioBDC_idPersona=56496 Lega Serie B Profile] {{in lang|it}}\n* [http://www.figc.it/nazionali/DettaglioConvocato?codiceConvocato=3484&squadra=2 FIGC] {{in lang|it}}\n\n{{Hellas Verona F.C. squad}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2015}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Silvestri, Marco}}\n[[Category:Italian footballers]]\n[[Category:Italy youth international footballers]]\n[[Category:Italy under-21 international footballers]]\n[[Category:Modena F.C. players]]\n[[Category:A.C. ChievoVerona players]]\n[[Category:Reggio Audace F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Calcio Padova players]]\n[[Category:Cagliari Calcio players]]\n[[Category:Leeds United F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Hellas Verona F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Serie A players]]\n[[Category:Serie B players]]\n[[Category:Association football goalkeepers]]\n[[Category:Italian expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Italian expatriate sportspeople in England]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in England]]\n[[Category:People from the Province of Reggio Emilia]]\n[[Category:1991 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football biography\n| name               = Marco Silvestri\n| fullname           = Marco Silvestri<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.efl.com/documents/professional-retained-report-2015-16549-3151378.pdf |title=EFL: Retained list: 2015/16 |publisher=English Football League |page=29 |accessdate=29 June 2016 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161202052144/http://www.efl.com/documents/professional-retained-report-2015-16549-3151378.pdf |archivedate=2 December 2016 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n| image              = \n| birth_date          = {{Birth date and age|1991|3|2|df=y}}\n| birth_place         = [[Castelnovo ne' Monti]], Italy\n| height              = {{Height|m=1.91}}\n| position            = [[Goalkeeper (association football)|Goalkeeper]]\n| currentclub         = [[Hellas Verona F.C.|Hellas Verona]]\n| clubnumber          = 1\n| youthyears1         = 2009\u20132011 | youthclubs1  = [[Modena F.C.|Modena]]\n| youthyears2         = 2010\u20132011 | youthclubs2  = \u2192 [[A.C. ChievoVerona|Chievo]] (loan)\n| clubs1  = [[A.C. ChievoVerona|Chievo]]\n| clubs2  = \u2192 [[A.C. Reggiana 1919|Reggiana]] (loan)\n| years1              = 2011\u20132014 \n| years2              = 2011\u20132012 \n| caps1  = 0  \n| caps2  = 27 \n| goals1  = 0 \n| goals2  = 0 \n| nationalteam1       = [[Italy national under-20 football team|Italy U20]]\n| nationalteam2       = [[Italy national under-21 football team|Italy U21]]\n| nationalyears1      = 2009\u20132011\n| nationalyears2      = 2011\n| nationalcaps1       = 5\n| nationalcaps2       = 1\n| nationalgoals1      = 0\n| nationalgoals2      = 0\n| club-update         = 18:01, 8 November 2019 (UTC)\n| nationalteam-update =\n| years3              = 2012\u20132013 \n| caps3  = 25 \n| goals3  = 0 \n| clubs3  = \u2192 [[Calcio Padova|Padova]] (loan)\n| years4              = 2014      \n| caps4  = 3  \n| goals4  = 0 \n| clubs4  = \u2192 [[Cagliari Calcio|Cagliari]] (loan) \n| years5              = 2014\u20132017     \n| caps5  = 88 \n| goals5  = 0 \n| clubs5  = [[Leeds United F.C.|Leeds United]]\n| years6              = 2017\u2013     \n| caps6  = 53\n| goals6  = 0 \n| clubs6  = [[Hellas Verona F.C.|Hellas Verona]]\n}}\n'''Marco Silvestri''' (born 2 March 1991) is an Italian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for Italian club [[Hellas Verona F.C.|Hellas Verona]]. Before joining Verona in 2017, he played in England for [[Leeds United F.C.|Leeds United]] and in Italy for [[A.C. ChievoVerona|Chievo]], [[A.C. Reggiana 1919|Reggiana]], [[Calcio Padova|Padova]] and [[Cagliari Calcio|Cagliari]]. Silvestri has represented his country at [[Italy national under-20 football team|under-20]] and [[Italy national under-21 football team|under-21 level]].\n\n==Club career==\n\n===Modena===\nBorn in [[Castelnovo ne' Monti]], the [[Province of Reggio Emilia]], Emilia\u2013Romagna, Silvestri started his career at [[Emilia (region of Italy)|Emilia]] club [[Modena F.C.|Modena]]. He was the third keeper behind [[Enrico Alfonso]] and [[Antonio Narciso]] in 2009\u201310 season.\n\n===Chievo===\nIn August 2010, Silvestri was signed by [[Serie A]] club [[A.C. ChievoVerona|Chievo]] on a temporary deal, with an option to purchase half of his registration rights.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.chievocalcio.tv/it/content/mercato-9|title=MERCATO|date=18 August 2010|accessdate=28 August 2010|work=AC ChievoVerona|language=Italian|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101122075607/http://chievocalcio.tv/it/content/mercato-9|archivedate=22 November 2010|df=dmy-all}}</ref> He was the third keeper of the team, behind [[Stefano Sorrentino]] and [[Lorenzo Squizzi]]. Silvestri also became the first choice keeper at [[Campionato Nazionale Primavera|the \"spring\" under-20 team]]. In June 2011 Chievo exercised the option to sign Silvestri in a [[co-ownership (football)|co-ownership deal]], for \u20ac300,000.<ref name=Chievo2011bilancio>AC ChievoVerona Report and Accounts on 30 June 2011 {{in lang|it}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.chievoverona.tv/it/news/compropriet%C3%A0-parolo-al-cesena-riscattato-silvestri|title=Compropriet\u00e0: Parolo al Cesena, riscattato Silvestri|trans-title=Co-ownership: Parolo to Cesena, redeemed Silvestri|date=22 June 2011|accessdate=24 June 2011|work=AC ChievoVerona|language=Italian|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110625021808/http://www.chievoverona.tv/it/news/compropriet%C3%A0-parolo-al-cesena-riscattato-silvestri|archivedate=25 June 2011|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n====Reggiana loan====\nSilvestri returned to [[Reggio Emilia]] for [[A.C. Reggiana 1919|Reggiana]] in July to replace [[Niccol\u00f2 Manfredini]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.chievoverona.tv/it/news/marco-silvestri-prestito-alla-reggiana|title=Marco Silvestri in prestito alla Reggiana|trans-title=Marco Silvestri temporary to Reggiana|date=4 July 2011|accessdate=8 July 2011|work=AC ChievoVerona|language=Italian|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120321093352/http://www.chievoverona.tv/it/news/marco-silvestri-prestito-alla-reggiana|archivedate=21 March 2012|df=dmy-all}}</ref> However Silvestri became the backup of Niccol\u00f2 Bellucci since round 12. After the winter break Silvestri re-affirmed as first choice. In June 2012 Chievo signed Silvestri outright for another \u20ac150,000.<ref>AC ChievoVerona Srl ''bilancio'' (financial report and accounts) on 30 June 2012 {{in lang|it}}, [http://www.registroimprese.it PDF purchased from Italian CCIAA]</ref>\n\n====Padova loan====\nIn July 2012 he left for [[Calcio Padova|Padova]]. The club failed to renew the loan of fellow U21 internationals [[Mattia Perin]]. Silvestri wore no.1 shirt for Padova in new season and would compete with ex-internationals [[Ivan Pelizzoli]] who acted as second-choice last season. However, on the last day of the transfer window, Pelizzoli rejoined Perin in [[Delfino Pescara 1936|Pescara]] and [[Luca Anania]], who became second choice in the same club, left for Padova.\n\n====Cagliari loan====\nOn 30 January 2014, Silvestri signed for [[Cagliari Calcio|Cagliari]] on loan, including the option for [[Cagliari Calcio|Cagliari]] to acquire half his ownership rights at the end of the season, the move saw [[Cagliari Calcio|Cagliari]] first choice Goalkeeper [[Michael Agazzi]] join [[A.C. Chievo Verona|Chievo]] on a permanent deal.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cagliaricalcio.net/news/15547/silvestri-al-cagliari.html|title=Silvestri al Cagliari|date=30 January 2014|accessdate=22 May 2014|publisher=Cagliari Calcio|language=Italian}}</ref>\n\nSilverstri was given the number 1 shirt. He made his debut for the club in the [[Serie A]] match against [[Parma F.C.|Parma]] on 27 April, coming into the side for [[Vlada Avramov]], keeping a clean sheet on his debut in a 1\u20130 win. On 6 May, Silvestri started the match against [[S.S.C. Napoli]], a game in which Silvestri was given a straight red card in a 3\u20130 loss after fouling [[Goran Pandev]]. After returning from suspension he returned for the final match of the season in a 3\u20130 loss against [[Juventus F.C.|Juventus]].\n\nOn 27 June, Silvestri's agent [[Francesco Romano (footballer)|Francesco Romano]], revealed that Silvestri was in talks over a move to English club Leeds United, owned by former [[Cagliari Calcio|Cagliari]] owner [[Massimo Cellino]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://translate.google.com/translate?hl=en&sl=it&u=http://gazzettadireggio.gelocal.it/sport/2014/06/23/news/marco-silvestri-oggi-firma-per-il-leeds-1.9479779&prev=/search%3Fq%3DMarco%2BSilvestri%2Bleeds%26biw%3D1525%26bih%3D674|title=marco-silvestri-oggi-firma-per-il-leeds|date=27 June 2014|accessdate=27 June 2014|work=Gazzetta Di Reggio|language=Italian}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.express.co.uk/sport/football/485254/Leeds-close-in-on-TRIPLE-swoop-with-Ross-McCormack-future-still-uncertain|title=The Italian job! Leeds close in on TRIPLE swoop with Ross McCormack future still uncertain|date=27 June 2014|accessdate=27 June 2014|work=The Express}}</ref>\n\n===Leeds United===\n\n====2014\u201315 Season====\nOn 8 July 2014, Silvestri left Chievo for a fee of \u20ac1&nbsp;million,<ref>{{cite book|title=A.C. Chievo-Verona S.r.l. bilancio al 30-06-2015|trans-title=A.C. Chievo-Verona S.r.l. financial report on 30-06-2015|date=2015|publisher=Italian C.C.I.A.A.|language=Italian|page=24}}</ref> and signed a four-year contract with English club Leeds United along with fellow Italian [[Tommaso Bianchi]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.yorkshireeveningpost.co.uk/sport/leeds-united/latest-whites-news/leeds-united-complete-silvestri-and-bianchi-signings-1-6718003|title=Leeds United complete Silvestri and Bianchi signings|date=8 July 2014|accessdate=8 July 2014|work=Yorkshire Evening Post}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.yorkshireeveningpost.co.uk/sport/leeds-united/latest-whites-news/leeds-united-new-faces-highlight-fresh-approach-to-transfer-market-1-6730859|title=Leeds United: New faces highlight fresh approach to transfer market|date=15 July 2014|accessdate=15 July 2014|work=Yorkshire Evening Post}}</ref> Silvestri's first appearance for Leeds came on 11 July in Leeds' first pre\u2013season game, which resulted in a 16\u20130 victory against Italian side FC Gherdeina.<ref name=\"Leeds United hammer Italian minnows FC Gherdeina 16-0\">{{Cite news\n| title = Leeds United hammer Italian minnows FC Gherdeina 16\u20130\n| url = http://www.yorkshireeveningpost.co.uk/sport/leeds-united/latest-whites-news/leeds-united-hammer-italian-minnows-fc-gherdeina-16-0-1-6723461\n| publisher = YEP\n| date = 11 July 2014\n| accessdate = 11 July 2014}}</ref> On 1 August, Silvestri was assigned the Leeds number 1 shirt for the 2014\u201315 season.<ref name=\"SQUAD NUMBERS RELEASED\">{{cite web |url=http://www.leedsunited.com/news/article/1wncxa2kw0zr11fmlyjr0m3t53/title/squad-numbers-released|title=SQUAD NUMBERS RELEASED|publisher=Leeds United|date=1 August 2014 |first=|last=|accessdate=1 August 2014}}</ref> Silvestri made his debut for Leeds on 9 August against [[Millwall F.C.|Millwall]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Millwall v Leeds|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/28646426|publisher=BBC Sport|accessdate=9 August 2014}}</ref> Silvestri kept his first clean sheet for Leeds in his home debut at [[Elland Road]] on 16 August in Leeds' 1\u20130 victory against [[Middlesbrough F.C.|Middlesbrough]] after a goal by [[Billy Sharp]].<ref>{{cite web|title=DEBUTANT SHARP BLUNTS BORO|url=http://www.leedsunited.com/news/article/5q0uro0bzx4a1ry3sxp6c1hkz/title/debutant-sharp-blunts-boro|publisher=Leeds United Official Site|accessdate=16 August 2014}}</ref>\n\nSilvestri kept a clean sheet and won the man of the match award after a string of saves in Leeds' 1\u20130 win on 30 August against [[Bolton Wanderers F.C.|Bolton Wanderers]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Leeds Vs Bolton Wanderers|date=30 August 2014|accessdate=30 August 2014|url=http://www.leedsunited.com/news/article/3fqrhs11d9xa18kq62h7zlkrz/title/bolton-live!|publisher=Leeds United official website|author=}}</ref> The performance led to him being named in the Football League team of the week.<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20140904004129/http://www.football-league.co.uk/features/20140901/sky-bet-football-league-team-of-the-week-300814-310814_2293307_4113706 Sky Bet Football League Team of the Week 30/08/14 \u2013 31/08/14]. Football-league.co.uk. 1 September 2014.</ref> Silvestri's impressive form continued against [[A.F.C. Bournemouth|Bournemouth]] in a 3\u20131 win.<ref>{{cite news|title= Bournemouth 1 \u2013 3 Leeds |date=16 September 2014|accessdate=16 September 2014|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/29120574|publisher=BBC Sport|author=}}</ref> With Silvestri earning praise from Caretaker Head Coach [[Neil Redfearn]] after a string of impressive saves to help keep Leeds in the game when they were 1\u20130 down.<ref>{{cite news|title= Neil Redfearn praised Leeds after win over Bournemouth |date=17 September 2014|accessdate=17 September 2014|url=http://www1.skysports.com/football/news/11688/9474081/redfearns-talking-italian|publisher=Sky Sports|author=}}</ref>\n\nSilvestri received the Man of the Match Award after keeping a clean sheet against the then league leaders Middlesbrough 1\u20130 on 21 February 2015.<ref>{{cite news |title=Middlesbrough 0 Leeds United 1: Mowatt shocks leaders Boro|url=http://www.yorkshirepost.co.uk/sport/football/leeds-utd/middlesbrough-0-leeds-unted-1-mowatt-shocks-leaders-boro-1-7119053 |date=21 February 2015 |accessdate=21 February 2015 |publisher=Yorkshire Evening Post}}</ref> On 4 March, Silvestri saved a late penalty from [[Daryl Murphy]] to help earn Leeds a 2\u20131 victory against [[Ipswich Town F.C.|Ipswich Town]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Leeds United: Mowatt is becoming a free-kick specialist|url=http://www.yorkshireeveningpost.co.uk/sport/leeds-united/latest-whites-news/leeds-united-mowatt-is-becoming-a-free-kick-specialist-1-7141861 |date=4 March 2015 |accessdate=4 March 2015 |publisher=Yorkshire Evening Post}}</ref>\n\nOn 18 April 2015, Silvestri was one of six [[Massimo Cellino]] signings (alongside [[Mirco Antenucci]], [[Giuseppe Bellusci]], [[Souleymane Doukara]], [[Dario Del Fabro]], [[Edgar \u00c7ani]]) who controversially pulled out of the squad with an 'injury' the day before a 2\u20131 loss against [[Charlton Athletic F.C.|Charlton Athletic]].<ref>{{cite news|title= Leeds United striker Steve Morison left bemused by latest chaos at Elland Road |date=19 April 2015|accessdate=|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-3046059/Leeds-United-striker-Steve-Morrison-left-bemused-latest-chaos-Elland-Road.html|publisher=Daily Mail|author= Press Association}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title= Neil Redfearn:'freakish events' caused six Leeds players to miss game |date=19 April 2015|accessdate=|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2015/apr/19/leeds-united-neil-redfearn|publisher=The Guardian|author= Press Association}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title= Leeds United should sack six players who pulled out of Charlton game at short notice, says former Whites captain Trevor Cherry |date=19 April 2015|accessdate=|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-3045573/Leeds-United-sack-six-players-pulled-Charlton-game-short-notice-says-former-Whites-captain-Trevor-Cherry.html|publisher=Daily Mail|author= Press Association}}</ref>\n\nOn 2 May 2015, Silvestri was one of five players nominated for the Fans Player Of The Year Award at Leeds United's official end of 2014\u201315 season awards ceremony, but lost out to eventual winner [[Alex Mowatt]].<ref>{{cite news|title= Mowatt scoops awards night double |date=2 May 2015|accessdate=|url=http://www.leedsunited.com/news/article/slzwndu1a9wb1kdweft4sskxz/title/mowatt-scoops-awards-night-double|publisher=Leeds United|author=}}</ref> After the end of the 2014\u201315 season, Silvestri after an impressive debut season proclaimed ''Life in Leeds is good. Me and my wife feel at home here''.''<ref>{{cite news|title= Goalkeeper reflects on his debut season at Elland Road|date=1 June 2015|accessdate=|url=http://www.leedsunited.com/news/article/1qzp8ek1zrw5w1pv4fm5468fy8/title/marco-hopeful-of-201516-improvement|publisher=Leeds United|author=}}</ref>\n\n====2015\u201316 season====\nAfter the signing of Goalkeeper [[Ross Turnbull]] on 15 July 2015, head coach [[Uwe R\u00f6sler]] revealed Silvestri would still be the club's number 1 goalkeeper.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/33540646|title=Ross Turnbull: Leeds United sign Barnsley goalkeeper|publisher=BBC Sport|date=15 July 2015|accessdate=15 July 2015}}</ref> Turnbull revealed he was going to challenge Silvestri for the Number 1 shirt.<ref>{{cite news|date=16 July 2015|accessdate=16 July 2015|url=http://www.leedsunited.com/news/article/2ne699mn7h3917n3ya2d5ngty/title/turnbull-vows-to-challenge-for-no1|publisher=Leeds United Official Site|title=TURNBULL VOWS TO CHALLENGE FOR NO.1}}</ref>\n\n====2016\u201317 season====\nAfter the signing of [[Robert Green]] as the club's first choice Goalkeeper, Silvestri on 5 August was given the squad number 12 shirt for the 2016\u201317 season.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.leedsunited.com/news/article/1d34ltj8uw4g21hgi949e2pbl8/title/201617-squad-numbers-confirmed |title=2016/17 SQUAD NUMBERS CONFIRMED |publisher=Leeds United |date=6 August 2016 |accessdate=6 August 2016 }}</ref> He made his first appearance of the season for Leeds on 23 August 2016, starting in Leeds' League Cup fixture against [[Luton Town]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.leedsunited.com/news/article/15gtq6yt2p00z193z1zfdakcla/title/matchday-luton-town-live!|title=MATCHDAY: LUTON- LIVE! |publisher=Leeds United |date=23 August 2016 |accessdate=23 August 2016 }}</ref> On 26 October 2016, Silvestri was the hero for Leeds, after saving 3 penalties for Leeds in their victory against [[Norwich City]] in the English League Cup, with a dramatic penalty shootout victory after a 2\u20132 draw in extra time.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.leedsunited.com/news/team-news/21284/norwich-match-report-title |title=NORWICH CITY: PENALTIES SEE LEEDS EDGE CLASSIC |work=Leeds United  |publisher= |date=26 October 2016 |accessdate=26 October 2016}}</ref>\n\nOn 29 November 2016, Silvestri started for Leeds in [[2016\u201317 EFL Cup|EFL Cup]] quarter-final match against [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]] at [[Anfield]] in a 2\u20130 defeat.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/38059968|title=Liverpool 2\u20130 Leeds United|publisher=[[BBC Sport]]|first=Jonathan|last=Jurejko|date=29 November 2016|accessdate=29 November 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Hellas Verona===\nOn 18 July 2017, Silvestri played the full 90 minutes of a closed-door friendly between Leeds and [[Bursaspor]],<ref>{{cite news|author=Phil Hay|publisher=Yorkshire Evening Post|date=18 July 2017|accessdate=19 July 2017|title=WATCH: Leeds United beaten by Bursaspor in last-minute friendly - report|url=http://www.yorkshireeveningpost.co.uk/sport/football/leeds-united/watch-leeds-united-beaten-by-bursaspor-in-last-minute-friendly-report-1-8654943}}</ref> but the next day he travelled to [[Verona]] to complete a transfer to [[Serie A]] club [[Hellas Verona F.C.|Hellas Verona]], for an undisclosed fee.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.leedsunited.com/news/team-news/22084/silvestri-makes-serie-a-move|date=19 July 2017|accessdate=19 July 2017|publisher=Leeds United|title=SILVESTRI MAKES SERIE A MOVE}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nSilvestri started his national career in the 2008 goalkeeper training camp.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.figc.it/it/204/20038/2008/11/News.shtml|title=Per rilanciare la scuola italiana, a Coverciano stage per 23 giovani |date=26 November 2008|accessdate=15 December 2011|work=FIGC|language=Italian}}</ref>\n\nSilvestri received his first cap in December 2009 from [[Francesco Rocca]] for the [[Italy national under-20 football team|Italy U20 team]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.figc.it/it/204/22834/2009/12/News.shtml|title=Quattro Nazioni: a Taranto arriva la Germania. Rocca ne convoca 18 |date=1 December 2009|accessdate=15 December 2011|work=FIGC|language=Italian}}</ref> He played that match, the round 3 of 2009\u201310 [[Italy/Germany/Switzerland under-20 Four Nations Tournament|Four Nations Tournament]], replacing [[Antonio Piccolo (footballer born 1990)|Antonio Piccolo]] in the second half. He also played the last round (round 6) in that tournament. Silvestri played twice (out of 6 games) in the 2010\u201311 edition.\n\nIn June 2011, he was picked for the [[Italy national under-21 football team|Italy Under 21s team]] by [[Ciro Ferrara]] to represent his country in the [[2011 Toulon Tournament]], serving as backup to [[Sergio Viotti (footballer)|Sergio Viotti]]. Silvestri only played once in the bronze match. After the tournament he did not receive a call-up for the [[2013 UEFA European Under-21 Football Championship qualification]].\n\nOn 17 July 2015, Ermes Fulgoni who was [[Gianluigi Buffon]]'s former goalkeeping coach at [[Parma F.C.|Parma]] described Silvestri as the heir to Buffon and tipped him to be [[Italy national football team|Italy]]'s future number 1 goalkeeper.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.figc.it/it/204/20038/2008/11/News.shtml|title=Serie A sides urged to sign Silvestri |date=17 July 2015|accessdate=17 July 2015|work=Team Talk}}</ref>\n\n==Trivia==\nSilvestri's partner is Moroccan [[Givenchy]] fashion model Sofia Jamal Eddine.<ref name = \"YP\">{{cite news|url=http://www.yorkshirepost.co.uk/sport/football/leeds-utd/leeds-united-v-wolves-silvestri-living-up-to-high-billing-of-cellino-1-6916474|title=Silvestri living up to high billing of Cellino|date=25 October 2014|accessdate=25 October 2014|work=Yorkshire Post}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://fashioncopious.typepad.com/fashioncopious/2013/12/sofia-jamal-eddine.html|title=Sofia Jamal Eddine|date=3 December 2013|accessdate=3 December 2013|work=Fashion Copious}}</ref> Silvestri also revealed that Eddine (who speaks fluent Italian and English) had been helping teach him [[English language|English]].<ref name = \"YP\"/>\n\n==Career statistics==\n{{updated|match played 3 November 2019}} <ref>{{Cite web\n|title= Statistics\n|url=http://www.soccerbase.com/players/player.sd?player_id=72015\n|publisher=[[Soccerbase]]\n|accessdate=1 December 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"MSSW\">{{soccerway|marco-silvestri/95180|accessdate=12 October 2017}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n!rowspan=2|Club\n!rowspan=2|Season\n!colspan=3|League\n!colspan=2|National Cup<ref>Includes [[Coppa Italia]] and [[FA Cup]]</ref>\n!colspan=2|League Cup<ref>Includes [[Football League Cup]] and [[Coppa Italia Lega Pro]]</ref>\n!colspan=2|Total\n|-\n!Division!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|[[Modena F.C.|Modena]]\n|[[:it:Modena Football Club 2009-2010|2009\u201310]]\n|[[Serie B]]\n|0||0||1||0||0||0||1||0\n|-\n|[[A.C. ChievoVerona|Chievo]]\n|[[:it:Associazione Calcio ChievoVerona 2010-2011|2010\u201311]]\n|[[Serie A]]\n|0||0||0||0||1||0||1||0\n|-\n|[[A.C. Reggiana 1919|Reggiana]]\n|[[:it:Associazione Calcio Reggiana 1919 2011-2012|2011\u201312]]\n|[[Lega Pro Prima Divisione|Lega Pro]]\n|27||0||1||0||1||0||29||0\n|-\n|[[Calcio Padova|Padova]]\n|[[:it:Calcio Padova 2012-2013|2012\u201313]]\n|[[Serie B]]\n|25||0||0||0||0||0||25||0\n|-\n|[[A.C. ChievoVerona|Chievo]]\n|[[2013\u201314 Serie A|2013\u201314]]\n|[[Serie A]]\n|0||0||2||0||0||0||2||0\n|-\n|[[Cagliari Calcio|Cagliari]]\n|[[2013\u201314 Serie A|2013\u201314]]\n|[[Serie A]]\n|3||0||0||0||0||0||3||0\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\"|[[Leeds United F.C.|Leeds United]]\